title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place sugar, butter and milk into heavy pan and cook over medium heat until it reaches soft ball stage or 235° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Pour into 2 (8 x 8 x 2-inch) greased pans.
Cut into squares when cool.
Makes 4 1/2 pounds.

title: spaghetti sauce of three meats(serves 12)
directions: Brown the meat pieces in hot fat with the sliced onion and garlic.
Add the strained tomatoes and paste.
Stir in the seasoning and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add the lemon juice to taste.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill for one hour. Serve with raw vegetables.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix the catsup and the Coke in a deep 2-quart saucepan.
Place chicken in saucepan.
Low boil the contents, uncovered, in the pan until chicken is tender, approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: jello pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and melted butter.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Let cool. Spread 2 cups powdered sugar, Cool Whip, cream cheese and mini marshmallow mixture over pretzels.
Pour strawberry jello and strawberries and water mixture over white layer.
Chill until firm.

title: cheese and rice krispies biscuits
directions: Cream the cream cheese, margarine, salts, Tabasco and paprika well.
Add flour and mix well.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well. Pinch off small amount and roll in palm of hand into small balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and press down with fork.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan at once to cool.
Yields 75 biscuits.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Bring margarine, cocoa, oil and water to a boil and then add sugar, salt and flour.
Beat well.
Dissolve soda in sour milk and add to the mixture, along with eggs and vanilla.
Beat well and pour in greased 12 x 18 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes good bars.
Nuts may be added.
Frost with chocolate icing.

title: jeanne's favorite cheese ball
directions: Mix together cream cheese and pineapple.
When smooth, add green pepper, onion, salt and 1 cup of the pecans.
Chill mixture (overnight is best).
Form into 2 balls and roll in remaining cup of pecans.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine and pour into buttered dish; 8 x 8 square works well.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Mix together in a large bowl the dry yeast, sugar, salt and warm milk.
Stir until yeast dissolves.
Add shortening and let stand 5 minutes.
Mix in flour with a wooden spoon until dough begins to leave the sides of the bowl.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer all ingredients in the order given in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Heat in a 350° oven for a few minutes until cheese is melted.
May refrigerate and heat right before serving. Serve with large dip chips.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together and add eggs, bananas and nuts.
Add flour, baking soda and vanilla.
Combine all ingredients and place in a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 13 pan at 375° until brown, approximately 1 hour.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix butter by hand with peanut butter and confectioners sugar (add sugar 1/2 box at a time).
Roll into balls and chill in refrigerator.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip candy into chocolate mix.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix all together in an angel food pan (greased). Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Take 2 cups of apples.
Peel and slice them.
Put in bottom of a baking dish.
Cut bread into strips and place over the apple slices.
In a bowl cream margarine, sugar, egg, vanilla and cinnamon.
Spread over the bread strips.
Bake for 35 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Peel potatoes; cube and boil for 20 minutes.
Cook ground beef until brown; drain.
Mix ground beef and mushroom soup in casserole dish.
Top with drained green beans.
Drain potatoes; add milk, butter, salt and pepper and mash with old fashioned hand-held vegetable masher.
Spoon potatoes on top of green beans; dot with butter.
Bake uncovered in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes. Serves 5. Yummy!
Very easy, too; my family loves it!

title: pumpkin pancakes
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, baking powder, pumpkin pie spice and salt in a large bowl. Combine milk, pumpkin, egg an oil in a small bowl; mix will. Add to flour mixture. Stir just until moistened; batter may be lumpy.

title: taco casserole
directions: Crush corn chips and cover bottom of greased dish.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Cut onion and add to beef.
Add taco seasoning mix and tomato sauce.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Place over corn chips.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, covered.
Add crushed corn chips on top and bake 5 more minutes, uncovered.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cut together powdered sugar, peanut butter and crushed graham crackers; mix well.
Melt butter or margarine; add to mixture. Press into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Melt peanut butter with chocolate bits; pour on top.
Refrigerate.
When set, cut into squares.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add pumpkin, dates or raisins and mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and nuts. Drop on cookie sheet and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken fried coon
directions: Clean good
inside
and
out.
Be
sure
to
remove the kernel shaped
glands
under
arm	pits
and between the legs. Take off as	much
fat
as
you can.
Cut into pieces; roll in batter and flour.
Fry
brown in deep fat and remove to roaster.
Season well with salt and pepper.
Make gravy from frying fat and pour	over the meat.
Add water and cook in oven until tender.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a large soup pot, except shrimp.
Cook shrimp separately, then add to broth.
Let soup steep for 1 hour before serving.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix
all
dry
ingredients
and stir well.
Store in an airtight container.
Shake well each time you go to use any of the mix.
Use
3 teaspoons of mix to an 8-ounce cup of boiling water when ready to serve.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: Pour enough
cold
water
on
corned beef in Dutch oven just to cover.
Add
small
onion, cut into fourths and the garlic. Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beef is almost
tender,
about 1 hour and 4 minutes.
Skim fat from broth. Add the 6 small onions, the carrots, potatoes and turnips.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.	Remove beef;
keep warm.
Add cabbage.
Heat
to	boiling;
reduce heat.	Simmer uncovered until vegetables
are
tender,
about
minutes. Serves 6.

title: chickpea and potato salad
directions: Put diced potatoes in small saucepan.
Cover with water and cook until tender (about 10 minutes).
Drain and cool.
Combine potatoes with remaining ingredients and toss.
May add red pepper sauce for spicier touch.
Great with barbecue meat.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix pork and beans, onion, mustard, sugar and bacon bits. Place in baking dish.
Place pineapple rings over beans with 1/2 wiener through pineapple hole.
Bake 15 minutes at

title: kahlua
directions: Combine water and sugar.
Bring to boil and boil 3 minutes. Cool.
Add vanilla and instant coffee which has been dissolved in 1/2 cup water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into dark bottles and age 2 weeks.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: monkey bread (pinch me cake)
directions: Bring to a boil and keep warm 1 cup sugar, 1 stick oleo and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Mix in a plastic bag 1/2 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Cut canned biscuits into fourths.
Shake 1 can biscuits in bag of sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Then place each biscuit piece in a well-greased pan.
Pour 3 tablespoons of syrup mixture over biscuits.
Put 2nd and 3rd can in pan as directed. After final can of biscuits, pour remaining syrup over top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool 5 minutes.

title: seafood linguine
directions: In a pan, melt butter.
Add onions and mushrooms; simmer until transparent.
Add tomatoes and seasonings; cook for 15 minutes. Add fan-tailed shrimp; simmer for 5 minutes.
Add scallops; simmer for 5 minutes.
Add cheese; simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over linguine.

title: french canadian meat pie(tortiere)
directions: Combine pork, beef, onion and garlic in large heated skillet. Cook, stirring often, until meats lose pink color.
Stir in poultry seasoning, salt, celery salt, pepper, sage and water; cover.
Simmer for 20 minutes; uncover.
Simmer for 10 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in mashed potatoes.
Cool.

title: coal miner's pie
directions: Crush Oreos and set 1 cup aside.
Melt stick of margarine and pour over Oreos.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix 2 packages of instant vanilla pudding, cream cheese and milk.
Put on top of first mixture.
Add Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle the reserved 1 cup of Oreo crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate chip cookies(better than toll house!)
directions: In large bowl, use electric mixer to cream together the first 4 ingredients, then beat in eggs and vanilla.
Remove beaters. Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Stir into first mixture by hand, then stir in the chocolate chips.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Remove to waxed paper to cool.
Makes about 3 dozen big cookies.

title: taco dip
directions: In round 10-inch glass baking dish, spread cream cheese over bottom.
Spread chili over this layer.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over top to form third layer.
Microwave 2 to 3 minutes until cheese melts.
Serve hot with corn chips.

title: hello dollys
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add, one layer at a time, graham crackers, chocolate chips, coconut, nuts and Eagle Brand milk (pour milk over top of everything).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Drain fruit. Add cool whip, cottage cheese and jello. Mix all together well and refrigerate.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package. In large skillet, brown ground beef and onions; drain off excess fat. Add taco seasoning, water and corn. Simmer 10 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in mixed vegetables. Sprinkle 1/3 corn chips over bottom of a 9 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Add half the meat mixture and top with half the enchilada sauce; sprinkle with half the cheese. Repeat layers, beginning with 1/3 corn chips and ending with cheese. Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: hamburg stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat. Add meat and brown. Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms. Cook 5 minutes. Add soup and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream. Heat thoroughly.

title: german apple pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs, flour and milk.
Divide butter or margarine between 2 (8 or 9-inch) round cake pans. Place pans in oven just until butter or margarine melts.
Remove pans from oven and rotate pans to coat thoroughly.

title: easy nacho dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Bring cream cheese to room temperature and spread on bottom of 9 x 13
baking dish. Spread chili on cream cheese, then the salsa. Top with the cheddar cheese and bake until hot and bubbly. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: best ever corn
directions: Cook corn per package directions (omit salt).
Melt butter. Add cream cheese, milk, garlic salt and pepper and stir until smooth.
Drain corn and stir into cream cheese mixture.
Serve hot. Serves 3 to 4.

title: lazy day cobbler
directions: Place butter in deep dish and place in oven to melt at 350°. Beat 1 cup sugar, flour and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Empty fruit (not drained) over batter and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add next 4 and mix well.
Fold in flour, rhubarb and nuts.
Spray Pam on 2 bread pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and let cool.
Freezes well.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix warm water and yeast.
Set aside.
Measure flour and sugar; sift together.
Put buttermilk in large bowl with oil.
Add other ingredients all at once.
Store in refrigerator overnight. Work up into biscuits and bake at 375° for 20 minutes until good and brown.
You can use part and store in refrigerator up to 4 weeks.

title: fancy baked beans
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in shortening until golden.
Toss mushrooms with it.
Mix with other ingredients.
Add frankfurters. Add canned beans.
Bake in greased casserole 1 to 1 1/2 hours in 350° to 375° oven.
(Cover when crust gets too dry.) Stir 2 or 3 times while baking.

title: texas hot cocoa cake
directions: Melt butter with liquid shortening, cocoa and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and stir.
Sift sugar and flour in a large bowl.
Pour liquid mixture over flour mixture; beat until smooth.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, cinnamon and vanilla, mixing well.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sassy black bean soup
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat until hot.
Add onion and garlic; saut 5 minutes or until tender.
Stir in beans and next 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in lime juice. Ladle into bowls and garnish with cilantro, if desired.
Makes six one-cup servings.

title: oatmeal chocolate bars
directions: In a double boiler, melt chocolate and butterscotch chips, milk, 2 tablespoons of butter and salt.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread 3/4 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour chocolate chip mixture over the flour mixture.
Crumble remaining flour mixture over chocolate.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool.
Ready to serve.

title: lemon curd
directions: Grate lemon rind into blender.
Squeeze lemons and strain juice into blender. Add eggs and sugar. Turn on motor and add hot melted butter gradually.
Place in a heavy saucepan and cook over moderate heat for 4 minutes until thickened.
Place in two small containers. Chill and serve on toast for breakfast or use in tarts.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Pour oil over crackers; mix well.
Scatter dry mix and seasonings over crackers.
Mix again.
It will look oily but crackers will absorb oil as it stands.
Do not bake.
Store covered.
Keeps well.

title: halloween pumpkins
directions: Soften cream cheese in mixing bowl.
Gradually add all ingredients except 1/4 of the powdered sugar.
Mix in flavoring and coloring.
Roll by teaspoon into ball about the size of a large grape.
Flatten slightly and use back of knife blade to press grooves into the sides to look like a pumpkin.
Press a clove (flat side down) into top of each pumpkin for a stem.
Let dry slightly and enjoy.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Beat the eggs slightly. Add salt, flour, cream and melted butter.
Bake at 375° on hot griddle.

title: sirloin stir-fry
directions: Cut sirloin tip into pieces in a medium bowl.
Marinate 30 minutes in soy sauce, 1 teaspoon oil, cornstarch, pepper and garlic salt.
In large skillet or wok, put 2 tablespoons oil. Heat 1 minute.
Add meat; stir quickly over high heat until browned.
Put back in same bowl.

title: avery island deviled shrimp(club member: leslie jordan)
directions: Mix egg and salt.
Dip shrimp into egg mixture, then coat with bread crumbs.
Melt butter in medium skillet.
Add shrimp and brown on both sides.
Arrange shrimp on rice.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Fry minced onion in bacon grease.
Add tomato sauce, water and spices.
Simmer slowly until thick.
May also be used as steak sauce.

title: strawberry buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple with jello, dissolve & cool. Add buttermilk & nuts. Fold in cool whip.
Chill.

title: spaghetti slaw
directions: Mix cooked spaghetti, scallions, cabbage, salt and green pepper.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and milk for the dressing; pour on top.
Stir together.
Refrigerate.
Serve chilled.
Yields 4 servings.

title: two-step cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar in large bowl, with electric mixer on high speed, until smooth.
Gently stir in lemon juice and whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Spoon the cherry pie filling on top of pie.
Refrigerate until firm.
(Other flavors of pie filling may be used instead.)

title: la. fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, mix all fruit together.
Pour peach pie filling over the fruit and fold over until mixed.
Chill before serving.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Boil 8 minutes.
Great on ice cream.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix together with a spoon margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; stir.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to margarine mixture.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and place on greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine eggs and sugar in mixer bowl.
Beat at high speed until light and fluffy.
Add oil and pumpkin.
Beat well.
Mix flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and nutmeg together. Add to batter, one cup at a time, beating at low speed just until blended.
Pour into ungreased 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool in pan for several minutes.
Remove to plate to cool completely.
Spread with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: happiness
directions: Sprinkle generously with kindness.
Add plenty of faith and mix well.
Spread over a period of a lifetime and serve everyone you meet.
See them as friends and not as strangers.
Be sure to cook with a lot of forgiveness.

title: scotch shortbread(4 to 5 dozen)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour a little at a time.
Pat out on floured board to 1/2-inch thickness.
Then use rolling pin to make dough smooth.
With a knife, cut into strips both vertical and horizontal, making about 1-inch squares.
Press with fork on all 4 sides.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until just turning brown. (They will brown a little after removed from oven.)

title: peas and asparagus casserole
directions: Place
strained
peas and asparagus in layers in medium size casserole
dish.
Pour
mushroom soup over layers.	Thin soup with 1 cup of juice from asparagus.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake
for
35 to 40 minutes at 325°.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: cheese stuffed fillets
directions: Combine and blend well together the tomato with Mozzarella cheese, thyme and grated cheese.
Spread mixture on each fillet. Roll and fasten with toothpicks.

title: mandarins oki(this dessert may be lightly broiled and served hot, if preferred.)
directions: Arrange Mandarin segments in serving dish. Mix with flavorings and sprinkle with coconut.

title: french dressing
directions: Shake up first 4 ingredients together in an 8 ounce screw-top jar.
Put some of the oil and vinegar in the jar and shake it until mixed.
Put the rest of the oil and vinegar in and shake well.
Put in the minced garlic and sweet basil.
Shake some more.
Keep in fridge and shake before using.
Makes almost a cupful.
You can use olive oil, but it hardens in the fridge.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain and rinse.
Add all other ingredients and simmer about 30 minutes.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Boil carrots in salted water (no longer than bring to boil; you want carrots crisp).
Run cool water over until cooled.
Alternate layers of carrots, green pepper and onion in dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Blend well; pour over vegetables. Refrigerate.

title: pinto bean pie(this has the flavor of pecan pie)
directions: Heat beans and pour off excess liquid.
Mash with a fork and measure out 1/2 cup per pie.
Mix butter and sugar well.
Add vanilla, beans, eggs and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Let stand until cooled before cutting. (Double last five ingredients for two pies.)

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Stir the first 6 ingredients together.
Put in a casserole dish.
Crumble cheese tidbits on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: frozen orange pudding
directions: In a small bowl, combine eggs, water, nonfat dry milk and salt; beat with electric or rotary beater until light and fluffy. Gradually add sugar and concentrate, beating until thick and lemon colored.
Freeze.

title: low-fat spicy barbecued chicken breasts
directions: To prepare the grill for cooking, spray the unheated grill rack with nonstick spray, then light the grill according to the manufacturers directions.
Place the rack on the grill.

title: too-easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fruit in buttered 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cut crusts from bread slices and cut each slice into five fingers.
Place bread fingers over fruit.

title: party meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients except sauce. Shape mixture into balls. Place in shallow pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°. Drain off fat. Pour sauce over meatballs and bake 30 minutes more at 350°.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Combine cauliflower, broccoli, peas, cheese, water chestnuts and bacon bits in large bowl; set aside.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and dressing.
Pour over vegetables.
Chill.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cafe mocha mix
directions: Sift together 4 times.
Pack in tight container.
To serve, measure 1 heaping tablespoonful into coffee cup.
Fill with boiling water.
Yields 80 servings.
Fills 1 pound coffee can.

title: macaroni shell salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix together.
Serves 12.

title: fruit cake
directions: Line a 10-inch round pan with wax paper.
Grease pan.
Add cake mixture and bake about 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: hot ham and cheese spread
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cheddar cheese and ham until well blended. Pour into crock or ovenproof bowl. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until puffed and slightly browned. Serve warm as a spread with crackers. Makes 2 cups.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook the grits in the garlic flavored water until done.
Add oleo and the cheese.
Stir until melted, then set aside for 15 minutes.
Beat the eggs in a one-cup measure, then finish filling the cup with milk.
Pour into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple-ice cream dessert
directions: Make a graham cracker crust for oblong dish.
Drain pineapple. Use liquid along with hot water to make 3 cups.
Dissolve Jell-O in the liquid.
Add ice cream while it's hot.
Let thicken (stir occasionally).
Fold in pineapple.
Pour in crust.
Top with crumbs.

title: peanut butter dip
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Serve with fresh fruit or vegetables.
Especially good with fresh apple slices.

title: banana split cake
directions: Layer ingredients over crust and cream mixture.
Chill overnight.
Enjoy!!!

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Put all ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Mix on medium until thoroughly combined.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve with sliced apples.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Drain cooked broccoli and rice.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Combine ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to package directions using the 3 cups of sugar to sweeten.
Add other ingredients just before serving.

title: prune pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in unbaked pie shell. Cover with pie crust.
Cut slits on top.
Bake at 425° about 40 minutes.

title: mississippi pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in prepared pie shell for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: chop suey
directions: Dredge the cut up meats in the flour, salt and pepper.
Brown well in a small amount of oil in a heavy skillet.
When meat is browned, add the molasses.
Cover and cook until tender.
Add the vegetables and continue to simmer until all are done.
Stir quite often so it doesn't stick.
Serve over Chinese noodles or rice.

title: poor man's stroganoff
directions: Melt butter.
Add beef, onion, garlic and mushrooms.
Cook until meat is browned, stirring to break up.
Drain.
Add lemon juice, bouillon cubes and water.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes. Add noodles (uncooked).
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until tender.
Add more water, if necessary.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in sour cream and heat gently.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley. Serves 4.

title: nacho potato soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine potatoes, corn, tomatoes and water.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 to 18 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add milk, cheese and hot sauce, if desired.
Cook and stir until cheese is melted.
Serves 6 to 8 (2 quarts).

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and place in bottom of long casserole dish. Combine sugar, flour and grated cheese; spread over pineapple. Crush 1 stack of Ritz crackers and spread over casserole.
Pour 2 sticks melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: apple cream muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Combine flour, sugar, brown sugar, and cinnamon. Stir to mix. Combine eggs, vanilla, and whipping cream. Stir in apples. Spoon into well greased muffin tin, filling each cup 2/3 full. Bake for about 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of one of the muffins. Makes 10 large or 12 medium size muffins.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Bake in slow oven and keep stirred until brown and crunchy. May be eaten as a cold cereal with milk added.

title: mellow potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes until soft; peel and place them in a large bowl. Add all ingredients except eggs.
Whip with a whisk until smooth texture.
Beat eggs and add them to the mixture, whipping until smooth.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shells.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Place uncooked pies on lower rack.
Cook for 30 minutes. Eat!

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream together butter, brown sugar and eggs.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add Worcestershire sauce and sherry. Add mushrooms.
Saute about 5 minutes or until tender.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown the hamburger with onion.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt or powder to taste.
Add oregano, tomato paste, water and cottage cheese.
Boil noodles; drain.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer noodles, meat sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with confectioners sugar; then mix with whipped Dream Whip.
Put about 1/2 in bottom of cake pan. Cover well in broken pieces of cake.
Put rest of mixture on top and put can of cherries on top.
Chill for a couple of hours or overnight.

title: raisin-spice coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Combine 1/2 dry cake mix, butter, brown sugar and nuts.
Set aside for topping.

title: herb butter for salmon
directions: Cream butter in food processor.
Add remaining ingredients and process until combined.
Spread on salmon before barbecuing.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Note:
Maraschino cherries may be added for color.

title: cocoa
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa together.
Add water and stir to a smooth paste.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Scald milk in top of double boiler.
Add slowly to cocoa mixture and stir until well blended.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into a baking dish sprayed with Pam.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt	and
vanilla
together	by
hand until foamy.
Heat milk slowly until
scalding
and
add to egg mixture while beating.
Sprinkle
top with nutmeg (if desired). Put pan in hot water in middle of
oven
and bake at 350° for 1 hour.	Add cooked rice to make rice pudding or add cubes of old bread and raisins for bread pudding.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening & sugar. Add eggs. Dissolve soda in the bananas. Add flour, baking powder, salt, and nuts. Stir in bananas and mix well. Pour into greased pans. Makes 2 loaves. Fill 8 inch loaf pans half full and bake at 350° about an hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs and blend.
Mix dry ingredients well, then add nuts, pineapple and carrots and blend well.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: In bottom of large casserole dish (9 x 13-inch), put uncooked rice.
Sprinkle half of cheese over rice.
Mix onion soup, broth and chicken soup together.
Pour 1/2 soup mixture over rice and cheese.
Mix with fork.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Pour the rest of soup mixture over chicken and rice.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Take out (add more broth if it becomes dry).
Sprinkle the other half of cheese over the top.
Cover with foil and bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: avocado seafood salad
directions: In blender container, place Green Goddess dressing and parsley.
Cover; blend until smooth.
Pour into small bowl.
Fold in whipped cream.
Cover.
Chill.
Cut avocado lengthwise in half. Remove pit.
Scoop avocado into 3/4-inch balls.
Place in bowl. Add lemon juice to keep from discoloring.
Drain off liquid from seafood.
Add seafood and celery to bowl; toss
very gently.
Line 4 salad plates with lettuce leaves.
Spoon avocado mixture into each.
Top with some dressing.
Serve rest separately.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream the margarine until fluffy.
Add sugar.
Beat in eggs, cocoa, vanilla and flour.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Spread Marshmallow Creme on top.
Cool.

title: rice pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, mix thoroughly and put in 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole dish.
Put casserole dish in a pan with about 1 inch of hot water.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm or chilled. Instead of cooked rice, can use 1/2 cup uncooked rice, do not scald milk, stir after 30 minutes.
Add 10 minutes to baking time.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add sauce, onion and brown sugar. Set aside.
Separate dough into 12 biscuits.
Place 1 biscuit in ungreased muffin tin, pressing dough up the sides to the edge of the cup.
Spoon meat mixture into cups.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Good after school snack.

title: frosty chocolate shake
directions: In small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over 1/4 cup milk; let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatin is completely dissolved, about 5 minutes.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt shortening over low heat.
Remove from heat and blend in brown sugar; cool.
Stir in egg.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in well greased and floured square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inches).
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until toothpick is clean.
Cut into bars while warm.
Delish! (Says my girls.)

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in cheese, onions and jalapenos. Add eggs, oil, sour cream and corn; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: wonder cake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and heat until blended.
Do not set back on stove and heat.
Pour the mixture into a large bowl with the white sugar, flour and eggs.
Be sure and mix sugar and flour together before adding eggs.
Beat mixture and add buttermilk with soda, salt and vanilla.
Bake at 375° or lower for 25 to 30 minutes.
This can be baked in a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until done.
Mix with rice in large casserole, stirring in celery soup, margarine and Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chewy nut cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add one egg at a time. Add flour, one cup at a time.
Add nuts.
Pour in pan, 9 x 14-inch.
Bake at 350°. Test with thin sharp knife.

title: easy rice pudding
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Simmer about 45 minutes.
Add last 2 ingredients.

title: coconut bars
directions: Melt the butter in a 12 x 9-inch pan.
Do not burn. Add the cracker crumbs to butter.
Mix and pat in pan. Add the nuts, chocolate chips and coconut.
Place over the crust.
Pour the Eagle Brand over top of this mixture. Bake for 20 minutes in preheated 350° oven. Cool and cut into bars.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream butter and shortening until soft and light, then add 2 cups sugar and continue creaming until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and molasses.
Sift all dry ingredients and add to mix little by little (beating hard).
Batter will be quite soft.
Roll into balls and into remaining sugar.
Place on greased baking sheet. Cook 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Let stand a minute before removing from pan.

title: reception party mints
directions: Thoroughly mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar together. Add peppermint oil and mix again.
Place a portion in the desired number of containers.
Mold in mint molds of desired shapes. Unmold and store until ready to use.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate for a few hours.

title: pie dough
directions: Mix together until resembles corn meal.
Put in covered bowl and store in cupboard.
Will keep for months.
Use 1 1/2 cups per pie shell.
Add 5 tablespoons cold water.

title: caramel fried bananas
directions: Cut bananas in half lengthwise and crosswise.
Saute in margarine until lightly browned.
Add topping; heat, stirring occasionally.
Spoon banana mixture over cake slices or ice cream. Makes 8 servings.

title: shells florentine
directions: Saute mushrooms, onion, garlic, Italian seasonings and pepper in olive oil until tender.
Remove from heat and stir in cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, spinach and Egg Beaters.
Spoon into cooked shells.
Spread 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce in the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass casserole dish that has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Arrange shells in sauce and a layer of grated cheese.
Pour the rest of the sauce over shells and top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: taco dip
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler or nonstick pan with the juice from the Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Chop tomatoes very finely to add to cheese.
Let simmer 1/2 hour.
Cook hamburger until light brown; drain excess grease.
Add 3/4 cup water and 1/2 package taco seasoning.
Let simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add hamburger to cheese and let simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Can be used as a dip for Doritos or topping for taco or burritos.
Use your imagination.

title: fat soup(ten calories per cup)
directions: Cook until cabbage is done.

title: italian bean soup with pasta(for 6 servings)
directions: Place beans in bowl.
Add 2 cups of water and let stand overnight or bring to a boiling in medium saucepan.
Boil briskly 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand, covered, 1 hour.

title: cocoa drops
directions: Mix thoroughly the sugar, margarine and egg.
Stir in milk and vanilla. Stir in dry ingredients.
Place apart on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: zesty chicken-potato dish
directions: Melt bouillon cubes in water; set aside. Slice potatoes; cut each chicken breast half into 6 pieces. Place in large mixing bowl, sprinkle with garlic salt, minced onion, salt and pepper. Fold over with spoon until seasonings are well mixed with chicken and potatoes. Heat oil in large frying pan or cooking wok. Pour mixture in hot grease, stir constantly until chicken is slightly cooked. Stir in water mixture and hot sauce. Cover and cook on medium-low for 15 minutes or until chicken is done. Serve immediately. Should be slightly juicy but not soupy. If too dry add a small amount of water.

title: coconut delight
directions: Melt oleo and mix with flour and pecans.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool.

title: almeta's pralines
directions: Mix pudding, sugar and milk in large saucepan.
Cook on medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves, about 5 minutes.
Add nuts; boil 5 minutes more or until a soft ball stage when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat, add margarine and vanilla.
Stir until mixture starts to thicken (like fudge).
Drop in small patties on waxed paper.
Cool, but remove pralines while still warm to prevent sticking.

title: elaine's green chili hash
directions: Boil chicken in water with salt and flavor enhancer until chicken is tender.
Debone chicken, discarding skin.
Chop into bite size pieces.
Put chicken into pot with 1 1/2-quarts chicken broth.
Add onions, eggs, chilies, pimientos and black pepper. Cook 5 minutes.
Stir together cornstarch and 1/2 cup milk, then add the other 1/2 cup milk.
Add this to boiling chicken mixture, stirring constantly until thickened.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: monster dip
directions: *Can add 1 lb. cooked, crumbled hamburger meat, or sausage.

title: quick and easy roast
directions: Place roast in crock-pot.
Mix together wine and soup mix; pour over the top.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 7 hours or all day while you work!

title: caramel rhubarb and dumplings(microwave)
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in a 2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Cook uncovered at 100% power for 8 to 9 minutes, stirring every minute until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Cover and keep warm.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a custard cup, melt the margarine about 45 seconds.
Add to dry ingredients along with the milk.
Mix until just blended.
Drop the batter by spoonfuls into the hot rhubarb mixture.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes or until dumplings are done.
To test, scrape the wet surface with a toothpick.
The dough should have a bread-like texture underneath. Stir together 2 teaspoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon. Sprinkle over dumplings.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: almond tofu
directions: Whip together 1/4 cup soy sauce, peanut butter, garlic powder and onion powder.
Mix with the tofu cubes and marinate for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in skillet; add tofu and brown until liquid is absorbed.

title: deep dish peach cobbler
directions: Mix salt, sugar, flour and milk.
Spread mixture over the bottom of a buttered deep dish.
Add peaches.
Do not stir. Sprinkle nutmeg and cinnamon over the top.
Dot with butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: washington apple pudding
directions: Core and chop apples.
Pour butter or margarine over breadcrumbs.
In a well-buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish, layer 1/2 of the breadcrumbs, then 1/2 of the apples.
Sprinkle 1/2 the sugar and nutmeg and repeat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Beat eggs and milk until frothy.
You may need a little more milk. Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased casserole dish approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Freeze steak for 1 hour (it's easier to slice).
When ready to cook, cut into 1/8-inch thick slices.
Heat fat or oil in skillet. Add garlic, salt, ginger and pepper.
Saute until garlic is golden. Add steak slices.
Brown slightly, 2 minutes.
Remove meat.
Add green peppers and onions.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Add beef, soy sauce, sugar, bouillon, water chestnuts, cornstarch dissolved in water, and green onions.
Simmer about 2 minutes or until sauce thickens.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 6 to 8 serving.

title: pia colada cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to box directions. Pour in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Remove from oven steaming hot and make holes in top with a fork. Mix milk and cream of coconut and dribble over hot cake. Top with grated coconut. Cool in refrigerator.

title: pork shish-ka-bobs
directions: Combine and mix well the following:
soy sauce, sugar, garlic, lemon juice, red wine vinegar and black pepper.
Add cubed meat and toss well.
Let marinate at least 8 hours in refrigerator, stirring (or shaking depending on container) 3 or 4 times so all meat gets marinated.
Use wooden or metal skewers.
Can alternate meat with fresh vegetables:
onions, red/green/yellow peppers, squash, etc.
Grill over hot coals until meat is tested done.
We have brought these to the family reunion and they went like hotcakes!

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli according to the package directions.
Drain and place in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Break up cooked chicken into bite size pieces and layer on top of broccoli.
In a saucepan, heat soup, mushrooms and reserved liquid over medium heat.
Blend in mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Continue cooking and stirring until heated through.
Pour soup mixture over chicken and broccoli and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Cover with stuffing mix.
Bake for 30 minutes or until top is brown.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving. Serves 6 to 8.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine ice water and vegetables.
Let stand for 2 hours, then drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar, boiling water and seasonings and bring to a boil.
Add vegetables and simmer until tender, about 10 minutes.
Put into jars, cover with syrup mixture and seal according to canning directions.

title: easy going meal
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Heat oil in a large, nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken, green pepper and seasonings.
Saute until chicken is lightly browned.
Stir in rice until coated with seasonings.
Stir in water and tomato sauce; bring to a boil, then cover skillet and reduce heat to low. Simmer until water is absorbed and rice is cooked.
Remove from heat and add parsley. Cover and let stand for 5 minutes.
This recipe is quite low in fat content.

title: pineapple icing
directions: Mix sugar and pineapple.
Add flour or starch.
Place on stove and cook 5 to 8 minutes (pineapple cooks quickly).
Add flavoring. Cool icing before spreading on cake layers.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 1 gallon punch.

title: cherry crowns
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese until soft and creamy; gradually add sugar.
Add egg yolk with extract; mix well.
Stir in flour. Cover and chill about 1 hour.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; dip tops in beaten egg white, then almonds.
Place on lightly greased pan; press a cherry half in top and bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: frozen chocolate mousse cake
directions: Crush Oreos.
Line bottom and sides of spring-form pan with Oreos.
Combine over hot (not boiling) water chocolate morsels and water.
Stir until melted and smooth.
Transfer to large bowl.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Set aside.

title: green grape delight
directions: Combine first five ingredients and mix until smooth.
Gently fold in grapes and nuts.
Chill thoroughly, about two hours. Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 4 - 6.

title: praline sauce
directions: Melt butter, add sugar, corn syrup, and flour.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat.
Simmer, stirring constantly for 5 minutes. Cool to luke warm, add milk and pecans.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli, then lay in casserole dish.
Melt together the two cheeses and the soup and pour over broccoli. Sprinkle on top the seasoned stuffing mix and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly and brown on top.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix cooked chicken with the cheeses and onion.
Add the chili powder and set aside.
Cover bottom of a hot frying pan with cooking oil.
Allow oil to heat up and fry each tortilla.
Pour enchilada sauce in a pie plate.
Dip the softened tortilla in the sauce and put about 2 tablespoons of the chicken mixture in tortilla.
Wrap up and place seam side down in baking dish.
Top with remaining sauce and cheeses.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: chicken oriental
directions: Slice radishes, water chestnuts and Fri chik.
Dice remaining vegetables.
In skillet, combine soup, pineapple and soy sauce. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes; stir gently now and then.
Serve with cooked rice and additional soy sauce.
Makes about 5 1/2 cups.

title: wilted spinach salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; reserve drippings.
Wash spinach and remove large stems.
Tear into bite-size pieces in salad bowl. Crumble bacon and add along with mushrooms, eggs and green onions. To 1/4 cup bacon drippings, add vinegar, brown sugar, mustard, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat and pour over spinach.
Toss lightly.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple and strawberries.
Let cool, then add mashed or cubed bananas.
Pour half the mixture into an 8 x 10-inch Pyrex dish. Chill until firm. Spread with sour cream. Pour remaining mixture over sour cream and chill.

title: egg casserole
directions: Beat all ingredients together, except sausage or ham.
Put greased 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Cover overnight in refrigerator. Sprinkle browned sausage or cubed ham on in morning.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes and combine with butter.
Add other ingredients and stir well.
Spread on topping mixture of 2 cups crushed cornflakes and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: roast chicken(crock-pot)
directions: Wash chicken and place in crock-pot on high for 1 hour and then on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: sugar and honey pecans
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan; mix well.
Cook mixture over medium heat stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
Continue cooking, without stirring, until mixture reaches soft ball stage (240°).
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat with a wooden spoon until mixture begins to thicken.
Stir in pecan halves, working rapidly, pour mixture onto waxed paper and separate pecans with a fork.
Let cool.
Yields 4 cups.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in sugar.
Cool.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat thoroughly (hand beat).
Stir in flour.
Add vanilla and stir in chips and nuts.
Pour in greased oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ham 'n tater casserole
directions: Place ham in baking dish.
Boil potatoes and onion in water until just barely done, but still firm.
Drain well and place in dish with ham.
Lightly salt and pepper.

title: holiday cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In separate bowl, combine juice, rind, Crisco and enough boiling water to total 3/4 cup.
Add well beaten egg.
Blend liquid into dry ingredients, stir only until flour is dampened. Add nuts and cranberries.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
For well rounded loaf, push batter up into corners, leaving center slightly hollowed.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: italian style zucchini
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in butter.
Add mushrooms.
Cook until soft.
Cook sausage, drain and set aside.
When zucchini mixture is ready, add tomato sauce, sausage and salt and pepper.
Simmer all together, the longer the better.
When ready to serve, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Slash the roast and insert slivers of garlic in slits.
Rub well with salt and pepper; place in glass or earthenware bowl. Cover roast with 1 sliced onion.
Heat water, vinegar, lemon slices and pickling spices together.
Pour hot marinade over roast.
Cover tightly and refrigerate for 2 or 3 days before cooking.
Turn occasionally so meat will be evenly marinated throughout.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring after 30 minutes.

title: grandma ransbottom's soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix Crisco.
Add white sugar; continue beating.
Add brown sugar, salt and vanilla.
Continue beating.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder and buttermilk.
Add to egg mixture.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients together until smooth.
Line muffin tins with muffin papers (cupcake).
Place 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of each.
Then divide mixture between the 24 muffin cups. Bake 15 minutes at 325°.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown meat; drain, rinse and drain.
Place in crock-pot with cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes and chilies.
Stir and cook until cheese has melted.
Stir well.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pineapple and cheese bake(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain pineapple, reserving 4 tablespoons juice.
In medium bowl, combine flour and sugar. Slowly stir in reserved juice.
Add pineapple chunks and cheese. Mix well and pour into lightly greased 1-quart casserole.
Mix butter and cracker crumbs in small bowl.
Sprinkle over pineapple mixture.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes until bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tomato soup
directions: Melt butter in a skillet with chicken bouillon, stirring to combine.
Add celery and onion and saute until tender.
Stir in the flour to make a roux.
Lower heat and cook for 10 minutes. Add chopped tomatoes, plus juice from their cans, along with tomato juice.
Stir until well mixed, then stir in evaporated milk.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: easy sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Place partially thawed vegetables in slow cooker.
Arrange pork chops on top.
Combine sauce mix and water.
Pour over chops and vegetables in slow cooker.
Cover and cook on low 7 to 8 hours.
Turn on high; add pea pods.
Cover and cook on high about 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: baked haddock
directions: Drizzle with melted margarine on both sides. Sprinkle Italian bread crumbs on both sides.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with fresh lemon.

title: easy german chocolate cake
directions: Put coconut and pecans in bottom of sheet cake pan.
Prepare cake mix according to directions on box and pour over coconut and pecans.
Cream butter, cream cheese and confectioners sugar together and drop by teaspoonfuls onto batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mom's pistachio nut cake
directions: Combine dry cake mix, soda, dry pudding mix, eggs and oil. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into 10-inch tube/Bundt pan that is greased and floured.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Let cake cool in pan; then turn cake onto serving dish and frost.
Can serve plain.

title: yule log roll
directions: Mix vanilla wafer crumbs, pineapple, cherries, pecans, condensed milk, coconut and bourbon (if used).

title: beef patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large dish.
Make large patties.
Cook in broiler.
Don't place too close to fire.
Cook until done.
Also may cook in barbecue outside.
Serve with salad.

title: italian dish meal
directions: Do entire large pan of ingredients in layers.
First, make a thin layer of potatoes.
Second, put meat in a layer on top of potatoes, then sprinkle some basil, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper.
Then, do next layer of potatoes, meat and seasonings. Continue layers until all is used.
Add water and oil to sides of pan, not on top of ingredients, then crush with hand both cans of tomatoes on top of ingredients.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: applesauce slush
directions: Heat first 2 ingredients until they boil.
Remove from heat. Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add cold water and stir. Put in pan and refrigerate.

title: georgia's southwest spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a shallow baking dish. Cook 25 to 30 minutes at 350°, until golden brown on top.
Serve with a loaf of sliced baguette bread (toasted or plain).

title: golden cheese bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in sugar, liquid nonfat milk, butter and salt.
Stir in 3 1/4 cups flour.
Knead on floured board until smooth and elastic.
Work in additional flour, about 8 minutes.
Place in buttered bowl; brush with butter.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled.
Punch down.

title: delicious deviled eggs
directions: Hard-boil eggs.
Peel eggs; slice in half lengthways.
Scoop out yellow yolks with spoon and put in mixing bowl.
Put white egg half in fancy deviled egg dish.

Add mustard and mayonnaise (to personal taste), approximately 1 large tablespoon of mustard (the spicier the mustard, the spicier the egg) and 1 large tablespoon of mayonnaise, into mixing bowl with egg yolks.
Mix yolks, mayonnaise and mustard together.
Fill white egg centers with yellow yolk mixture.
Garnish each egg with a dash of paprika.

title: cranberry spike
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend.
Makes 1 quart.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets about 1 hour or until soft when pricked with a fork.
Peel and place in a large bowl of mixer or large bowl.
Mix with sugar, eggs, oleo, milk, salt, vanilla and cinnamon. Beat until smooth. Strings will cling to beaters.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and add topping.

title: one loaf bread(may be doubled.)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add shortening, salt, sugar and 1/2 the flour. Beat until smooth. Add remaining flour and knead (you can do this in the bowl). Let rise in warm place until double (about an hour). Knead and let rest for 10 minutes. Put in bread pan and let rise again. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then lower heat to 325° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground round and ground sausage in large saucepan. Drain well. Return to medium heat and add seasonings, blending well into meats. Add tomato paste and water and stir well until sauce has thoroughly coated meat mixture. Add tomato sauce and blend well. Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, until thickened.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Drain the first 6 ingredients and reserve 1 cup of juice. Melt butter and add brown sugar, flour and the cup of juice.
Cook until smooth.
Place fruit in baking dish and pour liquid over fruit.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: ole settlers beans
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces.
Brown hamburger, bacon and onions.
Bacon will be soft.
Do not drain.
Add the rest of the ingredients in large pan or crock-pot.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or crock-pot on low overnight or 4 to 5 hours.
For best results, use crock-pot.

title: crab strudel
directions: In pan, saute onion and garlic with butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper; cook until blended.
Gradually add milk; stir constantly until thick and smooth.
Stir in sherry and crabmeat.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Dip chicken in eggs and roll in crumbs.
Saute in butter.
In crock-pot, arrange eggplant, then chicken.
Pour on sauce.
Cook 6 to 8 hours on low.
Add cheeses and cook 15 minutes more.

title: potage st. germain soup
directions: Simmer everything except half and half for 20 minutes.
Then place in blender and puree.
Add half and half; heat, but do not boil.
Serve with sour cream and croutons on top.

title: salmon dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator to blend the flavors.
Serve with snack crackers and chips.

title: b.b.q. ribs
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Press garlic over meaty sides of ribs.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Pour tomato juice over ribs; cover and bake for 1 hour.
Remove from tomato juice and discard juice.
Blend together ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar, worcestershire and chili powder.
Bring to boil over medium head; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Place precooked ribs on heated grill, meaty side up.
Brush with BBQ sauce mixture made from ketchup mixture.
Cover and grill 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: peanut brittle(50 years or older)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and cook until honey-colored.
Remove from heat and stir in soda.
Pour on well-buttered pan.

title: party salad
directions: Dissolve jello and hot water and cool to congeal.
Mix together cottage cheese, nuts, cherries, pineapple and cream. Sometimes I add 2 drops red food coloring to a dainty pink color. Pour into mold.

title: quick & easy casseroleeverton, missouri
directions: Layer potatoes, onion, green pepper and hamburger with cheese between each layer.
Top with cream of mushroom soup.
Cover with tin foil.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: bill's spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef, seasoned with salt and pepper.
Drain off grease.
Add soup and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted and stirred in good.

title: french fried okra
directions: Mash cooked potatoes with milk and butter.
Add 1 can Durkee French fried onion rings.
Mix together.
Put in dish.
Place grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix all ingredients with hamburger meat and simmer.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Chill several hours until firm.

title: potato rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
In a large mixing bowl, combine yeast packet (from hot roll mix) with water.
Add potato flakes, egg and soft butter.
Gradually stir in flour mixture; blend well. Cover.
Let rise in a warm place until light and doubled in size (about 45 minutes).
Grease muffin cups.
Shape dough into small balls; place in muffin cups.
Let rise about 45 minutes or until light and doubled in size.
Bake at 375 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush with melted butter if desired.
Yield:
18 rolls.

title: applesauce oatmeal muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 12 medium muffin cups with paper baking cups.
Combine oats, flour, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda.
Add applesauce, milk, brown sugar, oil and egg white.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill muffin cups almost full.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle evenly over batter.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes or until deep golden brown.

title: hershey's vanilla chip fruit tart
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Beat butter and confectioners sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour.
Press mixture onto bottom and up sides of a 12-inch round pizza pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely.

title: sweet potato muffins(from christina campbell's tavern in williamsburg)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease or use paper liners in small 1 1/2-inch muffin pans.

title: mexican food beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Add roast and remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 6 hours or until done. Remove roast and strip the fat off, then cut into bite size pieces. Put back into beans and simmer until thick.
Serve buffet style with bowl of the following: Fritos, shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes, chopped green onions, chopped avocado, picante sauce, sour cream, black olives and chopped jalapenos.
Stack as desired, starting with Fritos and beans.

title: nicki's icing
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and beat with a mixer 5 to 7 minutes.

title: potato buns
directions: Soften yeast in water for 10 minutes, then add 4 cups flour. Let set 1 hour.
Add 6 cups flour, potatoes, sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Mix well and let rise for 2 hours; punch down.
Drop by teaspoon or make a small ball.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate-pecan celebration pie
directions: Mix together sugars, flour, eggs, butter and vanilla.
Add chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans.
Mix well.
Shape into a ball.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll in pecans.

title: chocolate-coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa together.
Add eggs and mix well. Stir in vanilla, milk, margarine, coconut and nuts.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until firm.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain and rinse with cold water until noodles cool.
Add remaining ingredients to noodles.
Mix and chill for at least 1 hour.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Boil macaroni.
Mix eggs, milk, butter and most of the cheese and macaroni.
Place in a pan and sprinkle some of the Cheddar cheese over the top, then sprinkle a little paprika on top for color.
Bake for 20 minutes or until the cheese is melted.

title: mexican salad
directions: Empty into a bowl the lemon
jello and add the very hot water. Stir in the sugar,
salt,
vinegar
and
chili powder. Cool. Meanwhile, prepare the
vegetables.
When
the
gelatin mixture is slightly thickened,
add
the vegetables and fruit. Blend thoroughly.
Refrigerate for 3
to
4 hours.
To unmold, hold in hot water for a few
seconds and turn on a chef plate. Arrange salad greens around mold.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and bone fryer.
In bottom of 1-quart casserole baking dish, add mixture of melted margarine and, 1 1/2 cups stuffing mix and some of the chicken broth.
Mix together cream of chicken soup, cream of celery soup and 1 cup of stuffing.
Add boned chicken and place in baking dish.
Put about 1 cup of stuffing on top.
Bake 20 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: firesparrows
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
With a spoon, drop in heated oil (lard) and fry (deep fry).
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: coor's beer bread
directions: Melt butter and pour enough into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan to coat bottom.
In large bowl, mix flour, sugar and beer.
Spoon dough into loaf pan.
Pour remaining butter over the top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until bread is a light golden color (50 to 60 minutes).
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting with a serrated knife.

title: grandma's icebox cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Roll in wax paper into 1 1/2-inch log.
Place in freezer until ready to bake.

title: ritz-cracker cookies
directions: Mix pecans, sugar and just enough milk to make it stick together.
Put a teaspoonful on each cracker.
Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet about 10 minutes or until a light brown.

title: round about salad
directions: Blend together Jell-O and cottage cheese, then add remaining ingredients.

title: dump cake
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle dry cake mix over the top.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: easy eggplant parmigiana
directions: Wash, peel and slice eggplants into 1/4-inch slices.
Mix egg and milk and set aside.
Mix all other ingredients.
Dip slices of eggplant into egg mixture, then into crumb mixture.
Lay flat on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Turn once. Spoon a little sauce on the bottom of a large casserole dish. Layer slices of eggplant, sauce and grated Mozzarella.
On top layer, sprinkle more sauce, Mozzarella and grated Romano cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 or 40 minutes until bubbly.

title: icing for pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and pour over cake.

title: layer dinner(from the "guild cookbook," 1941)
directions: Salt and pepper each layer.
Cut green pepper up fine and sprinkle on top.

title: zesty shrimp appetizer
directions: Boil shrimp in plain water until tender, 3 to 5 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Cool and peel.
Combine salad dressing, parsley and vinegar.
Pour over shrimp; cover and refrigerate 6 to 12 hours. Drain and serve with toothpicks.
Makes 10 to 12 appetizers.

title: angel biscuits #2
directions: Mix yeast with water and stir to dissolve.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in refrigerator in covered dish until needed.
Bake in moderate oven until golden brown.
Good.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Beat the vegetable oil, water and pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients.
Add nuts and mix well. Bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oklahoma caviar
directions: Adjust all ingredients to suit taste.
Mix all ingredients and marinate at least 3 days or more to fully develop flavor.
When ready to serve, drain and serve with big corn chips.
Makes 2 quarts.
This is good cold.

title: four bean salad
directions: Drain all the beans.
Prepare Spicy Herb Dressing.
Place remaining ingredients except lettuce in a large bowl. Toss with dressing.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Drain salad, reserving dressing.
Serve in lettuce lined bowl.

title: old stone inn in kentucky stuffed eggplant
directions: Slice the chicken in thin strips.
Combine with the fettucine. Reserve 1/3 of the marinade for later use and pour the rest over the chicken and fettucine.
Toss and chill overnight for the flavors to blend.

title: homemade mincemeat
directions: Put all ingredients except brandy in a large saucepan.
Cook slowly 1 1/2 hours, stirring frequently.
Stir in brandy and pack into 4 hot, sterile quart jars.
Seal.
A quart makes 1 1/2 nine-inch pies.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix margarine, dry onion and milk.
Add melted Velveeta cheese.
Stir.
Sprinkle on garlic salt and hot pepper.
Serve hot as a cheese dip or cold as a spread.

title: iced cucumber limeade
directions: Mix lime juice and honey together and pour equal quantities into 2 glasses.
Peel cucumber and remove seeds.
Chop and put into a blender until smooth.
Add ice cubes and blend until mushy. Pour equal quantities into the two glasses and mix.

title: tator tot casserole
directions: Crumble and cook ground beef; drain.
Lay flat in a baking dish.
Then cover meat with slices of cheese; then pour soup on top of cheese.
Then lay Tater Tots on top and bake at 375° to 425°, depending on your oven for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into 3 round greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: skillet broccoli chicken(ready in less than 30 minutes.)
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Remove; set aside.
Pour off fat.

title: peachy spring breeze pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and pour into a graham cracker crust.
Boil 1 cup water, 1 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons cornstarch and Karo syrup until thick and clear, stirring constantly.
Add box of jello.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Add peaches and pour on top of filled pie.

title: orange sauce for angel food cake
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick and then cool.
Mix in 1 cup of whipping cream or Cool Whip.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender and tear into bite size pieces. Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine all ingredients together and stir until mixed.
Pour into 2-quart greased casserole pan.
Top with more shredded cheese.
Cover and cook at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: lo-cal cranberry punch
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Garnish with orange slices and strawberries.
Serve over ice.
Contains 11 calories per 8 ounce glass.

title: cream cheese ring with strawberries
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve over hot water. Combine
softened
cheese,	sugar,	almond	extract
and salt, blending until smooth.
Gradually add milk and gelatin.
Chill mixture until partly set.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into a 1 quart
ring
mold; chill until firm.
Unmold and fill center of ring
with	fresh
strawberries, slightly sweetened if desired.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites and set aside.
Sift flour and sugar.
Add oil, pineapple and egg yolks; mix.
Add cinnamon, hot water and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake 70 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: beverly's meat loaf(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except catsup, in large mixing bowl. Pat mixture evenly into 1 1/2-quart utility dish, or micro loaf pan.
Cook on Full power for six minutes.
Turn dish halfway through cooking time unless you have a turntable.
Drizzle catsup over top of loaf, cook on Full power for five minutes more.
If more than 1 pound of meat is used, cook for 2 to 4 minutes more. Let stand 3 to 5 minutes, easier to cut and remove.

title: almond hershey pie
directions: Cut up almonds in bars.
Melt the bars in a double boiler with the marshmallows and milk.
Cool in refrigerator.
Fold in chopped almonds and whipped cream.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Grease a 9 or 10-inch pie plate and put in the cranberries, 1/2 cup sugar and the nuts.
Mix the eggs, flour, cup of sugar and oil all together and then pour over the cranberry mixture that is in the pie tins.
Bake at 320° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: creeping crust cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 10-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and baking powder; add milk and mix.
Spoon over melted butter.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine the night before served.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil in a large mixing bowl with electric mixer.
Mix well.
Gradually beat in flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in carrots, nuts, pineapple and vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
May frost with your favorite frosting.

title: herb bread
directions: Mix last 6 ingredients.
Butter slices (both sides) with mix. Put together and wrap in foil.
Heat at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil and simmer 30 minutes. Strain to desired consistency and pack in hot jars; process 30 to 40 minutes in a hot water bath.

title: coconut dream pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping with 1 cup of milk; add 1 3/4 cups milk and pie filling.
Blend, then beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill 4 hours.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Mix sugar eggs, oleo and milk together.
Add 5 slices of bread (cubed) and pineapple tidbits.
Bake 1 hour at 350.
Serve warm.
Good with ham or pork.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel eggs, cut in half and remove yolks.
Mash yolks with a fork; add rest of ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Fill the cut egg halves with the mixture.

title: jobneh (syrian cheese)
directions: Heat the milk just enough to get the chill out.
Melt 2 Junket tablets in 2 or 3 tablespoons warm water.
Stir in milk for about 2 minutes.
Cover with lid and a large towel or warm cloth for 2 hours.
Pour into a cheesecloth and let all the water drain.
When cheese settles in bottom of bag, shape smoothly with your hands (cupping the hands) making sure all the water drains out. Sprinkle with salt.

title: chocolate deluxe icing
directions: Mix, then beat with rotary beater until fluffy.
Enough for 2 layers.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: In a small shallow bowl, combine flour, salt and pepper. Dredge pork chops in mixture.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Cook pork chops 10 minutes on each side. Place in a single layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine soup, broth, ginger, rosemary and 1/2 cup sour cream.
Pour over chops.
Sprinkle with half of the onion rings.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Stir remaining sour cream into sauce.
Top chops with remaining onions.
Return to oven, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
Good!

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place asparagus, cheese and crackers in casserole dish.
Pour milk and eggs over ingredients.
Salt, pepper and melted butter added to top.
Bake in moderate oven 45 to 50 minutes.

title: just delicious cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Shape in balls on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork or glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes a lot.

title: polenta, bean and pasta casserole
directions: In saucepan, stir together cornmeal and cold water.
Slowly whisk in boiling water.
Bring to boil and stir over medium heat for 10 minutes or until thick. Stir in corn and wheat germ.
Spread mixture in greased 10 x 10-inch or 9 x 13-inch casserole evenly over the bottom.
Refrigerate.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in jar with tight lid.
Place one heaping teaspoon or to taste.
Add hot water.
Stir well. Relax and enjoy.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Drain fruit and add juice to jello (no more than 2 cups).
Let partially set, then add fruit. Return to refrigerator to completely jell.

title: skillet enchiladas
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onions; drain off fat. (If you use electric skillet, cook at 350°.) Stir in soup, enchilada sauce, milk and chilies. Reduce to 220°. Cover and cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. In a small skillet, dip the tortillas in a little hot oil until limp; drain. Reserve 1/2 cup cheese. Place on each tortilla; sprinkle with olives. Roll up each tortilla. Place in sauce and cover until heated through, about 5 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and cook until cheese is melted.

title: honey dijon salad dressing
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a blender.
Pour into a cruet; mix in onion.

title: poppin-fresh barbecups
directions: In large skillet, brown beef; drain, add barbecue sauce, brown sugar and onions.
Separate biscuits.
Place each biscuit in an ungreased muffin cup, pressing dough up sides to edge of cup. Spoon meat into cups . Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes until brown.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix ingredients by hand and form balls.
Chill.
With toothpicks, dip balls in mixture made with 6 ounces semi-sweet chocolate and 1/4 square of household paraffin wax melted in double boiler.
After dipping balls, place on wax paper to dry. If finger print shows, not enough wax.

title: cin toast
directions: Put bread on cookie sheet.
Put butter on the bread.
Put cinnamon sugar on the bread.
Broil for 1 minute.
Serve.

title: stir-fry sauce
directions: Blend together and add to wok.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook ground beef and Italian sausage along with the onion until browned, then drain off fat.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Begin making the sauce the night before and then refrigerate or make early in the day before serving it.
Simmer on low, adding water or more tomato sauce as needed, so that it does not burn.
Serve over pasta.
Serves 6.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine cream cheese and margarine.
Add milk and vanilla. Gradually add sugar until frosting reaches spreading consistency.

title: easy chicken and rice dinner
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add chicken and cook until browned. Remove chicken.
Add soup, water, paprika and pepper.
Heat to a boil.
Stir in rice and broccoli.
Top with chicken.
Season chicken with additional paprika and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until done.
Serves 4.

title: salt substitute seasoning
directions: Blend in a food processor or blender until fine enough to go through salt shaker.

title: green beans and cheese
directions: Cook beans as directed.
Put all together in casserole. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Wind 1 strip of bacon around each chicken breast.
Line shallow baking dish with beef.
Arrange chicken breasts on this. Cover all with mushroom soup and sour cream.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: french fried potato puffs
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Sift together remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Heat fat, 2 inches deep, in deep fat fryer or deep pan to 375° on fat thermometer.
Drop potato mixture by spoonfuls into fat.
Fry 3 to 5 minutes or until brown.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar, then pumpkin and lemon juice.
Sift together the next 5 ingredients and mix in.
Spread mixture onto a well-greased and floured cookie sheet.
(Optional:
Sprinkle with 1 cup chopped nuts.)
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool slightly and place on small towel which has been sprinkled evenly with powdered sugar. Roll and cool.
Unroll and spread with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Roll and chill completely.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain whole artichokes and chop in food processor.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl and add chopped artichokes. Moisten mixture with mayonnaise.
Bake in an oven-safe dish for approximately 20 minutes at 350° until bubbling.
Serve with crackers.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and stir to blend.
Refrigerate until needed for serving.

title: collard greens
directions: Place turkey in Dutch oven with garlic.
Add water.
Cover. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, break off and throw away stems of collards.
Wash leaves thoroughly.
Slice into small pieces.
Add collards, onion, celery, green peppers, sugar, oil, salt and pepper.
Cook 30 to 60 minutes.
Simmer until done.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Chop tomatoes, onion, red pepper and green pepper; combine. Add salt and sugar.
Cook until mixture begins to thicken and add mustard seed, cinnamon, allspice and vinegar.
Continue cooking until mixture becomes like a thick sauce.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: fresh fruit pie
directions: Blend cornstarch with 3 tablespoons pineapple juice drained from canned pineapple.
Add remaining juice and pineapple; heat until thickened.
Layer banana slices, peach slices, blueberries and strawberries, leaving some strawberries and blueberries for garnish.
Pour thickened pineapple over fruit; garnish with reserved fruit and, if used, nuts.
Serve cold.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fluffy cocoa frosting
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar together.
Cream part of the cocoa and sugar mixture with butter.
Blend in vanilla and half the milk. Add remaining cocoa-sugar mixture and blend well.
Add remaining milk and beat to desired spreading consistency.
Additional milk may be added.

title: pumpkin walnut cookies
directions: Combine sugar and butter.
Beat eggs, vanilla, pumpkin, grated lemon peel and lemon juice.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add walnuts.
Beat all together.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: quick and easy french toast
directions: Dip bread in mixture.
Brown on both sides in hot buttered skillet.

title: blueberry yum yum pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Beat Dream Whip and milk until fluffy.
Mix together until fluffy.
Divide into pie shells.
Divide can of blueberry pie filling over both pies. Leave in refrigerator overnight.

title: watergate cake
directions: Beat all the ingredients together, except nuts, for 4 minutes. Add 1 cup nuts.
Grease and flour Bundt or tube pan.
Bake for 55 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine cornstarch and sugar.
Beat eggs and add cornstarch, sugar, salt, oleo and milk.
Stir corn into mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: river chili
directions: Combine the beef, onion and garlic in a skillet and sear until the meat is lightly browned.
Transfer this mixture to a large pot; add the remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat and simmer for one hour.
When done, transfer the chili to a bowl and place it in the refrigerator.
When the fat has congealed on top, remove with spoon.
