Reheat the chili and serve.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and cook and stir to a rolling boil; lower heat.
Keep stirring while mixture boils slowly (3 minutes).
Take off heat.
Stir in peanuts.
Heat until candy starts to thicken.
Drop from teaspoon on wax paper.

title: chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Grease a shallow (2-quart) baking dish. Place chicken and vegetables into baking dish. Stir together chicken broth, soup, pepper and salt. Pour over chicken mixture. Combine flour, milk and margarine. Stir until smooth. Pour over mixture in baking dish. Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until lightly browned. Let cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: low country frogmore stew
directions: Fill a large Dutch oven halfway with water.
Add 1/4 cup Old Bay seasoning.
Bring to a boil
Add potatoes; return to a boil and cook 10 minutes.
Add sausage and corn; resume boil and cook 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add shrimp; cook 3 to 5 minutes or until they turn pink.
Remove with slotted spoon. Serve with more Old Bay and cocktail sauce.
Yields 12 servings.

title: honeyed apple rings
directions: Arrange apple slices in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine honey, vinegar, salt and cinnamon in a small bowl. Drizzle over apples. Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes or until tender.
Yields 8 servings.

title: mixed fruit cream cheese pie
directions: Cream cheese and 1st preserves with electric mixer on medium speed until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip with electric mixer on low speed.
Spread this mixture evenly over graham cracker crust. Arrange fruit attractively on this layer.
Heat currant jelly until melted; stir in almond flavoring.
Brush this mixture evenly over the fruit.
Serve immediately or chill for 30 minutes.

title: chicken velvet soup
directions: In saucepan blend butter and flour; cook over medium heat for 2 minutes.
Heat milk, cream and stock; add a little at a time to butter/flour mixture, stirring until mixture is smooth and thickened.
When it begins to boil, add chicken and seasonings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Layer with remaining ingredients in the order listed in a casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: christmas slush
directions: Boil water and sugar for three minutes. Add rest of ingredients and freeze. When ready to serve, partially fill a glass with slush and add 7up or ginger ale.

title: deviled chicken
directions: Brown chicken in hot shortening.
Remove and add flour to pan, then water for gravy.
Simmer for 1 hour, but turn after 30 minutes.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Put in jar while hot and seal.

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix all together.
Bake on flat cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until tender with butter added to water.
Mix remaining ingredients with 1 cup chicken stock to form a soft dough.
Roll dough as for pie crust; cut in short 3-inch strips. Drop into boiling chicken stock.
When the last dumpling is dropped, cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Immediately lightly stir minced warm chicken into dumplings and serve.
Yields 8 servings.

title: mint drops
directions: Beat egg whites, extract, cream of tartar and salt until forms soft peaks; add sugar gradually until you get stiff peaks.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Add a few drops of red food coloring.
Cover baking sheet with plain brown paper, no butter.
Drop mints by very small teaspoons.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat eggs until light. Gradually add sugar while beating.
Add oil and zucchini.
Add cinnamon and vanilla; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake approximately 40 minutes (4 to 5 small loaves).
Two regular loaves take longer.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together and cook for approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Beat 3/4 cup sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir together 2 cups flour, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to mixture; beat until smooth.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Top mixture with berries.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup flour and 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Cut butter in until crumbly.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: oreo cake
directions: Mash together cookies and butter with a fork, potato masher, etc.
Pat into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Bring cheese spread and cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix until completely smooth and combined.
Shape into a ball, 4 to 5 inches in diameter.
Roll in ground pecans.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Serve in center of tray with assorted crackers.

title: red kidney bean appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill well.
Serve with crackers.

title: antelope delight
directions: Mix ready made meat marinade with vinegar, water and salad oil.
Pour this over antelope round steak and let marinate for 4 to 5 hours.
Lift meat from marinade and roll in flour.
Brown slightly in frying pan in cooking oil.
Mix rest of marinade with 1 cup of water and pour over meat.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
The larger amount of meat you use, the more marinade you will need.

title: brown sugar and orange glaze
directions: Cook ham according to directions, adding 1 cup of pineapple juice to pan while ham bakes.

Mix together brown sugar, dry mustard and enough orange juice to moisten. This recipe can be doubled or you can prepare it by adding half orange juice and half of the pineapple juice from the baking pan.

title: escalloped tomatoes
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add biscuits and sugar.
Cook slowly. Stir in tomatoes and seasoning. Place mixture in buttered, shallow pan and bake 45 minutes in medium oven.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Boil young carrots until skin slips; remove skin.
Slice or leave whole.
Pour syrup, spices (in a bag), sugar and boiling hot over carrots.
Let stand overnight.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Remove spices and pack in jars.
Pour syrup over carrots and seal.

title: pizza hamburger
directions: Mix altogether; put to edge of bread.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; top with cheese slices and bake for another 5 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: glazed meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs, bread, milk, salt and pepper in a large bowl and mix well.
Add beef, cheese, carrot and onion; mix well.
Shape into a loaf and place on a lightly greased rack on a broiler pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients and spoon over loaf.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or more, until done.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Soften cream cheese.
When softened, mix cream cheese, milk, sugar, Cool Whip and vanilla.
Slice off or tear off small pieces of cake.
In a large crystal bowl (such as a punch bowl), first layer cheese mixture, then cake, then cherries.
Continue layers in sequence, ending with cheese and cherries on top.
Chill overnight.

title: conestoga yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add butter, sugar and eggs; mix well.
Stir in flour until blended well; dough will be soft. Spoon into greased muffin tins and bake at 400° for 15 to 17 minutes.
Store remaining dough in refrigerator and use when needed.

title: mulberry garden casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
well.
Bake
30 minutes at 375°. May be topped
with grated cheese last few minutes of baking. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: oyster soup
directions: Saute onion in	margarine.
Add
milk and cream cheese; cook until smooth.
Add	rest of ingredients.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes, until edge of oysters curl.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Butter baking dish.
Spread 1/4 cup stuffing over bottom of dish.
Saute onion in butter.
Add tomatoes, sugar, salt and garlic powder.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.

title: frozen tomato sauce
directions: Cook until tender.
Cool slightly.
Put 2 cups of vegetables in blender and blend 1 minute.
Pour into containers or bags and freeze.
Good over meats and spaghetti sauce.

title: vanilla milkshake
directions: Beat all together until light and fluffy.
Pour into 2 or 3 chilled glasses.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Core and parboil cabbage.
Mix meat, onion and rice with salt and pepper to taste.
Place portions of meat mixture on cabbage leaves and roll.
Line roaster pan with cabbage leaves; stack rolls.
Mix soup and juice together and pour over rolls.
Top with cabbage leaves.
Cover roaster with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Remove foil for last 1/2 hour.
Leftovers may be frozen and reheated in microwave.

title: veal, creole style
directions: Cut veal into serving pieces and brown in shortening.
When they are half browned, add salt and onions; finish browning.
Add carrots, green pepper, catsup and water.
Cover and cook slowly for 45 minutes.
Thicken gravy if necessary.

title: old fashion rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add pretzels and mix.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Soak the rolls in water for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove and squeeze dry.
Combine meat, rolls and onion.
Add egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well and set aside.

title: hanky pankys
directions: Brown beef and sausage, drain well.
Add cheese, seasonings and stir until cheese is melted.
Spread mixture on bread slices, place on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350 degrees.
Serves a party of 20 to 25.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate the potatoes by hand or in a food processor.
Stir in the onion, eggs, salt, pepper and flour.
Heat a thin layer of oil in a large heavy skillet.
Drop the potato mixture by heaping tablespoonfuls into the oil, flattening each mound with a spatula. Fry the pancakes for about 4 minutes (until golden brown) on each side.
Drain on paper towels.

title: pam's ooy gooies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and pat half of mixture into greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake for 6 minutes at 350°.
Pour chocolate chips over this, melt caramels and 1/3 c.
milk and spread over chips. Crumble rest of cake mixture over caramels and bake for 15 to 18 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: ice box rolls
directions: Mix boiling water, 1/2 cup sugar, shortening and salt and let cool.
Mix warm water, yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar and let set 5 minutes.
Add egg and 2 cups flour and mix with first part and beat good with mixer.
Add 2 more cups flour and mix well and refrigerate.
Makes rolls of desired amount.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.
Refrigerate rest of dough.
Use within 3 days.

title: roast duckling with rice stuffing
directions: Thoroughly defrost duckling.
Remove giblets, neck and excess fat.
Salt the inside.
Place in 8-quart pot, cover with cold water. Place in refrigerator 2 to 4 hours.
Remove duckling and rinse thoroughly.
Cook rice as instructed on package.
Add onions and parsley.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Stuff duckling.
Place on broiler pan which has been coated with cooking spray.
Place duckling on pan and cover with aluminum foil.
Bake for 1/2 hour. Cook for 3 1/2 hours.
Enjoy!

title: cabbage and apples
directions: Cut up one head of cabbage in small pieces.
Put in Dutch oven with enough water to cover.
Add salt, pepper, sugar and Season-All.
Cook over medium heat until almost done.
Peel and slice apples.
Add to cabbage.
Finally add butter.
Continue cooking until both the cabbage and apples appear done.

title: bread recipe(sourdough)
directions: Let set in the fridge for 3 to 5 days. Take out of fridge and add the same ingredients again and let set 8 to 12 hours.
You must feed your starter as directed every 3 to 5 days.

title: cranberry wobbler
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar; set aside.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves. Chill until thickened.
Fold in cranberries, orange and nuts. Spoon into 6-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.
Serves 12.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Cut up lettuce in bite size. Drain corn and put on lettuce. Layer next 6 vegetables or any you prefer in layers.
Top with mayonnaise.
Top with bacon bits.

title: oven clucks and crisp piggy(eggs and bacon casserole)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Spray a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with Pam. Sprinkle crumbled bacon and onion in bottom of casserole. In a small bowl, beat eggs (until slightly frothy). Add milk and pepper. Pour over bacon. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake, uncovered, until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean (about 35 minutes). Serves 4 persons.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender, reserve stock.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Melt margarine in 9 X 13 inch baking dish. Sprinkle the stuffing mix except one cup over the melted margarine.
Saute onion and celery in a little margarine.
Mix with chicken and place on top of stuffing.
Spread all of the soup on top.
Sprinkle reserved stuffing mix on top.
Pour the 2 1/2 cups of chicken broth over all.
Bake at 350 for 35 minutes.

title: creates-its-own-crust coconut pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add milk and flour, blending well.
Add coconut.
Pour into a lightly greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and mix with your flour and salt mixture. Knead just like bread dough for a few minutes.
Put in a greased bowl and let raise for 45 minutes. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 1 round pizza crust.

title: oven stew
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 275°
for 5 hours in covered roaster.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt margarine.
Add mustard, Worcestershire, vinegar, sugar and pepper.
Stir until well mixed and smooth.
Makes enough sauce for 1 hog or to dip approximately 40 chickens.

title: raspberry chambord sauce
directions: Place berries in blender; process until smooth.
Puree through sieve to yield 3/4 cup juice, then discard seeds.

title: whipped sweet potatoes
directions: Pierce each potato twice with a fork so excess steam can escape while cooking.
Microwave* potatoes on HIGH 5 to 10 minutes or until tender, turning potatoes over halfway through cooking. Let stand 5 minutes or until cool enough to handle.

title: one bite mini fruit cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into petite-four cups. Bake 40 minutes at 225°.

title: peach jello salad
directions: In pan, mix water, sugar and jello.
Bring to a boil and stir until jello and sugar is dissolved.
Remove.
Add pineapple and strained peaches.

title: cheese and trees soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion and saute for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, water or broth. Bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and cook until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Remove 1 cup of potatoes with slotted spoon.
Set aside.

title: spinach muffins
directions: *May use broccoli, cauliflower or combination of vegetables.

title: chicken and broccoli bake with scallion cream sauce
directions: Stir cream cheese over low heat until melted.
Slowly add milk, grated cheese and scallions.
In separate bowl mix together chicken, broccoli, red pepper, black pepper and 3/4 of the cream sauce.
Pour into greased casserole dish and pour remaining sauce on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350°, covered with foil, for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bavarian meat balls and pears
directions: Drain pears; save liquid.
Mix beef, bread crumbs, milk, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape into 2 inch balls.
Heat oil. Brown meat balls.
Add 1 cup pear syrup, vinegar, cloves and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add pear halves; simmer 20 minutes more until meat is done.
Remove to warm platter.
Stir flour mixed with 2 tablespoons pear syrup in pan with juices. Cook until thickened.
Pour over meat and pears.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: holiday cutout cookies
directions: Mix
shortening,
sugar, salt, soda and flavoring.
Mix well. Add
egg.
Mix
well.
Add
flour.
Mix well.
Chill in refrigerator
(cover top).
On a lightly floured surface, roll out dough about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.
Cool and put a buttercream icing on them.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs, pumpkin and spices.
Sift together flour and soda.
Add to pumpkin mixture alternately with water.
Beat well.
Pour into well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 3 loaves baked for 1 hour, or 7 small loaves baked for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: marge's deviled eggs
directions: Cook the eggs, cool and peel.
Cut eggs in halves.
Put yolks in bowl; mash with a fork.
Then add everything but the milk and beat with electric mixer.
If too stiff, add the milk.
Fill the whites with the yolk mixture.
Garnish with paprika or small slices of black or stuffed olives, if desired.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Combine jello and boiling water. Stir until gelatin dissolves. Add cranberry sauce, stirring until blended. Chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg white. Fold in orange, apple and pecans.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 cup.
Dissolve sugar and Jell-O in hot water.
Add lemon juice and juice mixture.
Chill until partly set, then add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.

title: strawberry lemon trifle
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and yogurt.
Add the milk, pudding mix and lemon peel.
Beat until smooth in a blender. Process 1/2 cup strawberries and grape juice until smooth.
Tear cake into 1-inch cubes.
Place a third in a trifle bowl or a 3-quart serving bowl.
Top with a third of the pudding mixture and half of the remaining strawberries.
Drizzle with half of strawberry sauce.
Repeat.
Top with remaining cake and pudding mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Yield:
14 servings.

title: kim st. cin's easy cheese pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and cream cheese until smooth.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Pour in pie shell and refrigerate overnight.

title: ginger geometrics
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir baking soda into molasses; set aside for 20 to 30 minutes.
Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon and ginger; set aside.
Combine oil, sugar, egg and molasses in large mixing bowl; mix well.
Stir in flour mixture until well blended.
Press dough evenly into ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake about 15 minutes or until just set. Do not overbake.
Cool on wire rack 15 minutes and cut into trapezoids or other shapes.
Decorate with colored icings, as desired.
Undecorated cookies freeze well.

title: apple oatmeal crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread the sliced apples over the bottom of a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a mixing bowl, combine the sugars, flour and oats, then stir in the melted butter.
Spread this over the apples.
Pour the water evenly over the top.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until the apples are tender. Serve warm with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: baked lamb chops
directions: Flour chops and brown in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Combine all additional ingredients.
Place lamb chops in casserole dish and cover with mixture.
Bake uncovered for 2 hours at 325`.

title: cauliflower oriental
directions: Place cauliflower and water in a 2 quart casserole dish; cover and microwave for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Combine onion, celery, parsley, and butter in a 1 quart casserole dish; microwave for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring halfway through.
Dissolve bouillon in boiling water; stir in cornstarch, soy sauce, and pepper.
Pour this into the onion/celery mixture, cooking an additional 2 minutes or until thick, stirring halfway through.
Pour this mixture over the cauliflower and stir until well combined.

title: breakfast surprise pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line unbaked pie shell with 1/2 Mozzarella cheese strips.
Top cheese with cooked, crumbled sausage.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper; beat well.
Pour over ingredients in shell.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: diabetic sugarless spice cake
directions: Cook raisins and prunes in 1 cup until all water is gone.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl by hand.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Cover bottom of an 8 x 14-inch pan with 1/2 of this mixture. Mix Dream Whip and milk in blender.
When whipped, add sugar, then cream cheese and mix well.
Pour 1/2 of cream cheese mixture over graham cracker crust.
Spoon both cans of pie filing over cream.
Top cherry mixture with remaining half of cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle remaining graham cracker crumbs over cream mixture.
Let stand for 1 hour before serving.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit and combine.
Mix brown sugar, ginger, curry powder and margarine.
Pour over fruit.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
Goes well with Breakfast Casserole.

title: sour cream raisin pie #2
directions: Line pan with half the pastry.
Combine raisins and flour. Put in pan.
Mix the remainder of the ingredients and pour into shell over raisins.
Put top crust and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Or bake as is and top with meringue after pie is baked.

title: potato dish
directions: Cook potatoes and shred.
Melt oleo (reserve 1/4 cup for topping).
Cook cream of chicken soup with 1/4 cup oleo until smooth, then add sour cream with minced onion, salt and pepper. Pour liquid over potatoes, stir thoroughly.
If it seems dry, add a little milk.
Sprinkle 2 cups of shredded cheese on top, then sprinkle 2 cups of barbecue potato chips, crushed, over the top. Pour the other 1/4 cup of oleo over the top.
Bake at 350° if potatoes are warm for 15 minutes.
If they are cold, bake for 45 minutes.

title: abbott's stew
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Pour over beef in shallow dish. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Drain meat, saving marinade. Discard bay leaves.
Brown meat in oil.
Add broth and remaining marinade, bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add carrots, onions and potatoes.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes more.

title: burrito wraps
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Spread 2 tablespoons of mixture on 1/2 of a tortilla.
Roll tortilla, starting on the mixture side. Repeat rolling until all 8 finished.
Freeze 10 minutes.
Cut rolls in bite sizes (approximately 1/2 inch) and serve.

title: hershey with almond pie
directions: Line pan and bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse all beans.
Beat vinegar, sugar and oil.
Pour over mixture of ingredients.
Cover and chill overnight.
Can be kept several days; stir occasionally.
Makes 8 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together, then fold in the Cool Whip.
Chill, then serve.

title: oven pot roast
directions: You also need an oven dish with lid.

title: date bars
directions: Put 1/2 of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Spread filling evenly and sprinkle other half of mixture on top.
Pat lightly.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lemon ice cream soda
directions: Put milk and lemonade concentrate in a tall glass.
Add vanilla ice cream.
Almost fill with soda water.
Garnish with a strip of lemon peel.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix ingredients together with spoon. Pour into greased cake pan. Bake.

title: adobong carne(beef in hot and tangy coconut sauce)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except coconut milk, in a pot and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for an hour or until beef is tender.
Remove hot peppers after first 30 minutes and set aside.
(Or add peppers during last 10 minutes of cooking for not too hot a sauce.)
Add coconut milk and simmer 5 minutes longer. Return hot peppers.

title: virginia sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain the sweet potatoes well.
Hand mash, or with a food processor, combine sweet potatoes and all other ingredients.
Bake until glazed at 400°, then turn down the heat to 350°.
Small marshmallows can be added to the top and browned just before serving.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; crumble.
Set aside.
Wash broccoli; cut flowerets.
Slice onion very thin.
Mix broccoli, onion, raisins, sunflower seeds and bacon.
In small bowl mix Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over vegetables just before serving.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil sugars, syrup and water together in large pan to soft-crack stage or 290° on candy thermometer.
Add butter and melt.
Add vanilla and soda; stir until thick and creamy.
Pour over warm popcorn, mixing well.
Add nuts.
Shape into balls, if desired.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place browned hamburger and onion in bottom of casserole. Place drained green beans on top.
Cover with soup, slightly diluted.
Put Tater Tots on top and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours until Tater Tots are done.
You may also put grated cheese between green beans and Tater Tots if you use soup other than Cheddar cheese or you can omit cheese altogether.

title: pralines(microwave)
directions: Combine pecans, sugar, margarine and Pet milk in 8-cup glass bowl; mix thoroughly.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Remove from microwave and beat well.
Add vanilla and salt.
Return to microwave and cook 5 minutes more.
Remove from microwave.
Beat well and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter; add sugar.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly for 2 minutes.
Add milk.
Bring to full boil.
Remove and add 3 1/2 cups xxxx sugar, then beat.
Adjust the thickness of icing by using either more or less sugar.
Add vanilla, if desired.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in boiling, salted water until tender.
(Cut squash in thin slices before cooking.)
Drain off water, mash squash and add pepper, butter and cheese.
Mix well.
Put in Pyrex dish; bake at 350° in oven for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Let squash begin bubbling.
Take out of oven and let stand for about 5 minutes.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line muffin pan with paper cupcake liners.
In a large bowl combine oat bran, nuts, raisins, sugar, baking powder and spices.
Mix milk, egg whites, oil, applesauce and vanilla in a bowl.
Combine with oat bran.
Fill cupcake liners.
Bake 17 minutes.
Refrigerate if not used in 3 days as they contain no preservatives.

title: pumpkin raisin cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, pumpkin pie spice, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside.

title: chocolate cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Combine cream cheese, unbeaten egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt; beat well.
Stir in chocolate bits.
In another bowl, sift flour, cocoa, 1 cup sugar, soda and 1 teaspoon salt. Add water, oil and vinegar.
Fill cupcake papers with batter 2/3 full.
Top each with 1 teaspoon cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts and small amounts of sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen cupcakes.

title: mazetti
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix all ingredients including can of cheese sauce from macaroni dinner.
Bake at 400° until hot and bubbly.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese if desired.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and boil eggplant until tender.
Drain and mash.
Saute onion and pepper.
Combine eggplant, onion, tomato sauce, pepper, salt, pimento, crumbled crackers, beaten egg and cheese.
Pour into buttered dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: yogurt pops
directions: Mix well and freeze in molds (3 ounce paper cups work). Insert popsicle sticks when partially frozen.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Add 1/2 cup Eagle Brand milk and butter.
Pour 1/2 of batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Melt caramel squares and remainder of Eagle Brand milk in double boiler.
Pour over the partly baked cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over this. Pour the remainder of batter over chips and nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese-grits casserole
directions: Cook grits according to package. Add butter and cheese.
Stir until melted. Add Worcestershire sauce and paprika, mixing well. Add a small amount of hot grits to eggs.
Stir well.
Stir egg mixture into remaining grits.
Lightly grease two 1-quart baking dishes.
Divide grits equally into dishes and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon paprika. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking. Bake at 325° for 1
hour, uncovered.

title: r. p.'s crock-pot stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces.
Coat with flour, salt and pepper and brown on all sides.
Remove meat.
Brown onions. Alternate meat and onions in crock-pot.
Mix remaining and pour over meat and onions.
Cook 11 hours on low.

title: rigatoni alla vodka
directions: Saute shallots in pan with butter.
When golden, remove from heat and add vodka.
Meanwhile, cook pasta.
Wait until flame subsides.
Add chicken stock and tomatoes.
Reduce over medium flame 2 minutes.
Add cream, salt, pepper and parsley.
Cook briefly.
Toss with cooked pasta and add cheese.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in 3-quart pan; stir well.
Cook 2 1/2 minutes; add pecans and stir until coated.
Then spread on waxed paper and separate with fork; spread fast.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over pork chops in shallow dish. Refrigerate, covered, 6 hours or overnight, turning occasionally. Then grill outdoors over medium coals, brushing occasionally with marinade.

title: marvelous fresh strawberry pie
directions: In large saucepan, combine sugar, water and cornstarch over medium heat.
Stir until clear and thickened.
Add gelatin.
Let mixture cool.
Add strawberries to cooled gelatin mixture.
Pour strawberry filling into 2 baked pie shells.
Chill pies until ready to serve.
Top with whipped cream if desired.
Yields 2 pies (8 slices each).

title: chicken stew and dumplings
directions: In saucepan, put water, onion flakes, bouillon, celery, carrots and seasonings.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add chicken and peas.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and water until clear.
Add jello to hot mixture and stir to dissolve jello.
Cool.
Add one quart washed, whole strawberries to cooked pie crust.
Pour cooled mixture over berries.
Refrigerate until set, approximately 4 hours.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: pineapple "fondue"
directions: Crush vanilla wafers and line bottom of greased 9-inch baking dish, setting aside a small amount.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs and pour this mixture over wafer crumbs.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top.
Drain liquid from pineapple and place over nuts.
Top with whipped cream and the remaining wafer crumbs as decoration. Chill at least 4 hours.
Can be made 1 to 2 days ahead.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Drain pickles in colander and wash well.
Mix sugar, vinegar and spices and put back in jar.
Cut up pickles in finger size pieces and put back in jar.
Invert jar 2 or 3 times a day until sugar has melted and then store in refrigerator.
Good with soup or sandwiches.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar; combine with all dry ingredients.
Blend in eggs and buttermilk until well blended, then add food coloring. Bake at 350°.

title: tater tot 'n cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with the butter.
In a mixing bowl, whisk eggs and milk together. Season mixture with salt and pepper.
Add 1 cup of each cheese, ham and Tater Tots.
Pour mixture into prepared pan.
Sprinkle top of mixture with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: cornbread muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift the dry ingredients together in a bowl.
In another bowl, beat the eggs with the milk, then mix them into the dry ingredients.
Fold in the corn kernels and melted butter.
Pour into 8 to 10 muffin pans, buttered, and bake for 30 minutes or until golden.
Serve hot. Delicious with honey!

title: double apple salad
directions: Combine jello with hot apple juice.
Allow to soft set.
Stir in apples, celery and nuts and allow to set.
Very good!

title: caramel pie
directions: Place both cans of condensed milk in a deep boiler. Cover with water and boil 3 hours. (Keep covered with water.) Take out of water and set aside for approximately 10 minutes before opening. Place a dish towel over can when opening (contents may come out a little). Pour into pie crust. Chill for several hours. Serve with Cool Whip. Small servings suggested. Very rich, but very good!!

title: white fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan melt Almond bark and milk.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Spread into an 8x8-inch pan lined with waxed paper.
Let stand for 2 to 3 hours before cutting.

title: zucchini nut loaf
directions: Stir flour, baking powder, soda, etc.
Set aside.
Beat eggs, sugar, oil and add to flour mixture with zucchini and nuts.
Mix well.
Grease 9 x 5 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan and remove.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add unbeaten eggs and vanilla. Blend thoroughly with mixer.
Add dry ingredients alternately with bananas, blending well after each addition.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Makes 2 (1 pound) loaves. Bake in 325° oven for 60 to 65 minutes.
Great use of overripe bananas!

title: crabmeat appetizers
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients together.
Spread on muffins; sprinkle with paprika.
Cut into 1/4's or 1/8's.
Freeze on a cookie tray about 15 minutes, then place in a plastic bag and freeze.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until bubbly. Serve.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Mix pudding, cool whip and pineapple together to make frosting.
Refrigerate till firm.

title: pineapple icebox dessert
directions: Line an 8 x 12-inch baking pan with half of the water crumbs. Cream sugar and butter in a bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Spread over crumbs; add pineapple and spread whipped cream on top.
Sprinkle with pecans and top with remaining crumbs.
Garnish with additional whipped cream and cherries.
Yield: 18 to 20 servings.

title: sicilian supper(poor man's lasagna)
directions: For easy barbecue sauce, use equal parts of ketchup and grape or blackberry jelly.
Parboil smoked sausage.
Cut sausage in about 2-inch pieces.
Place in baking pan.
Cover with barbecue sauce.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rattlesnake chili
directions: In skillet, brown choice of ground meat with onion and garlic. Put in electric slow-cooker, adding remaining ingredients.
In pot, bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes to an hour. In slow-cooker, on low setting cook 6 hours or overnight.
Serves 6.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Cut in margarine until it looks like cornmeal.
Add egg and extract.
Mix well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased sheet. Place almond on top of each cookie and press to flatten slightly. Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Combine ingredients as listed.
Dot with cracker crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate and peanut butter angel cake
directions: Cut a 1-inch layer from the top of the angel food cake.
Cut the middle of the cake, leaving walls and bottom 1 inch thick. Fill cavity with chocolate silk pie mixture that has been made from directions on box.
Sprinkle half of crust crumbs (inside of box) over silk mixture in angel food cake.
Replace top.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes and add all ingredients except marshmallows. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.
Top with marshmallows the last minutes of baking.

title: baked limas
directions: Soak baby lima beans overnight.
Cook about 1 hour until soft. Drain.
Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 300° about 2 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cut up chicken; layer ingredients.
Combine soup, garlic salt and chili powder.
Pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° until center bubbles and top is brown.

title: cocktail shrimp spread or dip
directions: Mash cream cheese well with lemon juice; add onion, celery, catsup and salt and blend well.
Add shrimp.
Let stand for about 1 hour.
Serve with crackers.

title: "quick and easy" chicken and dumplings
directions: Rub flour on both sides of tortillas, using all of flour.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Bring broth and seasonings to a rolling boil.
Drop tortillas in broth.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Stir in cooked chicken and milk until heated. Let stand off heat for 5 to 10 minutes, covered.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into golf ball size balls.
Cook 1 hour.

title: patti's pecan pie
directions: In quart pan over low heat, mix brown sugar and butter until well blended.
Remove from fire and add sugar, mixing well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add salt, syrup and milk and mix well.
Put back over low fire for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire and stir in pecans and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 1 hour at 350° until golden brown.

title: strawberry stuff
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Chill in refrigerator for one hour.
Serves 8.
Approximately 303 calories per serving.

title: hog heaven cookies
directions: Flatten crescent rolls into a rectangular shape on greased cookie sheet, pressing seams together.
Heat sugar and butter together until pouring consistency.
Pour over rectangle.
Cover with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.
As soon as it comes out of the oven, pour on a package of chocolate chips.
Let stand a few minutes to soften, then use a spatula to spread chocolate as a topping over all.
Cool; cut into small squares.

title: potato wedges - cajun
directions: Preheat oven 425°.
Wash potatoes and cut into wedges with skin on.
Place potatoes in large bowl or plastic bag with oil and minced garlic, toss and coat well.
Combine all other spices and sprinkle on potatoes, place potatoes on cookie sheet or shallow baking dish and bake 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and grill another 20 minutes or bake 45 minutes.

title: red lobster cheddar bay biscuits(a copykat recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Mix together baking mix, cold water, and grated cheese. Cut biscuits with a cutter, and place onto a baking dish. Melt butter and seasonings together. Brush with the butter and spices and bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: amish wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
It will be dark.

title: carol damato's eggplant pie
directions: Saute eggplant, onion and garlic in butter.
Add seasoning. Cover bottom and sides of pie crust with zucchini slices.
Add the eggplant mixture.
Combine the milk and egg; stir in the cheese. Pour this over the veggies.
Preheat the oven and cookie sheet to 375°.
Bake pie for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spinach and bacon quiche
directions: Prepare pastry, put into 10 inch pie pan and bake at 375° for 5 to 6 minutes.
Meanwhile grate cheese.
Combine with eggs, cream, milk, and seasonings.
Mix well.
Add the cooked, drained spinach and the bacon and mix.
Pour into partially baked pastry shell.
Place in oven and bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until the quiche is set and a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Serve warm.
Serves 6.

title: goat cheese and basil bites
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine cheese, garlic, oregano and pepper.
Mix well.
Top each muffin with slice of tomato and brush with olive oil.
Place 1 teaspoon cheese mixture on top of tomatoes and bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with basil.
Serve immediately.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, salt and cocoa together.
Add soda to milk.
Add milk and dry ingredients alternately to creamed mixture.
Blend well; add vanilla and food coloring.
Add vinegar last.
Pour into 3 layer pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: corn vegetable casserole
directions: Cook veggies in water until tender; salt to taste.
Add milk to corn soup and heat to a boil.
In a casserole dish, layer 1/2 of drained and cooked veggies, then sprinkle 1/2 of cheese and 1/2 of corn soup.

title: baked hominy and cheese
directions: Beat egg.
Add hominy, cheese, milk, onion, bacon, butter and pepper; mix well.
Spoon in baking dish, 11 x 7 x 2-inch, greased. Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 8.

title: my mother's easy grape juice
directions: Put into quart jar and fill jar with boiling water.
Cold pack 20 minutes.

title: french onion casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook sliced onions in 2 tablespoons of butter for about 10 minutes or until onions are tender, stirring often.
Transfer onions to a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer Swiss cheese over onions.

title: marinated chicken strips with honey-mustard dressing
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Add chicken; cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Snap off and discard tough ends of asparagus spears and steam 8 to 12 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Drain chicken, reserving 1/2 cup marinade; return chicken to baking dish. Combine mustard, sesame seed and reserved marinade and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done, turning once. Remove from marinade and drain on paper towels.
Combine lettuces; place 1 1/2 cups on each of 12 serving plates.
Arrange remaining ingredients on lettuce and serve with Honey-Mustard Sauce.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix all together and place in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle dry yellow cake mix over this.
Cube 1 stick of butter and dot top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake another 1/4 hour or until done.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: layered jello
directions: Mix 1 package lime jello with 3/4 cup boiling water and 3/4 cup (1/2 can) evaporated milk. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and refrigerate until set. Mix 2nd package of lime jello with 1 1/4 cups boiling water. Pour over first layer and refrigerate. Repeat with other flavors.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, then sifted dry ingredients and mix in rest of ingredients.
Bake in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water in skillet over high heat.
Add peanuts and salt.
Turn to medium and cook 10 minutes.
Stir in butter and soda and mix well.
Pour into greased dish.

title: taco appetizer
directions: Blend avocado, cream cheese, sour cream and lemon juice in a blender or processor until smooth.
Spread mixture in an 8-inch pie plate.
Layer the remaining ingredients in the order listed. Refrigerate before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.
Serve with taco chips.

title: rum cake
directions: Beat all ingredients for 10 minutes.
Grease and flour Bundt pan, then sprinkle bottom of pan with 1/4 cup chopped pecans. Pour batter over nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
While hot and still in pan, pour glaze over cake.
Cake will shrink.

title: rolls
directions: Mix together 1 cup lukewarm water, yeast and pinch of sugar. Let set, without stirring, 5 minutes.
Add 1 cup lukewarm water, oil, sugar and salt.
Stir until sugar melts and blends in.
Add flour all at one time; stir until blended.
Set aside and let rise until doubled.
Punch down.

title: pina colada smoothie
directions: In a blender, mix tofu and pineapple chunks on whip setting for about 20 seconds until well incorporated. Next, add yogurt, flax seed oil, coconut extract and water. Serve immediately and freeze leftovers.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix with margarine and 2 eggs.
Press into the bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix vanilla, cream cheese, powdered sugar, remaining 2 eggs and salt.	Pour over cake mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: quick chocolate sauce
directions: Add the melted chocolate to the corn syrup.
Stir until well blended, then stir in the vanilla.

title: aunt eula's raisin cookies
directions: Boil raisins, water and soda for 5 minutes and cool.
Cream butter or Crisco with sugar and add egg (beaten).
Stir in cooled raisins.
Add flour, cinnamon, baking powder, vanilla and salt. Stir and drop from spoon onto greased pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach madeline
directions: Cook spinach; drain and reserve liquid.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until blended and smooth, not brown.
Add onion and cook until soft, not brown.
Add both liquids slowly, stirring constantly to avoid lumps.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Continue stirring.
Add seasonings and cheese.
Stir.
Combine with spinach.
Serve immediately or put in casserole dish and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Best done the day before and you can freeze it, too!

title: punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Some of the liquid may be frozen to float in punch bowl.

title: granola bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and heat until blended.
Then cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve the yeast in the warm water and add to the cooled mixture.
Add the remaining ingredients and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in large greased bowl, cover and let rise in warm place for 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down.
Put in 4 greased loaf pans and let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put in order. Can add green beans, broccoli, carrots or any vegetables towards end of cooking. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mom's tomato cocktail
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 20 minutes; chill.
Strain and serve.
Garnish with celery stalk, if desired, or "doctor up" otherwise.

title: venison stew with dumplings
directions: Shake the venison in 1 cup salted flour in a plastic or paper bag.
In a large pot (or pressure cooker, if the meat is tough), saute in cooking oil until browned.
Add a small amount of water, tomatoes, carrots, onion, garlic, garlic powder and bay leaves. Cook until meat is tender.
Add potatoes and continue cooking until these are tender.
It may be necessary to add more water during the cooking.

title: fabulous cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans.
Shape into 1 large ball, or 2 small balls.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Chill overnight. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: sky high biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Cut in margarine until mixture equals coarse cornmeal.
Add egg and milk, stirring quickly.
Knead lightly on floured board.
Roll 1-inch thick.
Cut into biscuits.
Place on greased pan 1-inch apart. Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Make 1 recipe of pastry shell.
Divide into 2 balls of dough. Roll out 1 crust to fit pie pan.
Empty apples into large container.
Add flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Use both hands to mix all ingredients; mix well.
Divide apples and juice into 4 equal parts.
Take one part of apple mixture and put into raw pie shell.
Roll out second ball of dough and place over apples to form a top crust.
Flute edges with fork and prick top of crust with fork tong.
Make about 10 pricks in crust.
Paint with melted butter.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease the bottom only of a loaf pan.
Mix sugar and butter in a bowl. Stir in eggs until blended.
Add bananas and water.
Beat. Stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened.
Pour into pan. Bake until toothpick comes out clean. Bake 8-inch loaf pan about 1 1/4 hours.
Bake a 9-inch loaf pan about 55 to 60 minutes. Cool and remove from pan.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: In top of double boiler, beat egg yolks until thick and lemon-colored.
Add 1 tablespoon lemon juice and water; beat together.
Stir in 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Place over hot, not boiling, water and stir constantly until egg yolk mixture is slightly thickened.
(Do not allow to curdle.)
Remove immediately from heat and beat in 1 tablespoon butter.
Gradually add remaining melted butter, 1 tablespoon at a time, stirring constantly.
When thickened, season with remaining lemon juice, cayenne pepper and salt.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt butter, then add all ingredients.
Pour in baking dish and cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple lemon salad
directions: Drain pineapple and set aside.

To the pineapple juice, add enough water to make 2 cups of liquid. Bring 1 cup of liquid to a boil. Add gelatin and stir until dissolved. Add remaining liquid and lemon juice. Gradually add yogurt, mixing well. Chill until thick, but not set. Add drained pineapple.
Pour into square container.
Chill and serve on lettuce leaves or as you like.

title: oyster stew
directions: Put raw oysters in saucepan.
Add butter and seasoning.
Cook for 2 minutes, allowing edges of oysters to curl.
Add milk and heat, but not to boiling point.
Salt to taste and sprinkle with paprika in serving dishes.

title: mom's bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice vegetables and sprinkle salt over all.
Let stand for 3 hours; drain.
Heat sugar, turmeric, ground cloves, mustard seed and vinegar thoroughly (do not boil).
Add to vegetables.
Pack in jars and seal.
These are best if kept in jars 3 weeks before opening.

title: coq au vin
directions: In large skillet, cook onion and mushrooms in butter over medium-high heat for 4 to 5 minutes or until tender.
Add chicken, wine, tarragon, pepper, and salt.
Bring just to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: strawberry freeze
directions: Place berries and Equal in food processor or blender.
Mix until coarsely chopped.
With motor running, gradually add milk. Mix until smooth.
Serve.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Warm soup with gelatin until dissolved.
Soften cream cheese and add remaining ingredients.
Blend well and pour into mold. Chill overnight.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: old fashioned popcorn balls
directions: Place popped popcorn in a large pan. Combine sugar, molasses and vinegar and cook to medium crack stage or 270°.
Remove from heat. Stir in butter and soda into syrup mixture.
Pour over popcorn and stir to mix thoroughly.
Cool slightly until you can shape into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli according to directions and drain.
Melt the cheese and 1/2 the butter.
Add lemon juice, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over broccoli.

title: beef alamo
directions: Score steak diagonally on both sides at 1-inch intervals in diamond pattern.
Spread mustard over both sides.
Chill, covered, for several hours.
Grill over medium-hot coals for 8 to 10 minutes on each side.
Stack tortillas; wrap in foil.
Place on edge of grill to warm.
Cut steak into thin slices.
Spoon onto warm tortillas.
Top with mixture of onion, tomatoes and chilies. Roll tortillas to enclose filling.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: nut brown bread
directions: Pour 1 cup of boiling water over the dates, sugar and butter. When cold, add flour, soda, egg, nuts and salt.
Bake slowly about 1 hour.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Form into 1-inch balls and put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press cookies with fork to make a crisscross.
Bake for 10 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.
My cookies are quick, easy and so good!!

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook the fryer and stew meat until well done. Grind in blender and set aside. Put onions through blender. Add onion and potatoes to broth from the chicken and stew meat. Cook until done in saucepan on top of range. Add meat and other ingredients. Place in slow cooker and cook on low for 12 hours or high for 8 to 10 hours. Add 1/2 cup barbecue sauce. Yield: About 8 to 10 servings.

title: sunset salad
directions: Mix jello as directed on package.
Fold in cheese, beating with a mixer.
Add whipped cream and pineapple.
Add nuts and marshmallows last. They do not need to be beaten.
Looks pretty just mixed in with spoon.

title: jelly roll
directions: Set out eggs 1 hour ahead.

title: ma-maw hash's fruit salad
directions: Add juice from pineapple and heat.
Add both boxes of Jell-O and cool.
Fold in other ingredients and refrigerate.

title: baked bean medley
directions: Fry bacon first, then brown ground chuck and onion together. Drain.
Grease a 2 or 3-quart casserole and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Can be extended with catsup, ground chuck or ground pork and pork and beans.

title: chili dip(appetizer)
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, spread cream cheese, softened, in bottom of pan.
Then spread the chili on top of cheese.
Last, spread over top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Place in oven until all is melted on top and hot.
Can also be put in Pyrex pan and covered then placed in microwave for 8 to 10 minutes on regular heat. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Make batter from beating together the egg, flour, salt and milk.
Dip onion rings into batter.
Lower into hot fat (375°) to float.
Fry until brown, about 2 minutes.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix beans and taco seasoning; spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread sour cream over beans.
Layer lettuce, tomatoes and onion.
Pour taco sauce over this, then add olives and cheese.

title: escalloped tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: skillet peanut butter fudge
directions: In electric skillet, combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk.
Set heat control at 280°.
Bring to a boil; boil 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn heat off.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla to skillet fudge.
Smask marshmallow and peanut butter, stirring and mixing well until well blended (do quickly as fudge is setting).
When mixed well, pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool and cut.
Makes 2 pounds.
Never fails. Crunchy peanut butter is best.

title: dannemann delight
directions: In a blender or beater, blend equal amounts of your favorite fruit and low-fat plain yogurt. Chill, if desired, and enjoy.
If you do not like yogurt, mix thoroughly and add a bit more fruit. (Give it a try.)

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and flour until it begins to thicken.
Add Jell-O.
Cook until clear and thick.
Place strawberries in baked pie crust.
Pour filling over strawberries.
Chill.
Spread whipped topping on top.
Serves 6.

title: momsie's vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients
and serve with vegetable tray. This recipe is best if made the day before.

title: oreo pudding dessert
directions: 1st Layer:
Smash Oreos and melt butter.
Combine and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press and freeze.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Pour butter over pretzels.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; melt 1 stick of butter and crumble one stack of Ritz or regular crackers on top of dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: plum cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Beat in eggs, baby food and food coloring.
Sift flour, soda and spices together.
Gradually add dry ingredients to liquid mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour batter into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Ice while warm.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together; shape into loaf and put into baking dish. Pour about 1/8 cup of water over the top and place in preheated oven at 350°; bake, uncovered, approximately 45 minutes.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Add ground pork to broth and boil until meat is white.
Add salt, peppers and vinegar.
Add corn, tomatoes and chicken. Simmer about 2 1/2 hours, stirring frequently.

title: sue's banana yams
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until soft.
Peel and mash while still hot.
Add cream and mashed bananas.
Mix well and place in a buttered baking dish.
Cover mixture with marshmallows and place in hot oven.
Bake until marshmallows are golden brown.

title: chicken taco rice
directions: Cook and stir chicken in oil until browned.
Add broth, tomato sauce and seasoning mix.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add corn and green pepper.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Serve with cheese, sour cream and tortilla chips.
Serves 4.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix eggs and milk.
Add other ingredients.
Pour onto heated griddle.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli as directed on package.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Do not cover.

title: caramels
directions: In a large bowl, combine oats and coconut; set aside.
In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, oil, honey and cinnamon; bring to a boil.
remove from the heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour over oat mixture; stir to coat.
Spread in a large shallow baking pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool. Add raisins.
Store in an airtight container.
Yield:
6 cups.

title: tex-mex meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, beans, 1 cup picante sauce, onion, garlic, bread crumbs, eggs, cumin and salt; mix well.
Press into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Pour off drippings.

title: coney island sauce
directions: Grind together the bologna, green pepper and onions.
Put in kettle.
Add the tomato juice, ketchup and chili powder.
Bring to a boil and simmer 4 hours.
Makes 1 quart.
Divide into small containers and freeze.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar, water and oil.
Cool and pour over drained kraut.
Add rest of ingredients and stir well.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: spinach dip
directions: Toss; refrigerate 24 hours.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Saute bell pepper and onion in oil.
Add rest of ingredients and bake at 350° until rice is done.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on until done.
Cube the larger ones and cut the smaller in half.
Add rest of ingredients.
Serve warm or chilled.
Pretty served on a bed of lettuce.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing and melted margarine.
Place half in deep casserole dish.
Add sliced chicken.
Combine soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Add remaining stuffing on top.
Pour 1 1/2 cups broth over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt butter in frypan.
Saute onions until clear.
Reserve 3 teaspoons cracker crumbs for topping and place remaining crumbs in lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Remove onions from pan.
Add soup and onions in alternating layer in casserole.
Combine eggs and milk and pour over onions.
Top with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Spread equal amounts of mixture over one end of each tortilla.
Roll up tortilla.
Cover each rolled up tortilla with plastic wrap; twist ends. Refrigerate for several hours.
Unwrap and cut into slices.
Serve with salsa for dipping.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together.
Beat eggs and add mashed bananas. Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Add to mixture.
Mix well and add nuts.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° until well done.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Separate sausage and brown.
Add greens and wilt.
Put dry rice in casserole and pour broth over it.
Pour sausage and greens; cook 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Add water if dry.
Use a 2-quart casserole dish.

title: baked tortellini with basil-cheese sauce
directions: Grease a deep baking dish.
Cook tortellini in 2 quarts boiling water until just tender.
Drain.
Melt butter over medium heat and make a roux by stirring in flour and stirring constantly for 3 minutes.
Add milk and stock, stirring until mixture boils and thickens.
Add basil and garlic (or pesto), nutmeg, salt and pepper.

title: gelatin-sour cream mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: strawberry banana freeze(makes 2 servings)
directions: Combine orange juice, honey, banana and strawberries in electric blender.
Cover; whirl at high speed until smooth.
With motor running, gradually add as much crushed ice as necessary for desired thickness.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. In large mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt, then sift. Using fingertips, rub butter and Crisco into dry ingredients until mix appears like crumbs. Make a well in center; pour in chilled buttermilk. Stir just until dough comes together. Dough will be very sticky. Turn dough onto floured surface; dust top with flour and gently fold dough over on itself 5 or 6 times. Press into a 1-inch thick round. Cut out biscuits with a 2-inch cutter, being sure to push straight down through the dough. Give the cutter a twist when you get to the bottom. Place biscuits on baking sheet so that they just touch. Reform scrap dough. Working it as little as possible and continue cutting. Press thumb in center of each biscuit to make a slight indentation. Bake until biscuits are tall and light gold on top, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked apples with raisins
directions: Place cored apples in a deep baking dish.
Simmer raisins in water for about 10 minutes.
Divide raisins into apples. Sprinkle cinnamon and cloves over the apples.
Add a small amount of extra water and margarine or butter.
Cover; cook in microwave on High for 15 minutes.
Check for the firmness you would like.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix oleo with boiling water and mix well with Bisquick.
Press in 9 x 9-inch square pan and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: boneless chicken saute
directions: In heavy skillet, melt butter and brown onion.
Add chicken and saute 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms, spices and 1/2 cup water. Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes to reduce liquids.
Add vermouth and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.
May add light cream and heat.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: marguerite's orange julius
directions: Blend 1/2 minute in blender.
Top with vanilla ice cream.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add milk, cornmeal, vinegar, lemon juice and salt.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake until set, about 45 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Wash and drain cranberries.
Do not peel apples and oranges. Remove seeds and core.
Grind all together.
Add sugar.
Put in large container or individual cups and refrigerate.
Make before Thanksgiving and save some for Christmas.

title: crock-pot soy glazed spareribs
directions: Place ribs on rack and bake 30 minutes at 400°, turning once. Remove and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place ribs in crock-pot and cover with sauce.
Cook on low 7 hours.
Remove ribs and set crock-pot to high.
Mix cornstarch and cold water and pour in cooked sauce.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes until sauce begins to thicken. Return ribs and coat with sauce.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add corn and eggs.
Scald milk.
Add slowly to egg mixture.
Stir well.
Add butter.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake 35 minutes at 325° or until top is slightly brown and firm in middle.
Serves 6.

title: bean soup
directions: Rinse and sort beans; cover with water and heat to boiling; boil uncovered for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 1 hour.
Add all other ingredients and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add more water if needed.

title: secret salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Stir.
Add cold water.
When mixture starts to thicken, add drained pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: praline squares
directions: Arrange crackers 1 layer deep in an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Place butter and brown sugar in a saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture over grahams.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Let stand two minutes.
Cut into squares while still warm.
Store in a cookie can.

title: dutch pantry pie with sauce
directions: Place 1 pie crust in pie pan or dish.
Melt cheese in 1/2 can of cream.
Add potatoes, onion, green pepper and salt to taste. Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Add diced Treet and top pie crust. Slit for steam.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: cheezy grits
directions: Cook grits in boiling water for 3 to 5 minutes. Combine the eggs (be sure to add a little hot grits while beating eggs so they don't curdle), paprika, butter or margarine, cheese, seasoned salt or garlic powder and Tabasco to taste and add to grits. Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 6 to 8.

title: corn bread
directions: In a large bowl combine flour, corn meal, baking powder, salt and sugar.
In a medium bowl combine eggs, milk, butter and corn. Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
Put in a small pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, milk and cocoa.
Bring to full boil. Remove from heat.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until peanut butter is melted.
Add quick oats instant oatmeal.
Drop onto waxed paper.

title: marinade for steak or beef roast
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over meat.
Refrigerate 8 to 12 hours, turning meat in marinade several times.
Save marinade to baste with if you are grilling meat.

title: texas chili
directions: Brown meat with onion, garlic and seasonings.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for at least one hour.
Serves 8.

title: baked glazed apples
directions: Mix apples with brown sugar, butter and ground cinnamon.
Add graham cracker crumbs and mix together.
Bake for about 45 minutes.
Serves 12 or more.

title: petite pecan tarts
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter. Blend in flour and chill for at least 1 hour. Shape into balls about 1-inch in diameter and press into tiny ungreased muffin tins.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl; use wooden spoon.
Stir in flour, cinnamon, powder and soda.
Mix well. Fold in rest of the ingredients.
Place in a greased Bundt pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool, then remove from pan.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain liquid from green beans.
Put in greased casserole. Blend mushroom soup with green beans.
Bake at 350° to 375° until soup begins to bubble.
Cover with French fried onions and bake until browned.

title: linda's west virginia biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening; blend.
Then add milk and blend to soft dough.
Turn out on floured board; knead just enough to give dough smooth surface.
Then roll out about 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut and place in greased pan.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Melt in your mouth.

title: chinese style barbecued ribs(an appetizer)
directions: Cut the ribs in half (or have the butcher do it).
Marinate ribs for 4 hours or even overnight.
Keep refrigerated.
Drain. Bake in oven at 325° for 30 minutes.
Turn ribs over and bake for another 15 minutes at 375°.

title: fruit snack
directions: Cut tops off berries; slice into small pieces and wash well. Add the sugar and mix it in good.
Slice bananas into the mixture. Stir it up and refrigerate for about 30 minutes.
Other fruits can also be added to make a larger snack.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute
onion,
green
pepper
and garlic in butter in a small skillet.
Combine
cabbage with 2 cups of cheese, bread crumbs, salt
and pepper in a large mixing bowl.
Add sauteed vegetables. Mix
and pour into a greased 3-quart baking dish. Sprinkle
with 1/2 cup cheese and pour the half and half over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: aunt mae's macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni, rinse and drain.
Add onions, cucumbers and tomatoes.
Set aside.
Bring sugar and vinegar to a boil.
Add to macaroni mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: punch
directions: Boil sugar in 2 cups of water. Cool. In a one gallon container, pour in sugar water and mix with kool-aid. Stir. Add frozen orange juice, pink lemonade and pineapple juice. Add enough water to fill one gallon. Stir. Chill. Freezes well in a milk jug. Thaw to a slush.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Add egg yolk, lemon juice, mustard, salt, pepper and oil to container.
Whip until mix becomes thickened.

title: kentucky potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the cheese.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan; top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, covered with foil.

title: stuffed pork tenderloin
directions: With a sharp knife, slit length of tenderloin, about 3/4 through.
In 1-quart pan, put butter, apple juice, onion and stuffing mix.
Combine all until well moistened.
Spread on tenderloin, packing in slightly.
Bring sides up and secure around stuffing, tying well.
Place on rack; bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours. Let cool 10 minutes before slicing and serving.

title: squash patties
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain.
Add chopped onions, salt and eggs.
Mix real good (add grated cheese, if desired).
Add cracker crumbs until easy to handle.
Spoon into skillet with shortening and brown on one side, then flip and brown other side. (Substitute freezer okra for squash and you have delicious fried okra.)

title: turtles
directions: Melt
caramels
and cream in microwave.
Melt chocolate and paraffin together.
Place pecan halves on wax paper.
Pour on caramels.
Top with chocolate.
This is my favorite teacher treat.

title: caramel orange ring
directions: Grease pan.
Add to the bottom chopped nuts and marmalade. Combine brown sugar and cinnamon.
Dip biscuits into melted butter, then roll in cinnamon mixture.
Stand upright in pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili con queso
directions: Saute onions and garlic in shortening.
Add all remaining ingredients, except cheese and simmer 20 minutes.
When ready to serve, add cheese to very hot sauce.
Remove from heat and let cheese melt.
Dip and eat.

title: broccoli with chowder sauce
directions: Cook broccoli in a small amount of boiling salted water until tender; drain well.
Arrange broccoli in a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish; set aside.
Combine chowder, sour cream and salt; mix well.
Spoon over broccoli.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and bake for 2 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: peanut brittle cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter
and
butter
and
mix.
Then add sugar and cream well.
Add
egg and vanilla.
Then add all the rest of the dry
ingredients,
sifting
flour, soda and baking powder together.
Mix well.
Shape in roll about 1 1/2 inch in diameter. Cool
in
icebox.
When
cool,
cut 1/4-inch thick. Place on cookie sheet.
Put	on
top of each cookie 1 teaspoon of peanut brittle.
Bake at 400°.

title: yumoney bars
directions: Combine flour, 1 1/2 cup oats, sugar, soda, salt and melted oleo.
Blend to form crumbs.
Press 1/2 crumbs into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips and 1/2 cup chopped pecans over this.
Mix 3 tablespoons flour with caramel topping; pour over mixture. Sprinkle with remaining crumbs and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
This will set as it sits.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Mix well and add to Starter.
Let Starter stand in fridge all day or until bubbly.
Remove 1 cup to make bread, then return rest to fridge.
Keep for 5 days and feed again (repeat).

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, green pepper, red pepper and salt. Cover with cracked ice.
Mix and let stand 3 hours.
Drain well. Combine remaining ingredients.
Bring just to a boil.
Seal at once in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 8 to 10 pints.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lazy mama's pie
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, mix together cherry pie filling and pineapple.
Sprinkle on cake mix.
(Do not stir.)
Sprinkle on coconut and nuts.
Melt butter and pour over.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef juicy
directions: Line bottom
and
sides
of
long
casserole with heavy Reynolds Wrap before
you
put
meat in.
Put another piece of Reynolds Wrap across top and seal everything in tightly.
Bake at 325° for
hours	until
fork-tender.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes on high speed.
Gradually add sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Fold dry ingredients carefully into egg batter.
Grease a cookie sheet, then cover with wax paper and grease the wax paper.
Spread the batter over pan.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake for 10 to 13 minutes at 375°.
Cover a clean towel with confectioners sugar (dish towel).
Roll up batter in the towel.
When cooled, unroll, fill and reroll.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix sugar and extracts together.
Mix sugar into the egg whites, fold until well blended.
Add pecans and fold again.
Spray Pam on cookie sheet and drop a teaspoon at a time.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Put remaining batter in refrigerator until ready to use again.
Remove cookies while still hot from cookie sheet.
Must be kept dry and don't put them in a sealed container.

title: pie crust for fried pies
directions: Mix flour, shortening and sugar with a fork until mixture resembles coarse corn meal. Add water and continue to mix.
Mix together salt, vinegar and egg. Add to first mixture and mix until it forms a soft ball. Chill at least 15 minutes before rolling out.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Melt chocolate in top of a double boiler.
Beat egg yolks and milk together.
Combine with chocolate and salt.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat; add sugar and butter.
Blend well. Cool.
Add vanilla.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in water and salt for about 5 minutes.
Mix together soup, sour cream, carrots, onion, flour, pepper and broccoli.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix stuffing mix and butter. Place on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a glass or plastic container. Add pork chops, cover and marinate in refrigerator 6 to 8 hours. Remove chops from marinade.
Grill 5 to 6 inches from moderate coals, turning frequently and basting with marinade, 35 to 40 minutes or until well done.
Yields 6 servings.

title: yams or sweet potatoes
directions: Cook yams in water until tender.
Peel and mash.
In a saucepan, mix butter, brown sugar, orange juice and grated orange rind; cook 3 to 5 minutes until well blended.
Mix this sauce into the mashed yams.

title: beef roll-ups
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together until smooth.
Then fold dried beef in half and lightly spread cream cheese mixture on and roll beef slices up.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Mix butter and cream cheese; add flour and mix well.
Shape dough into 24 balls; place each ball into a tassie or tiny muffin cup.
Press dough on bottom and sides of muffin cups to form tart shells.
Break up eggs with fork but do not beat.
Melt remaining butter; add with sugar and vanilla to eggs.
Mix well.
Sprinkle some of the pecans into tart shell; cover with filling.
Sprinkle remaining pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Yields 24 tarts.

title: black-eyed pea soup
directions: Saute onion in bottom of Dutch oven.
Add other ingredients, except rice.
Bring to boil and lower heat.
Add zucchini that has been cut into bite-sized pieces and cooked rice.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
This soup gets better the second day.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Brown the chicken breasts in 3 tablespoons olive oil.
Make a thick sauce of the mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese and the oregano. Place the chicken breasts in a ceramic casserole.
Cover with the sauce mixture.
Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs on the top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Garnish with fresh parsley when served.
Serves 6.

title: no fail fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese.
Mix vanilla, cocoa, and pecans with cheese mixture. Add powdered sugar gradually.
If mixture gets too stiff while mixing, put on low heat until mixed well.
Pour onto large buttered cookie sheet.
Makes about 6 1/2 pounds.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut in blender or with mixer. Stir in coconut by hand.
Pour in pie crust.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes or until done.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute bacon.
Remove.
Set aside and drain.
Brown ground round, onion, rice, tomato juice or canned tomatoes, garlic, green pepper and paprika.
Add bacon.
Cover.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: mexican pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 10-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion in 10-inch skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread beef mixture in pie plate.
Sprinkle with chilies and cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high speed or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean (25 to 30 minutes).
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except egg whites.
Cook on low heat until thick.
Cool, then pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until foamy; add 1/2 cup sugar gradually and beat until stiff. Top pie with beaten egg white mixture.
Brown in 350° oven until golden.

title: german apple cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel apples; slice thin.
Toss apples with 5 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Set aside.
Mix together flour, sugar, salt, eggs, oil, vanilla, orange juice, baking soda and baking powder.
With electric mixer, blend together on low speed for 1 minute.
Clean down sides of bowl and blend for 3 minutes on medium speed.
Dough will be thick.
Alternate layers of batter and apple slices.
Start and finish with batter using 3 layers of batter and two layers of apples.
Bake 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Cool on rack 10 minutes and then invert cake and remove pan.
Cool completely.
Make glaze with remaining ingredients.
Drizzle on cool cake.
Serve.

title: crunchy onion rings
