directions: Slightly beat egg whites with 2 tablespoon skim milk in a small bowl; set aside.
Mix seasoning into whole wheat flour in a small bowl; set aside.
Pour skim milk into a small bowl.
Pour bread crumbs into a small bowl.
Arrange bowls in the following order:
milk, flour, egg whites and bread crumbs.
Dip onion rings into bowls in the arranged order; lightly shake off the excess. Bake on a nonstick baking sheet at 375° until tender, about 15 minutes.
Cool slightly and serve.
Serves 8.

title: coffee punch
directions: Boil water; add sugar.
Turn off heat.
Add coffee.
Place lid on top and let steam.
Into a large container, put milk.
Add sugar and coffee mixture.
Add 1/2 gallon of vanilla ice cream. Later add another 1/2 gallon ice cream as needed.

title: heath bar cookies
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil; place crackers on foil. Over low heat, cook butter, oleo and sugars. Boil 3 minutes. Stir occasionally. Pour over crackers. Sprinkle chopped nuts over crackers. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Melt candy and drizzle over crackers. Chill and store in tin.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into unbaked frozen "Ritz" deep dish pie crusts.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix thawed peas with onion, eggs and cheese.
Add about 3/4 to 1 cup Miracle Whip (to make consistency you want).
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: yogurt popsicles
directions: You will need Tupperware popsicle molds.

title: frozen lemonade pie
directions: Mix sweetened milk and lemonade into Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crusts.
Refrigerate.

title: mary's cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Heat oil in skillet (black iron one if available).
Mix dry ingredients; add milk and egg.
Stir well. Pour in skillet and cook until brown, about 20 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco until creamy.
Add milk.
Mix well.
Add baking powder, vanilla and lemon.
Add eggs and flour alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° (preheat oven).

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs, fruit cocktail and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle over mixture in pan the brown sugar and pecans or coconut, or both. Bake at 350° until done.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Brown beef and onions, add salt, and pepper.
Spread into pie plate.
Beat milk, baking mix and egg until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake 25 minutes. Top with tomatoes and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes clean.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: marlys' lasagne
directions: Spray large cake pan with Pam.
Layer noodles, meat, sauces and cheeses 3 times.
Put cheeses on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until top is starting to lightly brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and form a loaf.
Place in shallow pan in 350° oven.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut the flour into Crisco.
In another bowl, add flour, sugar, salt and water; make into paste.
Add to flour and Crisco; knead well, then roll into crust or make crust for cobbler.
Makes 3 to 4 crusts.
Keeps good for several days in fridge.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; add potatoes, soup, salt and pepper. Pour into casserole.
Bake at 300° until done.
Yields 12 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Placed thawed potatoes in 9x13 baking dish.
Mix together next 6 ingredients and pour over potatoes.	Mix crushed cornflakes with 1/2 cup melted butter and drizzle over potatoes.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients in casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.
Add 2 cups chicken and 1/4 cup water to make a one-dish meal.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: crushed pineapple cake
directions: Mix according to directions on box in an oblong cake pan. When done, punch holes in cake and pour this topping over it.

title: boston cream pie cheesecake
directions: Grease bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Prepare cake mix as package directs; pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pecan delight
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix sugar and baking powder. Pour into egg whites.
Beat until stiff.
Mix cinnamon, pecans and Ritz crackers.
Pour into egg white mixture.
Stir until well mixed.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into well buttered pie pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool for 30 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate for 1 1/2 to 2 hours before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop beef fine.
Dice onions. Mix all ingredients except part of the beef.
Shape into ball.
Roll ball in rest of beef. Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: avocado dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve with chips or raw vegetables.

title: eggplant supreme
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil. Add eggplant, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add onion, garlic, basil, tarragon, mustard and tomato sauce.
Mix well and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: kahlua
directions: Combine 1 cup water and sugar in large saucepan.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Add 1 cup boiling water to the coffee.
When dissolved, mix into syrup.
Remove from heat.
Cool to lukewarm!
Stir in liquor and vanilla bean.
Pour into clean 1/2 gallon bottle.
Cap tightly.
Store at least 4 weeks before using, the longer, the better.
Serve over ice, with coffee or in cream.

title: dirt cake
directions: Put half crushed Oreos in bottom of pan.
With mixer, blend Cool Whip, cream cheese, sugar and margarine.
In bowl, combine pudding, milk and vanilla.
Beat this until consistency of pudding. Combine both mixtures and pour over layer of crusted Oreos. Sprinkle remaining Oreos on top.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: ray's mexicali meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, reserving 4 ounces tomato sauce for topping.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Bake, covered with remaining sauce, at 375° for 45 minutes until slightly brown on top.

title: hash brown #2
directions: Mix. Spread in greased cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Spread grated Cheddar cheese; dot with butter and 1 cup Corn Flake crumbs and bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: best in the world peanut brittle
directions: Place syrup, sugar and	water in iron skillet (size #8) and cook to soft
ball	stage
(230°).	Add raw peanuts.
Stir and cook these ingredients
on	medium-high to the crack stage (301° to 302°), stirring	constantly.
Turn off heat.
Stir in until well blended
margarine,
vanilla,	soda and salt.	This will want to foam
over.
Keep stirring fast until well blended.
Pour into large
platter
that is well buttered.
As soon as possible, start pulling over the edges of platter.	Work on Formica or
tile counter.
You can't pull this out thin until it reaches
the right temperature.	(If it's too hot, it will not be clear,
so just keep working with it.) You can make it as thin as you like, and break it into pieces.
Oh!
So good!

title: paximathia 2
directions: Beat eggs with oil; add sugar and beat well.
Add anise and then the baking powder and flour as needed.
Let the dough set for 1
hour.
Cut
dough
into	4 pieces.
Roll each piece into the shape
of a loaf.
Place on a cookie sheet for baking and bake
in 350° oven until golden brown.
Remove from oven. Slice into strips, 3/4-inch, and place pieces on side and bake once more until golden brown.

title: three day dream chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake as directed, using 2 round cake pans.
Cool cake; then use thread to slice each into two layers (making four thin layers).
Combine sour cream, sugar, coconut, and nuts.
Reserve cup of mixture.
Use the rest to frost between layers but not on top.
Mix one cup mixture with the Cool Whip and frost top and sides.
Sprinkle additional coconut and nuts if desired. After frosting, place cake inside Tupperware cake holder and refrigerate for three days.

title: magic meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Shape into a loaf. Place in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours (or on high for 4 to 6 hours).

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling water for five minutes; drain.
Blend together the carrots, cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Add squash and onions.

title: magic bar cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cracker crumbs and mix. Pat into bottom of pan.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate.
Mix all other ingredients until all are thoroughly mixed.
Spread on a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool. Cut into squares.
Freezes so well.
I do this for Christmas.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shells, 3 regular or 2 deep dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable bread
directions: Cut biscuits in fourths.
Crumble bacon.
Cook bell pepper and onion in butter.
Mix bacon, butter mixture and biscuits in bowl. Pour 1/2 mixture into ungreased Bundt pan; sprinkle with 1/2 cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix together cake mix, margarine and egg; pack into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix confectioners sugar, eggs and cream cheese; pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown; cut into squares.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugars, creaming until light.
Add eggs, beating well after each.
Sift together dry ingredients. Add alternately to creamed mixture with applesauce.
Stir in raisins and nuts.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream
butter and oil. Add sugars beating with electric mixer (2 minutes).
Add egg and vanilla.	Combine flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar. Add to creamed mixture, mixing well. Stir	in oats
and remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie
sheet.
Bake
at
375° for 10 minutes.
Cool. Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Combine water, oatmeal, vegetable oil, Karo syrup and salt. Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and mix well.
Blend in eggs.
Add flour and mix until dough is well blended.
Place dough in greased bowl and cover.
Store in refrigerator at least 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: If desired, use the juice drained from the pineapple as part of the 2 cups boiling water.
Dissolve gelatin in the boiling liquid. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a ring mold sprayed with nonstick spray. Chill until firm.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups water until water is gone or use 2 cups of drained cocktail instead of raisins.
Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and cooking oil.
Mix well.
Blend in baking soda and flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix.
Bake in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: *easter bread
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
In a large pot, place the other ingredients.
Mix all together and then knead for about 10 minutes until dough is elastic.
Dough will be on the wet side. Place in a warm place to rise until double in size.

Place dough into individual bread pans (spray with Pam) and let rise again. Before placing the pans in the oven, brush with beaten egg and if desired, sprinkle with sesame seed. Bake for about 40 minutes at 350° in 4 x 8-inch pans.
Makes 5 to 6 loaves.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Combine the biscuit mix and milk.
Crumble the raw sausage and cheese into the mixture.
Drop biscuits onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 16 minutes.
Makes about 1 dozen. Great for breakfast.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine the first 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then cook 20 minutes over low heat, stirring frequently.
In a bowl, beat egg yolk with 2 tablespoons milk and the pudding.
Add 2 more cups milk.
After you cook the rice mixture 20 minutes, add the pudding mixture slowly and cook until it thickens.
Add raisins when cooked, if you like.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar with margarine.
Add eggs and other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into well-greased and floured pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tallyho dressing
directions: Beat well with mixer or in blender.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine 1 1/2 tablespoons flour and salt.
Coat the meat with this.
In skillet melt 2 tablespoons of butter and brown the meat slowly on all sides.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Saute until onion is barely tender.

title: cowboy omelet
directions: Heat a medium-size skillet or omelet pan.
Add the bacon and saute slowly until the fat is rendered.
Turn up the heat and cook until the bacon begins to brown and crisp.
Add the onion and bell pepper; cook to soften and finish off the bacon.
Mix the tomato with the eggs, salt, pepper, cheese and picante sauce.
Pour into pan.
Cook until lightly browned on the underside.
Place under a preheated broiler and cook the top quickly until brown and puffy. Cut
into wedges and serve immediately.
Serves 2.

title: refrigerator sweet pickles
directions: Thoroughly wash and slice unpeeled cucumbers.
Place cucumbers, onion and peppers in a gallon container.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl; stir until sugar is dissolved.
This syrup needs no cooking.
Pour over the sliced cucumbers.
Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.
The pickles are ready to eat.
These are not for canning.
Chopped dill may be added for a dill flavor, but omit the seed.

title: double cheese delight
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
Brown hamburger, stirring until crumbly.
Add onion and celery; continue cooking until vegetables are tender.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and salt.
Bring to boil; simmer for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream and noodles. Pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Slice tomato garnish on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper well.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Place bread, bacon and cheese in casserole. Pour milk and egg mixture evenly over bread.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 8 hours.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 1 hour.

title: sugar plum pudding
directions: Sift dry ingredients in order given; stir in all other ingredients in order given.
Pour batter into 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: quick and easy punch
directions: In a punch bowl, mix softened sherbet (1 gallon), 1 large can pineapple juice and 2 bottles ginger ale.
Break up the sherbet just a bit.
Ready to serve.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Cream egg yolks.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add whiskey to egg
mixture.
Add whipped cream or Cool Whip to egg yolk mixture.
Last,
fold
in
the
stiffly beaten egg whites.
(Instead of whipped
cream,
I use a large Cool Whip. This is easier and better tasting.)

title: cheese and apple spread
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and salad dressing, mixing until well blended.
Add cheese and chopped apples; mix well.
Chill. Serve with apple wedges, crackers or party rye bread slices.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: angel frost punch
directions: Combine berries, lemonade, water and ice cream in punch bowl until thick and smooth.

title: lemon cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water and vegetable oil and beat at medium speed about 3 minutes.
Bake in well-greased Bundt pan in 350° preheated oven until done.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine mayo, lemon juice and soy sauce to make sauce; set aside.
Prepare remaining ingredients and mix in large bowl.
Stir in sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate.
Serve over lettuce leaf.

title: frozen monkey bread
directions: Place the pecans in the bottom of a greased tube or Bundt pan. Scatter the frozen rolls in the pan.
Sprinkle the dry pudding mix over the rolls.
Melt butter and add brown sugar.
Blend well and add milk.
Mix well and pour over frozen rolls and pudding mix.
Cover and let rise at room temperature for 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° on bottom rack of oven for 25 minutes or until done.
Butter top after removing from oven.
Invert pan onto serving plate immediately, serve warm.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage and steam until tender.
Salt and pepper.
Grease a baking dish and place layer of cabbage and layer of
Cheddar cheese.
Add soup with milk and butter, melted.
Sprinkle stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Combine cucumbers and onion.
Stir together remaining ingredients.
Mix together with vegetables.
Cover and chill. Stir occasionally.
Makes 3 cups.

title: pierre's cake
directions: With a mixer, beat butter; beat in powdered sugar.
Beat in eggs and flour.
Add flavoring and beat 2 minutes.
Pour in a greased, floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 345° for 1 hour.
Glaze if desired.

title: ritz pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar.
Crush crackers; add baking powder and nuts.
Add to egg whites.
Pour into buttered pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes; cool and top with peaches and whipped cream.

title: kathy's five minute rehab luncheon pea and peanut salad
directions: Thaw peas by rinsing in cold tap water.
Drain peas.
Mix in a bowl the peas, chopped red onion and full can of Spanish peanuts with mayonnaise.
Serve.

title: the next best thing to robert redford
directions: Mix together by hand: flour, sugar, butter and chopped pecans. Press into a 9 x 13-inch cake dish (bottom and sides).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Mix together powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip and spread mixture on cooled crust.
Mix together pudding mix and milk and pour on cheese layer.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with pecans.

title: vanishing oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat Oleo and sugars until creamy, add eggs and vanilla. Mix all dry ingredients well in separate bowl. Add wet ingredients to dry, mix well. Drop by Tablespoons on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10-12 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften the cream cheesecake in a mixing bowl.
Add the powdered sugar, vanilla flavor, Cool Whip and peanut butter.
Mix all the ingredients together in a bowl.
Mix until smooth.
Put into a graham cracker pie crust that has been baked.
Use peanut butter morsels on top of the pie for decoration.
Place the morsels like buttons over top of pie while soft.
Put your pan in the fridge. Let it freeze.
Take pie out a short time before you are going to serve it.
You can take one piece out if that is all you want at that time.
Put back.
Keep it frozen.
Eat later.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in colander and run hot water over it for a few minutes.
Put broccoli in casserole dish.
Place onion on top of broccoli.
Top with soup and milk (best if mixed together first). Top with cheese.
Melt butter and pour into cracker crumbs.
Stir until all crumbs are coated, then pour on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast sausage bread
directions: Allow dough to rise until nearly doubled.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Add liquid.
Add dry ingredients alternately with bananas.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in loaf pan 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: rachel's brownies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.
Cream eggs and sugar together.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt.
Gradually add to egg and sugar mixture.
Blend in butter and vanilla.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan 30 to 35 minutes

title: cheese wafers
directions: Have cheese and butter at room temperature.
Mix and add combined remaining ingredients.
Roll in long roll.
Chill overnight.
Slice in wafers.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° (better if they do not brown).
Use as an appetizer snack or like a cookie.

title: sausage balls
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Brown sausage and drain.
Mix salt, baking powder and flour.
With pastry cutter, cut in margarine.
Stir in milk, sausage and cheese.
Shape into bite size balls.
Bake until light brown, 25 minutes.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, sugars and pudding mix in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs; gradually add flour mixture, then stir in chips and nuts (batter will be stiff).
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased baking sheets 2 inches apart.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 7 dozen.

title: brownie mud puddle cake
directions: Microwave chocolate and butter in large microwavable bowl on High 2 minutes or until butter is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir in sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and stir until well blended.
Spread into greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out with fudgy crumbs.
Do not overbake. Cool in pan on a wire rack.
Add milk to pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk for 2 minutes or until well blended; spread over brownie, leaving a 1-inch border around the edge.
Sprinkle with crushed cookies to resemble dirt.
Cut into 16 wedges to serve.

title: nut macaroon squares
directions: Mix together butter and 1/2 cup brown sugar; press into an 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients together thoroughly.
Spread over baked layer.
Return to oven to bake 1/2 hour or until lightly browned.

title: connie's fudge
directions: In heavy pan, put sugar, butter and margarine.
Bring mixture to a rolling boil and let boil 6 minutes.
Pour over remaining ingredients, mixed.
Stir and stir until all is well melted and mixed.
Pour into pans to set.
Makes about 4 pounds.

title: rice krispies squares
directions: Melt margarine in 3-quart saucepan.
Add marshmallows and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until marshmallows are melted and mixture is syrupy.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies cereal and stir until well coated.
Press warm mixture evenly and firmly into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.
Yields 24 (2 x 2-inch) treats.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together in blender and pour into greased pie plate.
Bake in oven at 350° until firm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cut green onions with
some tops.
Shred dried beef and mix with cream	cheese.
Add
garlic
salt
and Worcestershire sauce. Mix together and form a ball.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: tuppence's stuffies (stuffed quahogs)
directions: Melt oleo, add onion, parsley, and clams with juice.
Add bread crumbs to a consistency that is slightly mushy, as it becomes drier when it's reheated.
Can be reheated in microwave, small double boiler, or oven in quahog
shells - whatever. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: homemade goulash
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add to remaining ingredients. Simmer approximately 2 hours.
Delicious on a cold night.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed above.
Drop onto cookie sheet by tablespoon or ice cream scoop.
Flatten.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook to boil, but don't overcook (large crock-pot works best). Serve
with tortilla chips or crackers.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Season with picante, if desired.

title: no-fat strawberry shortcake
directions: Make the following layers:
cake, Cool Whip, cake, yogurt, cake, nuts, cake, pineapple and top with strawberries.

title: poppy seed dressing for fruit salad
directions: Put all ingredients except oil in a deep mixer bowl.
As you run the mixer on medium speed, slowly add salad oil.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with low salt Triscuits crackers.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Combine sugar, water and cream of tartar.
Cover and boil 5 minutes.
Uncover, wipe sides of saucepan with a damp cloth.
Boil without stirring to firm ball stage (245° to 248°).
Pour slowly, stirring constantly, over stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add flavoring.
Continue beating until candy holds its shape when dropped from a spoon.
Drop teaspoonful onto waxed paper. Sprinkle with nuts.

title: cheese loafers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into small roll.
Keep in refrigerator overnight. Slice thin and bake in a 350° oven for a few minutes.

title: grape ice cream
directions: Mix grape juice, sugar, lemon juice and water.
Let stand until sugar is dissolved.
Add cream and mix.
Pour into freezer container and freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: lazy cabbage rolls
directions: Saute meat until browned.
Drain off fat.
Add onion soup mix and rice to meat.
Stir well.
Put cabbage in large casserole dish.
Add salt and pepper.
Spread meat mixture over cabbage. Mix water and tomato soup together and pour over the meat and cabbage.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until cabbage is tender.

title: appleless pie
directions: Bring water, sugar and cream of tartar to a boil in saucepan. Add crackers; boil 2 minutes more.
Pour into pie crust; sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: microwave tuna-noodle dish
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Put cooked noodles in bottom of ovenproof dish.
Put tuna on top of noodles. Add grated cheese on top.
Cook in microwave for 3 to 5 minutes (until cheese is melted) on High.

title: pepper steak with port mushroom sauce
directions: Prepare the Port Mushroom Sauce; set aside and keep warm. Combine mushrooms and flour in a bowl; toss. Combine the wine, shallots and balsamic vinegar in a medium skillet. Bring to boil; cook until thick (about 3 minutes). Reduce heat to medium. Add broth, Worcestershire sauce, tomato paste and rosemary; cook 1 minute. Add mushroom mixture; cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Stir in mustard. Yield: 1 cup.

title: italian ziti with broccoli
directions: Cook ziti; drain.
Cook broccoli; drain.
Combine; let cool. Saute garlic pieces in olive oil; add to mixture.
Serve with Italian sausage or smoked sausage and a salad.

title: peanut butter chocolate squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate.
Melt chocolate chips in microwave.
Spread over mixture.
Chill.

title: homemade ice cream and sauce
directions: Combine condensed milk with water, beaten egg yolks and vanilla.
Fold in heavy cream that has been whipped until fluffy. Pour the mixture into a 2-quart foil-lined container (such as a loaf pan).
Cover pan with foil or plastic wrap and freeze for 6 hours or until firm.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and granulated sugar.
Blend in one egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Measure sifted flour. Stir flour, baking powder and salt into oil mixture.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Drop teaspoonful of dough into powdered sugar.
Roll in sugar and shape into balls. Place about 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: terri's chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion and pecans in butter until onion is tender. Combine cream cheese, 1 Tbsp. milk, salt and cumin.
Add nut mixture and chicken.
Stir until well combined.

Spoon about 1/3 c. chicken mixture onto each tortilla (near the edge) and roll up. Place filled tortilla (seam side down) in greased baking dish. In another bowl, combine soup, sour cream, 1 c. milk, and jalapenos. Pour over enchiladas. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with cheese, and bake until cheese melts.
Makes 6.

title: mock cabbage roll casserole
directions: *If I have ground pork, I decrease the beef by 1/2 pound and use 1/2 pound ground pork.

title: cheese cake - no bake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, oleo and powdered sugar.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan (up sides).
Save some for top.
Dissolve and cool over cold water, Jell-O and hot water.
Cream the cheese, sugar and vanilla; cream together with fork.
Chill evaporated milk, beaters and bowl.
Whip until stiff (approximately 5 to 7 minutes).
Add Jell-O , then cream cheese; blend.
Pour into crust.
Top with reserved crumb mixture.
Store in refrigerator 12 hours or more.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel apples and remove core; slice apples in thin slices and put in lightly greased round pie pan.
In a bowl, mix oats, sugar and flour.
Add butter or margarine and stir until you have a crumbly mixture.
Pour mixture on apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: two crust pastry
directions: Mix flour and salt together.
Cut shortening in with fork until crumbly.
Add cold water.

title: spicy chiffon cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice and cloves in big bowl.
Make a well and add oil, egg yolks and cold water.
Beat with spoon until smooth.
Measure egg whites and cream of tartar into large bowl, whip until it forms stiff peaks.
Pour egg yolk mixture gradually over whipped egg whites, gently folding with spoon until blended.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cool before icing.

title: mixed nut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, water and Karo syrup to 280° on a candy thermometer.
Add other ingredients and boil to 300°.

title: baked beans and cheese spaghetti
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put bacon on top.
Put in buttered casserole and bake at 350° until it is browned.
You may cook ground beef with the onion.

title: hard candy
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients together in a large heavy saucepan. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.

Boil, without stirring, until temperature reaches 310° on thermometer or until drops of syrup form hard and brittle threads in cold water. Remove from heat. Stir in the desired flavoring and food coloring if desired.
Pour onto foil covered pan (about 18 x 24-inches) that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar. Cool thoroughly. Break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: flawless fudge
directions: Heat milk and chocolate over low heat until chocolate is melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, salt and nuts. Chill in buttered 8 x 4-inch pan. Cut into squares.

title: peach-pecan pie
directions: In saucepan combine the 1 1/2 cups sugar, corn starch, cinnamon and stir in water.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add peaches, return to boiling.
Cover and keep warm over very low heat.

title: upside down meat pie
directions: Melt shortening in 10 inch skillet; add onion and ground beef and brown lightly. Add tomato sauce, salt, chili powder, and pepper; mix thoroughly; simmer while preparing cornbread batter. Slice green pepper into 7 rings. Turn meat out of skillet; place pepper rings around edge of skillet with one in the middle. Spoon meat back over rings; pour cornbread batter over meat. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all together and store in refrigerator.

title: cheesy chive stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to broil.
Clean mushrooms; discard stems.
Fill mushroom caps with whipped cream cheese.
Place on cookie sheet. Broil 5 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: cheese "n" cream potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease 1 1/2-quart round casserole. Cover potatoes with boiling water in small bowl. Let stand uncovered 10 minutes; drain thoroughly. Beat milk and eggs with hand beater. Mix all ingredients in casserole. Bake, uncovered, until potatoes are tender and top is golden brown, 45 to 50 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and blend for 1 minute. Makes 5 1/2 cups.
May be frozen.

title: play dough for kids
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan until well blended.
Cook over medium heat for 4 minutes, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens to mashed potato thickness.
Cover with damp cloth to cool.
Knead as you would dough.
Do not eat.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions and place in greased casserole.
Mix other ingredients (except crumbs) and pour over the broccoli. Top with cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix and put in casserole, cover with Ritz Cracker crumbs.
Heat until bubbly.
Don't overcook as it is best if celery is still crisp.
Serves 6.

title: tostada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger. Add 1 1/2 cups tomato sauce and taco seasoning. Mix, stirring well. Put 2 cups corn chips in bottom of pan. Spoon meat mixture over this. Combine remaining tomato sauce with refried beans. Spread over meat mixture. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and remaining corn chips. Bake 5 more minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Put butter and cream cheese in a mixing bowl.
Let it soften, then blend until creamy.
Add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time, until real fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix real good, then add flour, 1/4 cup at a time, and blend on low until you have used all the flour.
Stir in vanilla.
Put in 10-inch tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine eggs, sugar, corn syrup, butter and vanilla.
Fold in chocolate morsels and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes, or until set.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and remove and add onion and pepper. Add remaining ingredients and bacon.
Bake in a greased casserole in oven at 350°, about 30 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add beaten eggs and oil, stirring with a large spoon until moist.
(Do not beat.)
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, bananas and 1 cup of nuts. Spoon into 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes, then remove.
Cool completely before icing.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease cookie sheets. In medium bowl, combine all ingredients. Roll generous teaspoonful of dough in hands to make ball. Place on baking sheet. Bake for 35 minutes. Remove and cool on wire racks. When cool, roll in powdered sugar. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Melt 2/3 cup butter and stir together with graham cracker crumbs.
Press into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and dry orange jello.
Mix well and add cottage cheese, oranges and pineapple.
Chill for 3 hours.
Also can use miniature marshmallows if prefer (about 1 cup).

title: cowboy stew
directions: Combine and simmer on stove or in crock-pot.
Serve with grated cheese, optional.

title: bread boas
directions: Divide the dough into 6 pieces.
Dip each in flour.
Roll each piece into a snake.
Add raisins for eyes.
Melt the margarine. Color half the margarine red and half green.
Use it to paint the snakes like boas.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken, then remove bone.
Save some broth to use in salad.
Chill chicken, onion, pickle and eggs; then grind in a sausage grinder.
Add salt, pepper, celery seed and mayonnaise along with some broth.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2-quarts.

title: frosty lemonade pie
directions: Combine crushed cereal, brown sugar and butter; mix thoroughly.
Reserve 1/4 cup crumb mixture for garnish.
Press remaining mixture firmly into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool, then freeze.
Allow lemonade concentrate and ice cream to thaw just enough to mix easily.
Spread in pie shell and garnish with reserved crumbs and lemon slices.
Return to freezer; keep frozen until serving.

title: chef salad(for one)
directions: Combine all ingredients and top with 2 tablespoons nonfat salad dressing.
A very filling meal with less than 300 calories!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli in water for 8 minutes, or until tender.
Drain broccoli, reserving the salt water.
Layer broccoli in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cut up cream cheese into salted water; melt over low heat.
Pour over the broccoli.
Top with grated cheese. Mix melted butter and Ritz cracker crumbs; stir until well coated. Sprinkle over broccoli and cheese mixture.
Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oven "fried" potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel potatoes and cut into thin strips. In medium bowl combine potato strips, oil and salt and pepper. Toss so that oil is thoroughly coating potatoes.
On nonstick baking sheet arrange potatoes, leaving space between strips.
Bake 20 minutes, turn potatoes over with a spatula and bake until brown and crisp, about 20 minutes more.

title: bread pudding(new orleans style)
directions: Soak French bread in milk; crush it and beat eggs in separate bowl.
Add sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Put butter in 3-quart pan.
Add egg mixture to bread and milk; blend until bread is completely soaked.
Pour in baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until brown.
Let cool.

title: cherry squares
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Mix and press down a layer of oatmeal mixture in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread filling and top with remaining oatmeal.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until brown.

title: fried rice
directions: Beat egg whites and yolk together.
In a small skillet, scramble eggs in 1 tablespoon of the olive oil.
Set aside.
In a large skillet, saute green onions in the remaining teaspoon oil. Add rice and mix thoroughly.
Stir in soy sauce and sugar.
Stir in eggs and meat.
Total cal. 167.
Sat. fat cal. 6.

title: filled chocolate sandwich cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all cookie ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 13 minutes or until set.
Cool completely.

title: coconut icebox cake
directions: Heat milk and add egg yolks and plain flour.
Cook milk, egg yolks, sugar, flour and salt together until mixture coats spoon over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup water and add to other mixture and cool.
Beat egg whites until very stiff and add to cooled custard mixture the whipping cream (whipped and sweetened) and coconut.
Use a Pyrex dish about 9 x 13-inch.
Sprinkle a layer of broken bits of angel food cake over the bottom of the Pyrex dish, then pour over this a layer of the custard mixture, then another layer of cake and another layer of custard.
Now add thick layer of coconut and last, garnish with whipped cream.
Sprinkle more coconut over whipped cream and refrigerate.
This may be served in about 2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, salt, pickles and pecans.
Moisten well with mayonnaise.
Makes 8 servings.

title: popcorn balls
directions: In a saucepan, mix syrup and sugar.
Cook on medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until smooth.
Pour over popcorn.
Mix until well coated.

title: filled cupcakes
directions: Mix chocolate cake according to box, then set aside.
Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix cream cheese, egg and sugar until creamy, then add chocolate chips, coconut and vanilla to cream cheese mixture.
Fill cupcake pans with liners.
Pour cake mixture half full and add 1 tablespoon cream cheese mixture to batter.
Bake at 350° until done.
Let cool and ice.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup juice.
Cut pineapple in quarters; set aside.
Coat chicken with flour and salt.
In skillet over medium heat in hot oil, cook chicken until golden and fork-tender, about 15 minutes, turning once.
Remove chicken; keep warm.
In drippings, stir honey, teriyaki sauce, dried chives, pepper and 1/4 cup juice.
Over high heat, bring to boil and boil for 30 seconds.
Add pineapple; heat through.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Delicious served over wild rice!

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, sugar, egg, vanilla and almond extract. Blend in flour and baking soda.
Cover; chill 2 to 3 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each half 1/4-inch thick and cut into desired shapes.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes or until light brown around edges.
Yields approximately 4 dozen, 2 to 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Make icing first so it can cool while other preparation is made.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and butter together.
Pour over Rice Chex in large pan.
Stir and mix well.
Dust with powdered sugar in large sack.
Shake until coated.
Serve.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put all ingredients in a large plastic bag and close bag and shake until all potatoes are evenly coated. Put potatoes in baking pan.
Bake for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally, and cook until tender and golden brown.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Melt butter and stir in brown sugar while still on the stove. Cool and add remaining ingredients. Bake in a greased 10 x 7-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: upside-down rhubarb cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Spread rhubarb in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and then with the 3/4 cup sugar.

Cream butter and 1 cup sugar until fluffy; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and vanilla.
Batter will be very thick.
Spread on rhubarb mixture.

title: up and down biscuits
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add milk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly 4 or 5 times.
Roll dough to a 20 x 10-inch rectangle 1/4-inch thick.
Brush on melted butter. Combine 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over dough.
Cut lengthwise into five 2-inch strips.
Stack strips, cinnamon side up, on top of each other.
Cut stacks into 2-inch sections.
Place each stacked section, cut side down, into lightly greased muffin pans.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Yields 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: mystery crackers
directions: Put crackers into
an airtight plastic container.
Pour oil over crackers.
Stir
gently
with wooden spoon.
Sprinkle both packets of soup mix
over crackers and stir well.
Do not refrigerate.
Stir before
serving.
"Everyone will wonder how you made these."

title: lola causey's washboard cookies
directions: Mix eggs and sugar together.
Add shortening.
Add soda in hot water; mix well.
Add vanilla and flour.
Roll in small balls. Press with fork across both ways.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Drain pineapple chunks, reserving juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 1/4 cups liquid.
In 2-quart casserole, thoroughly combine brown sugar, cornstarch and ginger.
Stir in soy sauce, vinegar and pineapple juice.
Microwave, uncovered, on Full power for 4 to 5 minutes or until mixture boils and thickens, stirring 3 times.
Stir in chicken, green pepper and pineapple.
Microwave, covered, on Full power for 5 to 6 minutes or until well heated, stirring once or twice.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Serves 4. Serve over rice.

title: microwave potato casserole
directions: Layer potatoes, ham, broccoli and mushrooms in casserole.
Mix soup with milk and pour over casserole.
Top with cheeses.
Cook in microwave until potatoes are soft to touch, approximately 20 minutes.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper (or seasoning salt); brown in fat.
Remove chops to casserole; saute onion and green pepper in fat.
Add rice to casserole; pour in consomme and water.
Place onion and green pepper on top of chops.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until rice absorbs all liquid in a covered dish.

title: crown beef bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix beef, mushrooms and 2/3 can onions. Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Heat mushroom soup and stir in 1/2 cup sour cream.
Pour over casserole and stir.
Cut biscuits in half and arrange flat cut side down around edge of casserole. Sprinkle remaining onions on top of casserole.
Mix 1/2 cup sour cream and egg.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes until golden.

title: german sweet chocolate cream cheese brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce and place in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Layer next 5 ingredients.
Add sugar to mayonnaise.
Spread mixture over top as you would frosting.
Top with grated cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.
Mix just prior to serving.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating lightly after each addition.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add flour alternately with milk; begin and end with flour.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Pour into tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mash softened cream cheese and Blue cheese until smooth.
Add milk and onion and mix thoroughly.
Using wax paper, roll cheese into a ball, then roll in pecans until completely covered.
It's easier to shape the cheese ball after covered with nuts.
Chill.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix meats.
Stir in next 7 ingredients.
Soak bread in milk; add eggs.
Beat with rotary beater.
Combine meat and egg mix. Form 2 loaves.
Roll in bread crumbs and place on greased pan. Spread 1/2 cup of chili sauce over each loaf.
Pour 1/2 cup boiling water around loaves.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chile con carne
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight.
Drain and cover with cold water.
Bring to a boil. Boil 5 minutes. Drain. Cover with cold water. Add salt and cook until beans are tender.
Pour 1/2 water off.
Mince garlic and stir through beans.
Saute onions
in ground beef suet until soft and limp. Add meat to onions and cook until meat is brown. Add onions and meat to beans. Stir together. Add tomato juice, chili powder and cayenne. Bring to a boil.
Let boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add more salt, chili powder and cayenne to taste, if desired.
Let chile stand to bring out flavor.

title: clams oreganata
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil.
Add onion, parsley, oregano and breadcrumbs.
Brown slightly.
Add clams and juice.
Spoon into seashell baking foils or dishes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: polish soup
directions: Put chuck in water with celery leaves, salt, pepper and tomato soup.
Simmer at a low boil until beef falls apart.
In each soup bowl, put a large spoonful of rice and ladle soup over it.

title: pralines
directions: Have ready baking sheet covered with waxed paper.
In a large saucepan, cook all ingredients to rolling boil.
Let boil 30 to 40 seconds.
Remove from heat and start beating.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: baked spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and pepper in butter until meat is done.
Add tomato soup, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter delights
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and both sugars together.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture to make a dough.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into walnut size balls and place in ungreased 1 1/2-inch muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Immediately after removing cookies from oven, press a miniature peanut butter cup into the center, until only the top of peanut butter cup shows.
Let cool for 10 minutes.
Remove cookies from muffin tins.
Store in airtight containers.
Makes about 38 cookies.

title: grits spoon bread
directions: Melt margarine in 1-quart casserole.
Add grits to boiling water in saucepan.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally; remove from heat.
Add melted margarine, dry milk powder, eggs, sugar and salt.
Beat for 1 minute.
Pour into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended. Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Top with fruit.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Stir all ingredients together until mixed well.
Cover and chill.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: house shrimp dip
directions: If shrimp are frozen, thaw.
Chop coarsely.
(Hold several shrimp for garnish.)
In a small bowl, combine all ingredients. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Makes 3 cups dip.

title: yeast bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, eggs, shortening and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Gradually mix in the remaining flour until smooth.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
(The dough is ready if indentation remains when touched.)

title: hurry up casserole
directions: Cut luncheon meat into strips; saute meat and onions in margarine in skillet.
Simmer until onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer covered until heated through. Garnish with sliced, hard-boiled egg and additional parsley, if desired.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Simmer ground meat, garlic clove, tomato sauce, salt, and pepper for 20 minutes.
Beat in mixer the following:
sour cream and cream cheese.
Add the egg noodles, which have been cooked and coated with butter.
Stir in 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Put all in casserole and heat thoroughly.

title: magic pumpkin pie
directions: In
large size mixing bowl, blend together all ingredients. Turn
mixture into pie shell.
Bake in 375° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: one egg cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add whole egg; beat thoroughly, then add flour, which has been sifted with baking powder several times. Gradually add milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in buttered cake tins at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat well eggs, sugar, flour, vanilla and pudding.
Add half and half and whipping cream.
Fill with milk to fill line on ice cream maker.
Follow ice cream maker directions.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Prepare unbaked pie shell.
Cream butter and sugar together with mixer.
Add flour and eggs; beat well.
Stir in buttermilk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Bake on lower rack of oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Place on wire rack and let cool completely before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Take a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Layer nacho chips in bottom.
Take the bones out of your boiled chicken.
Spread the chicken over your chips.
Mix cream of celery soup, mushroom soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Spread soup mixture over chips and chicken. Place slices of cheese over top to cover.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts and inside is bubbly.
You can also make this with ground beef that has been browned and the fat drained off.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Wash spinach well.
Toss all together.
Serve with Strawberry Vinaigrette Dressing.

title: pineapple carrots
directions: Cut carrots into strips.
Heat 1 inch of salted water to boiling.
Add carrots; cover and cook until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes. Drain.
Heat butter in skillet until melted.
Add carrots, brown sugar and salt.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Stir in pineapple chunks.
Heat until pineapple is hot. Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream and water.
Makes 6 servings.

title: japanese fruit cake pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly. Add other ingredients and pour into uncooked pie shells. Bake at 300° for 50-55 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Boil 1 cup water with onion and margarine.
Add frozen broccoli.
Bring to boil.
Add Minute rice.
Cover and take off burner.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz. Mix.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: ugly cookie bars
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar. Mix well. Add slowly Bisquick and vanilla. Mix into the ingredients the pecans, coconut and chocolate chips. Pour into a greased and floured 12 x 14 or 9 1/2 x 14 3/4 pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Check for doneness. The secret is not to cook too fast.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Put oil, basil, garlic and nuts in blender or food processor. Pour in bowl and add cheese.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: hamburger macaroni casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix ground beef with cooked macaroni.
Add soups and mix well.
Layer mixture, cheese, onion. Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix all ingredients together and put into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in boiler and mix well.
Add milk. Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves, then bring to a boil. Stir occasionally until small amount in cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Beat and add nuts until thick.
Pour on buttered platter.

title: lynn's macaroni
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and milk.
Add macaroni, salt and pepper to taste and cheese chunks.
Cook until cheese bubbles and browns, about one hour at 350°, preheated.

title: thanksgiving salad
directions: Dissolve Jello and sugar in the hot water.
Add juice and cool.
Grind cranberries, oranges with the skin and apples, cored, with the skin.
Add to above mixture
Add nut meats.
Place in mold and cool until set.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour melted margarine in mixing bowl.
Mix soup, milk and mayonnaise.
Put a layer of crushed cornflakes in baking dish.
Spread cabbage on top of cornflakes.
Add melted margarine to soup, milk and mayonnaise mixture.
Mix well and pour over cabbage.
Sprinkle a layer of grated cheese on top of cabbage mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: spicy oven barbecued chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side up, in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, until thickest pieces are done, about 30 minutes longer.

title: lo-cal strawberry nut salad
directions: In large bowl, combine gelatin with boiling water, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Then fold in, all at once, strawberries, pineapple with juice, bananas and nuts.
Turn half of strawberry mixture into 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish as first layer.
Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Mix these ingredients well and pour into buttered pan. Sprinkle brown sugar, cocoa and hot water over batter.
(This makes the sauce.)
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve with ice cream. Put this in the oven right before serving dinner and it will be ready for dessert.

title: caramel apples
directions: Place caramels, water and salt into top of double boiler over boiling water until caramels are melted and mixture is smooth, about 10 minutes.
Stick wooden skewer in the top where stem should be.
Dip apples in caramel.
Sprinkle with nuts if desired. Set aside on wax paper-lined cookie sheet.
If caramel should become stiff, add a few drops of water.
Chill until caramel coating is firm.

title: kabob appetizers
directions: Thread pineapple chunks, strawberries, cheese, ham and turkey onto 4-inch skewers.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Blend well.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well a 1 1/2-quart round casserole.
In large bowl with fork, mix flour and next 4 ingredients.
With pastry blender, cut in margarine or butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
In cup with fork, beat eggs slightly.
Remove 1 tablespoon and reserve.
Stir butter, milk and remaining egg into flour mixture just until flour is moistened (dough will be sticky).
Turn dough into well-floured surface; with floured hands, knead about 10 strokes to mix thoroughly.
Shape dough into a ball; place in casserole.
In center of ball, with sharp knife, cut a 4-inch cross about 1/4-inch deep.
Brush dough with reserved egg.
Bake bread 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of loaf comes out clean.
Cool in casserole on wire rack for 10 minutes. Remove from casserole and cool completely on wire rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: etta carter's date drop cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, soda, salt and vanilla. Sift a little flour over dates and nuts to separate them.
Add the flour to the first mixture, then add dates and nuts to mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto oiled cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: lazy man's beef stew
directions: Grease a large casserole dish.
Add beef, carrots, tomato soup, bay leaf, potatoes, 1/2 cup wine and onions.
Cover and bake at 275° for 4 hours.
Remove form oven and stir.
(Meat will be a little dry.)
Add frozen peas, remaining 1/2 cup wine and mushrooms (optional).
If necessary, add a little water.
Cook for one hour longer.
Serves 6.

title: green beans - swiss style
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, sugar and onion. Add sour cream gradually, stirring constantly, until thickened. Fold in green beans.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Grate cheese and sprinkle over beans.
Crush corn flakes into fine crumbs.
Mix with melted butter and sprinkle over cheese.
Bake in 400°
oven for about 20 minutes.

title: coconut raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan. Toss raisins in the flour. Add sugar and baking powder, then mix.
Add coconut, vanilla extract, almond extract, egg, milk and water.
Mix by hand until blended.
Pour into loaf pan and bake for approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: pear preserves
directions: Wash fresh, good ripe peaches; drain.
Remove seed and put peaches through a grinder or food processor.

title: dill pickles
directions: Combine all ingredients, except dill and garlic clove.
Bring to boil.
Pour over cucumbers and process for 10 or 12 minutes.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together, then add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in a 375° oven for approximately 10 minutes.

title: banana loaf cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together in small bowl bananas, applesauce, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Combine all dry ingredients in large bowl; add banana mixture.
Stir until combined.
Pour batter into a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool on rack in pan for 5 minutes before removing.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and set aside.
Mix dry ingredients and blend in moist ingredients.
Pour in greased Bundt pan in layers starting with batter and ending with batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bones.
Melt butter and mix into dressing mix.
Layer:
chicken, dressing mixture, can of cream of mushroom soup and can of broth.
Repeat, using cream of chicken soup instead of the mushrooms.
Top with remainder of buttered dressing mixture.
Bake, uncovered.
(One canister Stove Top stuffing mix may be used in place of Pepperidge Farm mix.)
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple syrup.
Stir to dissolve.
Chill until partly set.
Add remaining ingredients and chill until firm.

title: golden meatball casserole
directions: Mix meat and onions and form into small meatballs and cook well.
Drain off fat.
In the same skillet, add 1 cup long grain rice, water, bell pepper and carrots.
Cover and cook for 25 minutes and add cubed cheese and simmer 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: baked marinated chicken breast
directions: Marinate chicken at least 2 hours or overnight if possible in a covered container, turning occasionally.
Reserve marinade; place chicken, skin side down, on unheated rack of broiler pan. Brush with marinade.
Bake 4 to 5 inches from heat for 20 minutes, brushing often with marinade.
Turn chicken; marinate again and broil 20 minutes more, or until done.

title: chicken fantastic
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Garnish with fresh parsley, grated cheese or paprika. Serves 12.

title: fiber rich bread
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 cups flour and the remaining dry ingredients and mix together well.
In saucepan, heat water, molasses and butter to 120° to 130°.
Butter may not be melted. Add to dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour, until dough is soft, but not sticky.
Knead, let rise in greased bowl.
Punch down.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 350°.

title: icicle pickles(14 day icicle pickles in one hour)
directions: Wash pickles and dry.
Cut pickles into chunks.
Heat sugar, vinegar, and spice.
Bring to a boil and pour over pickles. Refrigerate or can in jars.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and pie filling together in medium-size bowl; add pecans.
Drain pineapple and add to other ingredients. Mix in 8 ounces Cool Whip and stir together.
Chill overnight, if possible, before serving.
For best results, must be chilled before serving.

title: country corn muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease 12-muffin pan. In medium bowl, mix together flour, cornmeal, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar.
In another bowl, combine oil, eggs, milk and creamed corn.
Add to flour mixture and stir.
Add raisins.
Pour into pan filling 2/3 full.
Bake about 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crockpot swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces; season with salt and pepper and place in slow cooker with onion slices. Pour tomatoes over steak and onions. Cover and cook on LOW for 8-10 hours

title: weight watchers hot cocoa
directions: Per serving:
98 calories and 1 gram fat.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil and bone chicken.
Save water chicken was boiled in to boil the spaghetti.
Saute bell peppers in margarine.
Put everything together except the Cheddar cheese.
Mix well.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes, after topping with Cheddar cheese.

title: classic baked pasta
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients with exception of 2 cups cheese.
Bake, covered, for 35 minutes.
Uncover and add remaining cheese on top.
Cook an additional 10 minutes or until brown and bubbling.

title: apple pecan cake
directions: Blend shortening
and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, milk and lemon extract.
Sift
in flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Blend chopped
apples
to the mixture and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle
with
sugar
and pecans.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except blueberries, until smooth with mixer. Blend in berries with spoon. Bake at 325° for an hour.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Heat oil in soup pot.
Add onion, celery and garlic and cook until soft, about 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except macaroni.
Simmer, covered, for 25 minutes.
Add macaroni and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve hot.
Makes six 1-cup servings.

title: hanky-pankies
directions: Cook sausage and hamburger, mashing to make crumbly.
Drain. Add cheese and cook over low temperature until cheese is melted. Add spices.
Let mixture thicken.
Spread on rye bread.
Place in oven and heat through at 400° for 5 minutes.

title: irish bread(with buttermilk or sour cream)
directions: *Use green citron for St. Pat's.
Use red or green for Christmas.

title: chicken pie
directions: In bottom pie crust (unbaked) sprinkle flour.
Add chicken, salt and pepper.
Add butter (in pieces over chicken).
Add 3/4 cup chicken broth.
Rub edge of crust with water and add top crust.
Flute edges and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until browned.

title: cherry pineapple salad
directions: Pour gelatin over cottage cheese in its dry form.
Mix.
Add drained pineapple to cottage cheese.
Mix with whipped topping.

title: bean casserole
directions: Drain all beans, peas and sliced chestnuts.
Mix together with mayonnaise.
Spread in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with French fried onion rings and brown.

title: country chicken and biscuits
directions: In a greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish, combine the first 4 ingredients and 1 cup cheese.
Blend soup and 3/4 cup milk (or water or combo); pour over casserole.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: braised apple dumplings
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Melt Mazola in a large skillet.
Add bread and toss lightly.
Cook over medium heat, turning often until toasted.
Add apples, raisins, cinnamon
and syrup; toss to coat.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes, tossing occasionally, turning once or twice until apples are tender. Sprinkle with brown sugar and chopped walnuts.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.
Very good.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions in oil or margarine.
Add all other ingredients, except cooked rice.
Pour over cooked rice in greased casserole dish.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Heat in oven.

title: prize-winning cheese potato balls
directions: Mix potatoes, onions, butter and cheese.
Roll into 8 balls and roll balls in egg and water mixed with salt.
Roll balls in bread crumbs.
Place on greased foil-lined pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Spread with butter and place in greased pan.
Cook sausage until crumbly and place on bread. Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Combine half and half, eggs and salt.
Spoon over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove 15 minutes before cooking.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes uncovered.

title: cheese ball
directions: Use 1/2 nuts.
Mix ingredients and form into ball. Refrigerate overnight.
Roll in rest of nuts in a.m.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Bring water and pineapple juice to a boil; add sugar and jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple and cheese. Refrigerate until mixture partially sets.
Add Cool Whip and nuts. Refrigerate until firm.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Alternately add sifted flour and whipping cream.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese dainties
directions: Separate and spread 1 package of rolls in bottom of 12 x 14-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk until fluffy.
Spread on rolls.
Separate remaining rolls and carefully place on top of cream cheese mixture.
Brush top with slightly beaten egg white.
Bake at 375° until golden.
Glaze with combined powdered sugar and boiling water.
Drizzle over top.
Cool and cut into strips.

title: hungarian goulash(international:  hungary)
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add a little water halfway through cooking time, if needed.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Beat egg, salt, milk and baking powder together.
Add flour to stiffen the batter.
Let stand one hour before cooking.
After one hour, drop dough from spoon into boiling broth.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Will keep in refrigerator for many months.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla and sour cream. Mix well.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add slowly to shortening mixture and blend well.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour. Drop by rounded teaspoon about 2-inches apart on foil lined baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned or when lightly touched until finger almost no imprint remains.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients with about 1 quart whole milk.
Put in ice cream freezer and add enough whole milk to fill line.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; shape into small balls.
Then roll in coconut.

title: will's favorite apple cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In medium saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts. Cut shortening in flour.
Add milk; stir with a fork.
Turn out onto floured board and knead until smooth.
Roll out dough into a large rectangle, about 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle apples over dough; sprinkle cinnamon over apples.
Roll up dough like a jelly roll.
Slice dough into slices, about 1/2-inch thick.
Place in pan with melted butter.
Pour sugar syrup around rolls.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: maple cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add syrup and egg yolk. Mix in flour and salt. Divide in half and chill 2 hours. Roll out to 1/8-inch and cut into shapes. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Cool and glaze.

title: shrimp and okra gumbo
directions: Put a small amount of oil in pot to brown onion and okra together. Once the okra and onion are brown, add bell peppers, garlic and onion tops and smother awhile. Add salt, cayenne pepper and shrimp and cook until the shrimp are pink.

title: tuna and fettuccine
directions: In a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, saute the mushrooms and onions in the oil until tender, about 5 minutes. Add the tomatoes, tuna, broth and pepper flakes.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 5 minutes.
Transfer the tuna mixture to a serving dish.
Add the hot fettuccine; toss quickly.
Add the basil; toss again.
Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese.
Serve immediately.
Serves 2.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, soda and cinnamon. Set aside. Combine and beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla on medium speed until well blended. Stir in zucchini, raisins, nuts and dry ingredients.
Pour into 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Put dry ingredients into bowl and mix well with a fork.
Add shortening and mix well with a pastry blender until ingredients are crumbly.
In a small bowl, beat together 1/2 cup water, vinegar and egg.
Combine the 2 mixtures, stirring until all ingredients are moistened.
Divide dough into 5 portions and shape into flat rounds.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill at least 1/2 hour before using.
This dough can be frozen for future use.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Melt cheese
with lime jello on low heat.
I use a fork to mash and
stir
it	up
until
all is mixed well.
Then add pineapple and pecans.

title: no name cake "simplicity"
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in tube pan at 325° until cake is done.

title: cream cheese braids(very good and easy)
directions: Heat sour cream over low heat; stir in sugar, salt and butter and cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast over warm water in large mixing bowl, stirring until yeast dissolves.
Add sour cream mixture, eggs and flour; mix well.
Cover tightly; refrigerate overnight.

The next day, divide dough into four equal parts; roll out each part on a well floured board into 12 x 8-inch rectangle. Spread 1/4 of cream cheese filling on each rectangle; roll up jelly roll fashion, beginning at long sides.
Pinch edges together and fold ends under slightly; place rolls seam side down on greased baking sheet.
Slit each roll at 2-inch intervals about 2/3 of the way through dough to resemble braid.
Cover and let rise in warm place, free from drafts, until doubled in bulk (about 1 hour).
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Spread with glaze while warm.
Yields 4 (12-inch) loaves.

title: rotel
directions: Heat to boiling. Boil 10 minutes. Seal while hot.

title: tea cakes
directions: Stir in enough flour to make a little softer dough than biscuit doll; roll out about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out with biscuit cutter and bake at 400° for 6 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken, broccoli and carrot casserole
directions: Barely cook broccoli spears; place in buttered casserole dish.*
Add layer of chicken; cover with soup, then add layer of shredded cheese.
Top with cracker crumbs, mixed with 2 teaspoons margarine.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb downside cake
directions: Mix cake mix.
Pour over rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: taco wraps
directions: Cook ground beef.
Crumble while draining.
Put some beef on tortilla; add a little tomato, lettuce and onion and top with cheese.
Roll up.
Pop in microwave for 30 seconds.
Take out and top with salsa.

title: robinson's hush puppies
directions: Mix well.
If too dry, add more milk.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil in skillet or deep fryer.
Cook until light brown and floating.

title: pork chops in crock-pot
directions: Heavily coat chops in next 3 ingredients. Brown in a little oil in skillet.
Place chops in crock-pot.
Pour soup over top. Don't add salt or water.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours. This can be made with 4 chicken breasts (skin removed).

title: sugar-free lemon pies
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Add sugar-free lemonade mix.
Fold in 2 heaping teaspoonfuls of Cool Whip.
Pour into baked pie crust and store in refrigerator for an hour.
Makes 2 pies.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots for 5 minutes.
Drain. Place in greased casserole. Dot with margarine.
Add onion.
Sprinkle with cheese. Top with crushed potato chips. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: granola bars
directions: Place oats in an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, stirring at 5 minute intervals; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add oats and mix well. Spread mixture into a lightly greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hot crossed buns
directions: Soften yeast in water.
In a small saucepan, heat shortening just until melted.
Stir in milk, sugar, salt, cinnamon and currants and allow to cool slightly.
When this is just warm to the touch, add it to the yeast-water in a large bowl and stir in eggs.
Add flour until moisture is absorbed and let rise until doubled.

title: french-style mustard (dijon)
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in pan; bring to boil, then simmer 5 minutes.
Pour and cool.
Strain into mustard.
Beat constantly until smooth.
Blend other ingredients.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Cool.
Store in covered non-metal container.
Chill at least 2 days to develop flavor.
Makes 2 cups of rugged mustard.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Cover cabbage with boiling water and let set 10 minutes, then drain.
Add bacon drippings, vinegar, sugar, water, salt and pepper.
Boil about 20 minutes.

title: pineapple dessert cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on package.
Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350°.
Cool cake.
Cook pudding according to package until thickened.
Cut cream cheese into hot pudding; mix until well blended.
Add well drained pineapple; spread over cake.
Cool thoroughly.
Spread with whipped topping.
Garnish with cherries and nuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken enchilada bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine first 7 ingredients in large mixing bowl and put in greased, 2-quart baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, oleo, oil and vanilla, then add the 2 eggs.
Beat, then add flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sweet and sour carrot pennies
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until just tender.
Do not overcook.
Drain and cool.
Combine remaining ingredients to make a marinade.
Stir carrots into marinade; let stand for 24 hours. Will keep a week.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix well and store in airtight container.
When ready to use, add 1/4 cup of mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add enough water to liquid from drained pineapple to make 1 cup.
Stir into gelatin mixture; add lemon juice.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in other ingredients.
Chill well before serving.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: skillet lasagna verde
directions: In skillet, brown meat and onion until it loses pink color. Spread Ricotta evenly over veal.
Spread noodles on top.
In small bowl, mix tomatoes with seasoning.
Pour evenly over noodles. Cover and cook over medium heat for 20 minutes or until noodles are almost tender.
Sprinkle evenly with Parmesan cheese. Re-cover and let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: sausage-onion squares
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain fat.
Combine biscuit mix with milk and one egg.
Mix well.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with caraway seed.
Top with sausage mixture. Combine sour cream and one egg, blending well.
Pour over sausage and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Remove membranes (stringy, fatty pieces) of the livers.
Melt 2/3 of the butter in a skillet over medium heat.
Add the onions; cook for 2 to 3 minutes (don't burn) until soft.
Add the livers; cook until pink inside, 2 to 3 minutes.
Put mixture in a bowl previously rubbed with garlic clove.
Add the allspice.
Blend in food processor or blender, adding the sherry, then beat in the remaining butter and cream; check the seasoning.
Put in dish; chill.
If keeping, you can put some melted butter on the top. Serves 6.

title: cabbage strudels
directions: Cook cabbage and drain.
Mix cabbage, sour cream, curry powder and salt.
Fold 1 phyllo leaf crosswise into halves.
Brush with margarine.
(Cover others with damp towel.)
Fold leaf crosswise into halves again.
Brush.
Place 1/2 cup cabbage down center of leaf.
Fold long sides, then short, overlapping.
Place strudel, seam side down, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Repeat with remaining leaves.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: vodka sauce
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil.
Add crushed tomatoes, basil, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add vodka and grated cheese.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add heavy cream.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes more.
Add to cooked macaroni.
Enjoy.

title: fried apples
directions: Core and slice apples.
Put oleo in skillet; add apples and cook on medium heat.
Add brown sugar and let cook down.
Add water to start cooking.
Serves 4 or 5.
Serve for breakfast or with pork dishes.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs with fork.
Add sugar, buttermilk, coconut, vanilla and melted butter.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and cook at 325° until firm in the center.

title: potato filling(pennsylvania dutch)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In skillet, saute the celery and onions in margarine.
Pare and boil potatoes in salted water.
When done, mash using just a little milk.
Mix into potatoes the rest of the ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Put into greased baking dish.
Bake for one hour.
Cover for first half hour, uncover for remaining time.
Serves 4 to 6.
