title: grilled salmon
directions: Heat grill to medium. In a very small saucepan, melt butter. Add lemon juice and garlic. Place salmon, skin side down, on grill (do not turn). Baste with butter sauce approximately 3 times while grilling. Grilling time will be approximately 9 to 15 minutes, depending on the thickness of the salmon.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add to the rest of the ingredients and refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight.

title: impossible chicken and broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Thaw broccoli; drain. Mix broccoli, chicken, 2 cups cheese and onion.
Beat milk, eggs, Bisquick, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour over.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: old fashioned fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, stir together first 4 ingredients until well blended.
Add milk and 2 tablespoons of the butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches 234° on a candy thermometer or forms a soft ball when a spoonful is dropped into ice cold water (soft ball stage).

title: star spangled crispies
directions: Place white chocolate chips and margarine in a microwaveable bowl.
Heat at medium power for about 1 minute.
Do not allow chocolate to burn.
Stir until mixture is smooth; combine with cereal and M&Ms red and blue candies.
Drop onto waxed paper-lined sheet pan to set.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: First mix the 2 tablespoons cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar. Second, melt some butter for 15 seconds in the microwave.
Next, open 1 can or more of canned biscuits.
Spread the butter and sprinkle the cinnamon and sugar on the biscuits. Finally, bake them on a pizza pan for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Place milk and vinegar together; set aside.
Mix flour, shortening and salt and then add to the milk and vinegar mixture.

title: pizza by the yard
directions: Brown meat and drain. Add paste, onions, Parmesan, olives, oregano and salt. Cut bread lengthwise in half. Spread meat paste on bread. Top with tomato slices, green pepper rings and Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts and starts to brown.

title: grannie's pecan pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven until set.

title: barbecue flapjacks
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce and Tabasco sauce; simmer.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press biscuits over pan to form crust.
Spread beef mixture over biscuits. Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: quiche
directions: Boil the broccoli flowerets and saute onion in oil.
Mix eggs with Bisquick.
Mix everything together and put in baking dish (10-inch glass greased pie plate).
Spread grated cheese (Parmesan) on top and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in refrigerator.

title: garlic bubble loaf
directions: Thaw and soften dough.
Blend butter, garlic, parsley and salt.
Cut off dough into pieces the size of a walnut.
Dip in butter.
Place pieces of dough into greased loaf pan.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.
Good heated up after being frozen.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water till tender.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over carrots.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Will keep for weeks in refrigerator. Marinade may be used again when carrots are depleted.
Serve cold. Use 1 1/2 qt covered casserole.
Serves 6-8.

title: junior's cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Liberally grease the side and bottom of an 8-inch spring-form pan with butter.
Crush to powder enough graham crackers to lightly coat bottom.
Refrigerate pan until ready to use.
Mix the sugar with the cornstarch.
Add the cream cheese and stir to blend well; stir in egg and blend again.
Add heavy cream, a little at a time and mix.
Stir in the vanilla. Spoon the batter into prepared pan.
Bake for approximately 40 minutes until top is golden brown.
Transfer cheesecake to a rack and let cool for 3 hours.

title: white chocolate candy
directions: Melt white chocolate in microwave, then add peanut butter and Rice Krispies; mix well. Pour in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cut in squares.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Stir in syrup, sugar, dates, nuts and egg.
Cook over slow heat.
Remove and cool enough to handle. Stir in Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Roll into balls, then roll in powdered sugar or coconut.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Cook frozen peas, cool and drain.
Layer head lettuce, chopped celery, green pepper, red onion and peas.
Cover with mayonnaise and sprinkle with sugar.
Top with layer of bacon, broken up. Refrigerate overnight.
Toss and serve.

title: dream pie
directions: Bring strawberries and water to a boil.
Add sugar and stir. Add Jell-O and mix well.
Turn into pie pan or dish and chill until almost jelled.

title: pudding mix
directions: To prepare mix, stir the ingredients together until well mixed.
Store in tightly covered container in a cool place.

title: nice 'n spicy salad dressing(yields 1 cup)
directions: In a small saucepan, combine apple juice, vinegar, garlic powder, cornstarch, oregano, mustard, paprika and black pepper. Bring to a boil.
Cook and stir until thickened, about 2 minutes. Pour into a small bowl.
Cover and chill until ready to use.
Beat with wire whisk before serving.
Contains 11 calories per tablespoon.
Contains less than 1 gm fat per tablespoon.
Contains no cholesterol and .2 mg sodium per tablespoon.

title: almond croissant
directions: Combine all ingredients-let set in refrigerator for 1 hour. Then form dough into little croissant as long as you index finger. Bake on a ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10-15 minutes.
While still warm roll in powered sugar then again when cooled.

title: jolly jumbo bars
directions: Mix and bake at 400°.

title: scalloped green beans
directions: Drain green beans and put in shallow baking dish.
Cover with tomato sauce.
Mix together the bread crumbs and grated cheese. Bake in 350 degree oven until tomato sauce bubble and bread crumbs are brown.

title: cabbage with beer and bouillon
directions: Combine cabbage, bouillon, beer and pepper in a pressure cooker.
Cover securely and cook at 15 pounds pressure for 5 minutes.
Cool pressure cooker at once under cold water.
Drain cabbage; garnish with Parmesan cheese and serve immediately. Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach squares
directions: Beat eggs; drain spinach
and cube cheese. Add to eggs, butter, milk, cheese, onion and spinach.
Blend in flour, salt and baking powder.
Pour into
buttered
x
13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve hot.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat filling, milk and eggs together until well blended.
Combine all spices (sprinkle small amount on bottom of pie shell).
Add blended spices to filling mix and stir well.

title: fudge cupcakes
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Stir in margarine, eggs and chocolate. Stir as little as possible.
Add pecans and vanilla; stir as little as possible.
Fill baking cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: easy deep dish cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
In bowl, mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk together, then pour over melted margarine.
Pour pie filling on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Add vanilla, flour and salt to the creamed mixture. Blend until smooth (the mixture will be crumbly). Spread crumb mixture on blueberries. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. A sugar crust forms on top.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice 1/2 into baking dish.
Blend 1/2 can of soup with knife or spoon over potatoes.
Pour 3/4 cup milk over potatoes.
Add the rest of potatoes (sliced) to the mixture. Blend the rest of the soup and milk and pour over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: creamy laced hot chocolate
directions: Combine chocolate and cocoa in small saucepan.
Stir well. Stir in milk.
Add marshmallow cream.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly with a wire whisk until smooth.
Remove from heat and add Amaretto to taste.
Top with whipped cream, chocolate shavings or marshmallows if desired.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Soften cream cheese and work dry jello in with a fork.
Pour in cup of hot water and marshmallows.
Add 7-Up and orange sections.
Pour in mold and refrigerate.

title: dill onion rings
directions: Bring to boil and pour over onion rings.
Cover tightly in jar.
Let stand overnight.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind peppers, onions and tomatoes.
Soak vegetables in 1 cup salt for 4 hours, then drain.
Mix following ingredients in a large pan and bring to a boil:
vinegar, sugar, mustard, allspice and red pepper.
When boiling, add vegetables and boil 10 minutes. Put into sterilized jars and seal hot.
Pint jars are best.

title: party mints peppermint
directions: Cream potatoes, sugar, salt, butter and extract.
Knead slightly. Roll into cherry size balls; use extra sugar, if needed, to roll.
Flatten; dry overnight.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: In a nonstick saucepan, combine cocoa and margarine.
Stir over medium heat until melted.
Add 1 3/4 cup of milk and the sugar.
Stir until hot, not boiling.

title: easy shower punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except ginger ale. Freeze overnight. When ready to serve, thaw slightly and mix with ginger ale. Any Kool-Aid can be used to change the color of the punch, but raspberry tastes best.

title: sizzling steak fajitas
directions: Blend steak sauce and picante sauce.
In nonmetal dish, pour marinade over steak.
Cover; chill 2 hours, stirring occasionally. In large skillet over medium-high heat, cook onion and pepper in margarine for 3 minutes or until tender.
Remove with slotted spoon; reserve.
Add steak with marinade in same skillet.
Cook and stir 8 minutes or until done.
Add onion and pepper.
Cook until heated through.
Serve with tortillas and your favorite fajita toppings.

title: baked grits
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: peached pears
directions: Peel pears except for small circle near tops; leave stems on. Slice a little off bottom of pear so it will sit straight up. Place pears in pan and fill pan 1/2 way up with water. Add rest of ingredients and cook over medium heat about 15 minutes or until tender. Serves 6.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Brown meat and onion in large saucepan; drain.
Add water, tomatoes with juice, carrots, mushrooms, barley, garlic and oregano.
(Other vegetables may be added or substituted.)
Bring to boil; reduce heat and cover.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes until barley is done.
Add cubed cheese; cover and simmer for 5 minutes until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: potato bake
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: creamy chicken
directions: Debone and skin chicken breasts; cut in pieces and salt. Place chicken in skillet with butter; saute until done. Cut onion and carrots; saute until tender (use very little butter). Cook sweet peas. Cook egg noodles (as on package).

Warm cream of chicken soup using a whole can of milk; heat to boiling. Sprinkle black pepper just for taste. After all has been prepared, add noodles to cream of chicken soup; stir well. Add sweet peas, onion, carrots and chicken. Stir all together. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: coq au vin
directions: In a large pan, put oil, chicken, onions, salt and pepper. Stew for 10 minutes.
Add flour, wine, bouillon and then all other ingredients, except carrots and mushrooms. Cook 25 to 30 minutes. Add mushrooms and carrots and simmer until carrots are soft.
Pour over rice.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar and
Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after
each
addition.
Add flour, baking powder and salt alternately
with
milk.
Stir
in vanilla flavoring. Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: party size chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and cocoa together twice.
Cream shortening and add to sugar and beat until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Sift in dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Blend until smooth.
Add vanilla. Bake in three 9-inch layer pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients together.
Cut in the margarine. Add raisins and caraway seed.
Now add the egg and buttermilk. Mix thoroughly.
Turn into a 9-inch pie pan, spreading evenly. Cut across the top about 1/2-inch deep.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: boiled oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring to rolling boil the sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine. Boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in vanilla, peanut butter and oats. Very quickly spoon onto waxed paper.

title: fantastic ice cream
directions: Mix together and pour in freezer. Finish filling freezer with milk.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and then add cold water, lemon juice and pineapple juice; mix well.
Freeze in a gallon plastic jug.
Remove from freezer 5 hours before serving time. Add ginger ale.
This makes a slush punch.
Serves about 35 punch cups.

title: lower fat chocolate eclair
directions: Mix together pudding and milk.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly.
Layer a 9 x 13-inch container with whole graham crackers.
Top with half of pudding mixture.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Frost with chocolate frosting.
Chill several hours before serving.
Makes about 15 servings.
tags: Betty Crocker light creamy deluxe milk chocolate frosting

title: chicken wrap with mushrooms
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Wrap with bacon.
Arrange strips in crock-pot.
Cover with soup and water.
Cook on slow until tender. Serve over rice.

title: chicken chimichangas
directions: Preheat oven to 475°. Combine chicken, picante sauce, onion slices, cumin, oregano and salt in pan. Simmer 5 minutes or until most of the liquid has evaporated. Brush one side of tortillas with butter. Spoon about 1/3 cup of chicken mixture onto center of unbuttered side. Top with 2 tablespoons cheese. Fold the 2 sides over the filling and fold the ends down. Place in baking dish with seam sides down. Bake in preheated oven for about 13 minutes or until golden brown and crisp. Add your favorite toppings, if desired.

title: a man's favorite
directions: Blend shortening, sugar and egg.
Add raisins and applesauce. Sift spices and salt with flour.
Add in several portions. Before last of the flour, add soda dissolved in the water.
Beat well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: blueberry sour cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously butter 9 to 10-inch spring-form pan or square cake pan.
Combine first 6 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Turn into pan and sprinkle with blueberries.
Combine sour cream, egg yolks, sugar and vanilla and blend well.
Pour over blueberries.
Bake 1 hour or until edges of custard are lightly browned.

title: bride's cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: captain's chicken(curry)
directions: Rub the chicken with salt and pepper.
Rub in Accent, if desired.
Set aside.
Mix rest of the ingredients in large saucepan and cook on low heat for about 30 minutes.
Place chicken in a baking dish and pour rest of ingredients over chicken.
Cover and cook in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Uncover for last 15 minutes of cooking.

title: devils throne sandwich
directions: Place open bun on cooking sheet.
Put
hot cheese on first and then pastrami, fresh onion and top with American cheese on one side of bun and Swiss cheese on the other side.
Heat in oven until hot at 350°.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 2 large loaves or 5 small ones.

title: sweet and sour meatballs and sauce
directions: Combine and form into balls.

title: chocolate decadence cake
directions: Position rack in center of oven and preheat to 350°.
Butter 10-inch spring-form pan with 2-inch sides.
Melt both chocolates with Espresso and butter in heavy saucepan over medium-low heat, stirring until smooth.
Pour into large bowl.
Cool.
Mix in vanilla extract.

title: andy and brian's favorite butter cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour and vanilla and beat well. Bake in a tube pan at 325° for about 1 hour.
Cool.

title: hungarian cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar and lemon juice.
Stir in the almonds. Mix in the cinnamon and cocoa and half the flour.
Mix in remaining flour.
Chill dough for 30 minutes.
Roll out on floured surface, one half at a time, to 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut with a 2 inch round cookie cutter.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 325 degrees for 12 minutes then let it cool.
Put pairs together sandwich fashion with raspberry jam.

title: no-bake roll-ups
directions: Drain and pat dry ham slices.
In bowl combine softened cream cheese, pickles and spices.
Stir until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Spread thin layer of mixture over slice of ham and roll up.
Place toothpick in roll about every 1/2 inch (6 to 8 per roll) and place on cookie sheet.
Continue until all of mixture is used.
Place roll-ups in refrigerator overnight or at least 2 to 4 hours.
When cream cheese mixture becomes firm, slice between toothpicks for bite-size servings.
May be garnished with olives, cheese, radishes, etc.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Beat 4 minutes. Refrigerate for 3 hours. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple delight(healthy choice)
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients together.
Cover; let set for hours or overnight.
Stir and serve.
Delicious and satisfies a desire to have something sweet.

title: chocolate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Beat margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy. Mix in flour, baking soda and the box of pudding. Stir in chips and walnuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from cookie sheets. Cool on wire racks. Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: hog's head cheese
directions: In a 4-gallon stockpot, place all ingredients up to and including the whole peppercorns.
Add enough water to cover contents by 3-inches and bring to a rolling boil.
Using a ladle, skim all foam and other impurities that rise to the surface during the first 30 minutes of boiling.
Continue to cook until meat is tender and pulling away, approximately 2 1/2 hours.
Remove all meat from the stockpot and lay on a flat baking pan to cool. Strain and reserve 10 cups of the cooking stock and discard vegetables.
Return stock to a low boil.
Add all remaining ingredients, except gelatin, salt and pepper.
Boil for 3 minutes and remove from heat.
Season to taste using salt and pepper.
Add dissolved gelatin and set aside.

title: chili sauce
directions: Dice tomatoes, chop peppers, onions and celery in blender or food processor.
Combine all ingredients in large pot and boil about 2 1/2 hours.
Place in hot, sterilized canning jars.
Yield: 20 pints.

title: party time punch
directions: Chill soda and juice.
I fill ice cube trays with juice so when they melt, you still keep flavor.
Add sherbet-juice and soda in punch bowl.
Add ice cubes.
It's done and very good.
Make as little or as much as you want.
Equal parts juice and soda.

title: black and white bars
directions: Cream butter, vanilla and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat.
Add flour and salt and mix until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Divide batter in half.
Add cooled melted chocolate to half the batter.
Drop batter alternately by teaspoonfuls onto greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Run knife through batter several times to marbleize.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool on wire rack and cut into bars.

title: penne alla vodka
directions: Cook pasta as per label directions.
In large skillet over medium-high heat, cook onion in hot butter until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Add vodka; cook 5 minutes.
Blend cream, heat to boiling.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese and heat through.
Toss with hot drained pasta. Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy caramel pecan rolls
directions: Thaw bread dough the night before.
In the morning, roll flat; butter and sprinkle with brown sugar, then cut each loaf into 12 pieces.
Butter 13 x 9-inch pan and put desired amounts of nuts in bottom of pan.
Place the pieces of bread atop of the nuts.
Heat butter, pudding mix, sugar and milk in saucepan until butter is melted and ingredients are mixed.
Pour mixture over bread and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat undrained pineapple until boiling.
Add jello and dissolve.
Cool; add buttermilk.
Let cool and fold in Cool Whip. Mix thoroughly and congeal.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 12 muffin tins.
Stir flour, poppy seed, salt and baking soda together.
In large bowl, beat sugar and butter for 2 minutes.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Beat in sour cream and vanilla.
Gradually beat in flour mixture. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: creamy ginger dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing until well blended.
Chill. Serve with fruit.

title: venison breakfast sausage
directions: Cut deer and bacon into 3/4-inch cubes.
Place in medium mixing bowl.
In small bowl, mix salt, sage, ginger and pepper. Sprinkle over meat; mix well.
Chop or grind to desired consistency.
Shape into thin patties and fry over medium heat until browned and cooked through, turning once.
Sausage can also be frozen uncooked.

title: brisquet
directions: Before marinating brisket, spread with 1 tsp. liquid smoke. Combined ingredients for a 4-5 pound brisket.

title: peanut butter easter eggs
directions: Mix thoroughly and shape into eggs.
Let set until firm in refrigerator.
Coat with chocolate chips, melted.

title: quick tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed.
Add tuna, soup and peas.
Heat over low heat until hot.

title: custard pie
directions: Bake in hot oven for 10 minutes, then slow oven for 30 minutes.

title: corn meal pasties
directions: In bowl, mix pastry (flour, lard and water); refrigerate 1 hour.
Toss meat, rutabaga, onion, potatoes, salt and pepper. Divide dough in fourths; roll into 8-inch circles.
Spoon 1/2 cup filling on 1/2 of circle.
Fold over onto moistened edge, forming a half moon.
Crimp together; cut 3 small slits in top.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: black cherry delight
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Stir in juice from cherries. Add prepared cherries.
Stir in pineapple and pecans.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil, peel and mash potatoes.
Add ingredients and blend. Place in pie crust.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: curry-sour cream appetizer
directions: In a small mix-n-store pitcher, combine all ingredients except vegetables.
Transfer to dip-n-serve bowl.
Apply seal.
Chill until serving time.
Serve with fresh vegetables arranged on dip-n-serve tray.
Makes 1 cup.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Cook onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons oil until tender.
Add tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes or until slightly thickened, stirring occasionally.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs stiff as cake dough, then add all other ingredients and beat well.
Pour in freezer and finish filling with whole milk.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with paprika and pepper.
In a large skillet over medium-high heat, brown chicken in oil.
Meanwhile, drain pineapple juice into 2-cup measuring cup.
Set pineapple chunks aside.
Add water to juice to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Add brown sugar, soup mix, vinegar and ginger; stir until blended.
Pour over browned chicken and bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink when cut along bone.
Transfer chicken to a serving platter; cover and keep warm.
In small bowl, mix 2 tablespoons cold water and cornstarch until smooth.
Stir into liquid in skillet.
Stirring over medium heat, bring to boil and boil for 1 minute.
Add pineapple chunks and cook 2 minutes longer or until pineapple is heated through.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle chicken with almonds and serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla, then add flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Nuts can be added if desired.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until it turns loose from edges.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: in pie pan pie crust
directions: Melt margarine in pie pan.
Mix flour and sugar with the margarine in pan with a fork until it is cool enough to work with your hands.
Shape it in a ball in center of pan; then start flattening it in pan working to edge of pan and up the sides. Flute the edge with fingers.

title: hamburger and cornbread
directions: Brown meat and onion. Drain.
Add chili powder, Worcestershire sauce and tomato sauce. Simmer 15 minutes.
Add beans and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cornbread and pour over.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Add chopped onion, when hamburger is just browned and continue to cook about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake covered with foil for 30 minutes.
If you want it brown, uncover and broil for 5 minutes.

title: bran-brown bread
directions: Blend well together.
If desired, add 1 cup dates, raisins or nuts.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat all ingredients, except shrimp, until smooth.
Add shrimp and beat slightly.
Serve cold.
Very good.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet; press lightly with a fork.
Bake in a 350° oven for 5 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer potatoes, carrots, mushrooms, onion, green beans or peas.
Top with browned hamburger and tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until vegetables are done.

title: sauteed chicken uplands
directions: Salt and pepper chicken breasts, which should be at room temperature.
In a large pan, with a lid, melt butter.
As it begins to brown, put in chicken and brown on both sides.
Add rosemary.
Cover; cook on low heat for almost an hour, basting with butter occasionally.
Toss in mushrooms; cook a few minutes. Add brandy and burn off.
Add Madeira and cream.
Simmer for a short time, spooning juice over chicken.

Serve very hot with dry rice, a bottle of Good Bordeaux and if the right season, young small green peas cooked for a few minutes on very wet lettuce, a lump of butter, a tiny pinch of thyme, salt and a slight dusting of sugar.

title: mom's cheese cake
directions: In a bowl, combine zwieback teething toast with butter and sugar. Mix well and press into bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Set aside.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Dice onions, pepper and mushrooms.
Brown in a small amount of Wesson oil.
Add meat and stir over heat until browned.
Cut sausage into 1-inch pieces and brown in another pan.
Add sausage to pan of meat mixture.
Stir in sugar while mixing.
Chop tomatoes and add to tomato sauce and paste with 1 can of water (use tomato paste can).
Mix well and cook in crock-pot about 5 to 8 hours or on stove top 3 to 5 hours (simmering).

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together. Pour into greased tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Chop or dice onions and celery and saute in olive oil. Combine salmon, celery, onion, cornmeal and flour in mixing bowl and stir with fork until blended well.
(Add milk for moistness, only if needed.)
Form into patties and fry in corn or vegetable oil.
Notice when crust starts to form around the edges, turn over and fry on other side.
Makes about 12 to 16 patties, depending on size.

title: wet coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Poke warm cake with fork.
Mix together cream of coconut and milk.
Pour over warm cake.
Cover and place in refrigerator, overnight is best.
Before serving, spread on Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut on top.
Return to refrigerator between serving.

title: quick taco casserole
directions: Grease deep casserole dish.
Line bottom and sides with corn chips.
Brown hamburger with onions.
Warm chili and add green chilies.
Layer in casserole dish on top of chips the chili mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese, hamburger mixture, sprinkle with cheese and chips.
Repeat until mixture is used up.
Top with cheese and corn chips.
Bake at 350° until heated through (20 to 25 minutes).
Serve topped with lettuce, tomatoes, avocado and sour cream.

title: stuffed pepper pot
directions: Cut thin slice from stem end of pepper.
Remove seeds; discard.
In a skillet, saut onions and brown ground meat.
Add remaining ingredients except peppers; mix well.
Stuff peppers with mixture and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple cinnamon muffins
directions: Combine flour, dry milk, sugar, baking powder, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon and salt in a large bowl.
Beat egg with water.
Stir in apple and butter.
Add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
Batter will be stiff.
Fill 12 buttered 2 1/2-inch muffin cups 2/3 full.

title: vanilla sauce
directions: Scald cream, all but 1/4 cup of milk and sugar in saucepan over medium heat.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup milk and add to cream mixture.
Bring to a boil until thickened (about 3 minutes). Remove and add butter, vanilla and nutmeg.
Cool slightly before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Use
2	quart
casserole
dish.
Blend all ingredients, except crackers.
Crush
crackers	and spread on top.
Place 4 or 5 pats butter on top.
Let cool 6 hours or overnight before baking.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: frozen fruit cups(diabetic recipe)
directions: Beat cream cheese, sour cream, Equal and lemon juice in medium bowl until smooth; gently mix in fruit. Spoon

mixture into 12 paper-lined muffin cups or spread in baking dish, 10 x 6-inches. Garnish with pecan halves and additional fruit, if desired. Freeze until firm, 6 to 8 hours. Let stand at room temperature until slightly softened, 10 to 15 minutes, before serving.

title: gone all day stew
directions: Mix together soup, water and flour until smooth.
Combine with remaining ingredients in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake at 275° for 4 or 5 hours.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Grease 3 cake pans. Mix all ingredients and pour into pans. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Blend ingredients together, except cheese and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mexican caviar(salsa)
directions: Using a bowl, you can put a lid on.
Mash garlic and rub in bottom of bowl.
Leave garlic in bowl.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Cover and chill overnight.
Serve with chips.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: watergate salad
directions: Add pudding mix to crushed pineapple.
Chill.
When well chilled, add remaining ingredients and refrigerate until time to serve.

title: crab and shrimp casserole
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine soup, mayonnaise, milk and sherry.
Whisk until smooth.
Add crab, shrimp and mushrooms and heat until well blended.
Place uncooked noodles in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour heated ingredients over noodles.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: crisp oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal with sugar, salt and flour.
Add melted margarine and mix. Dissolve soda in boiling water and add to mixture.
Form dough into roll and chill. Slice thin and bake in a 375° oven for 10 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, stuffing mix, celery, onions, melted butter, mayonnaise and 1/2 stick butter together.
Pour into baking dish that has been buttered.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: low-cholesterol white sauce
directions: Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.

title: lithuanian honey cake(meduolis)
directions: Cream the butter with sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time. Keep beating until light and fluffy.
Beat in the honey.
Sift the flour with all other dry ingredients.
Add alternately with sour cream.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Stir into a 13 x 9-inch buttered pan and bake in a 325° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Slice cake into five long lengthwise strips.
Then cut each strip diagonally into diamond shapes.

title: easy chicken marsala
directions: Melt butter and saut mushrooms in butter on medium heat. Remove mushrooms from skillet and set aside.
Lightly sprinkle chicken w/Lawry's seasoning salt and sear in mushroom butter on medium-high heat.
Add two cans of soup and mushrooms.
Cover and cook on medium-low heat for one hour, checking occasionally to turn and stir sauce.

title: ruby slipper cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sour cream, water and eggs in large bowl. Blend, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes until creamy.
Spoon 1/3 of batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the gelatin.
Repeat the 2 layers. Spread remaining 1/3 of batter over gelatin to cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until cake springs back when pressed.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Put on plate or rack and sprinkle with confectioners sugar if desired.
Makes a pretty holiday cake.

title: fruit filled crumb cake
directions: Mix together in large bowl the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add eggs.
Cut in margarine; work with hands to form dough. Divide dough in half.
Put one half in refrigerator.
Spread other half in 17 x 10-inch jelly roll pan (bottom and up sides).

title: butterfly fried shrimp(great!)
directions: Add a little water to the eggs to thin; beat well.
Mash shrimp flat.
Sprinkle shrimp with Accent; let sit a while.
Dip shrimp in cracker crumbs, then egg mixture, then cracker crumbs again.
Lay on wax paper.
When all shrimp are finished, lay wax paper on top and press to secure cracker mixture.
Let sit in fridge about 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter together.
Add sugar and continue to beat.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until fluffy. Sift flour; measure and add salt, soda and baking powder.
Sift again.
Gradually add sifted ingredients to creamed mixture and mix thoroughly.
Chill dough in refrigerator for several hours.

title: coconut bars
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Spread evenly in a greased and floured oblong pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs.
Mix flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add to sugar mixture.
Mash bananas and add to mixture 1 cup of pecans, if desired.
Also can add chocolate chips and/or cherries.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until tested dry with toothpick. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: scampi in wine sauce
directions: Put the oil and the garlic in the pan.
Wait 2 minutes, then add scampi and saute with the parsley.
Pour wine and wait few minutes.
Add small spoon of flour, at the end a spoon of butter. Serve with rice.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook meat and onions in a large kettle.
Salt and pepper as desired.
Add spaghetti sauce and mushrooms.
Simmer 30 minutes. Cook macaroni and drain.
Add to spaghetti sauce mixture.
Layer: Meat and sauce mixture, sour cream (spread thin coat over meat), Cheddar cheese (sliced thin), meat mixture and sour cream (spread thin on top).
Sprinkle lightly with Mozzarella cheese.
Makes 2 large casseroles.
This freezes well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: korean barbecued beef(bul ko gi)
directions: Cut steak into narrow strips about 1/4 x 4-inch, cutting strips across the grain for tenderness.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Add meat pieces.
Mix thoroughly.
Marinate meat strips 15 to 30 minutes.
Broil over hot charcoal.
Turn meat only; thin strips should cook for 2 or 4 minutes.
Cooking time depends on degree of doneness desired.
Serves 5 to 6 persons.

title: fruit cup
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and Mandarin oranges well.
Place in large bowl.
Sprinkle pudding over fruit.
Add 1 cup pineapple juice.
If not quite enough, add water to make 1 cup.
Stir in fruit and chill.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: fruit cake
directions: Line loaf pans with wax paper.
Pour mixture in and make sure all air is out.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.
Remove from pans and pour rum or bourbon over while hot.

title: colorade delight salad
directions: Combine cheese and gelatin.
Add 1 cup boiling water gradually.
Stir until smooth and blended.
Chill until partially set.
Add pecans, fruit cocktail and marshmallows.
Fold in cream. Chill until firm.

title: valerie's company carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender in boiling salted water.
Keeping 1/3 cup carrot water, drain carrots and place them in a 3-quart greased casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pork chops and crawfish
directions: Cut meat in small pieces and brown.
Add onion and bell pepper to browned meat.
Cook for a few minutes.
Add roux to pan, plus water.
Cook until tender, add crawfish and more water to gravy if needed.
Serve over rice.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto foil-covered pan. Put in oven and turn oven off. Leave in oven until it cools or overnight. Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: baked beans and franks
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon.
Stir well.
Put into casserole dish; top with bacon strips.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: elegant beef burgundy
directions: Brown the beef in the margarine or butter in a large heavy stock pot.
Add onions, carrots, celery and water to cover the meat.
Add seasonings, coffee and Burgundy.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 2 hours.
Add the mushrooms and the sherry.
Cook 15 minutes longer; serve over noodles.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together flour, sugar and salt. Add egg.
Put mixture on top of peaches.
Drizzle melted margarine over the top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sally's spiced tea
directions: Mix together.
Store in refrigerator.
Heat by the cupful in microwave.

title: souper corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine soup, eggs and milk.
Stir in muffin mix just until blended.
Gently fold in sausage.
Pour into 9-inch square pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: custard ice cream
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients.
Place in a double boiler and cook until just starting to thicken.
Take off heat and cool completely.

title: banana bobs
directions: Cut bananas into crosswise pieces about 1 1/2-inches thick. Insert a wooden toothpick and place on a baking sheet.
Freeze bananas until firm, about 2 hours.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Spread in 8 X 8 inch greased pan.
Sprinkle nuts over top or others.
Bake 15 minutes, insert a toothpick in center to test for doneness.
Cut in strips to serve.
I like just the coconut best. Bake at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cook carrots, sugar, butter or margarine, cloves, nutmeg, salt, raisins, water and cinnamon in a saucepan, allowing to boil for 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: french silk pie
directions: Melt
chocolate
and cool completely.
Cream butter and sugar until
smooth and silky.
Blend in cooled chocolate and vanilla. Add
eggs,	one
at
a time, beating 5 minutes after each
egg. Pour
into	cooled	pie crust and chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Serve with Cool Whip topping.

title: ham yam casserole
directions: Cook green pepper in margarine 3 minutes.
Combine soup and milk, add onions, pepper and mustard.
Blend flour and water.
Add to soup, stirring over low heat until thick.
Add green pepper and ham.
Place in greased casserole and top with fluffy yams. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix together cranberries, pineapple, marshmallows, nuts and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Whip cream and fold in cranberry mixture.
Freeze.
Remove about 1/2 hour before serving.

title: wendy's honey mustard dressing
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Wonderful served over shrimp salad.

title: molded egg salad
directions: In a medium saucepan soften gelatin in water for 5 minutes. Stir over low heat until gelatin dissolves.
Remove from heat and whisk in mayonnaise.

Stir in eggs, relish, onions and peppers. Mix well. Pour into a well-oiled 8-cup mold and chill overnight. You may place this when unmolded on large lettuce leaves and garnish with a few slices of ham.
